title: hot milk cake(good used with berries or other fruit with cool whip)
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs at high speed until thickened, then add sugar, beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Combine flour and other dry ingredients.
Add to batter with vanilla.
Beat until batter is smooth.
Heat milk and butter just until butter melts.
Add to batter beating until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: peaches for fried pies
directions: Mix and cook slowly until thick and dark.
Seal in hot sterilized jars and water bath to insure seal.
Tastes like dried peaches with a lot less work.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix together and shape into balls.
Fry slowly until brown on both sides in 4 1/2 tablespoons of oil.
Drain.

title: raspberry lime chicken
directions: Halve the breasts; bone and skin.
Flatten with hand.
Melt butter in heavy pan over low heat.
Add chicken; cover tightly. Cook slowly until it is no longer pink inside (approximately 5 to 7 minutes), turning once.
Do not brown.
Remove chicken and reserve.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in 12 x 8-inch casserole.
Combine reserved juice, broth, soup mix and pineapple.
Pour over chicken, cover with wax paper and microwave on High for 18 to 22 minutes. Rearrange pieces after a minute.
Remove chicken to serving platter.
Combine flour and water; stir to make a smooth paste. Slowly blend into broth.
Microwave on High 1 minute; stir. Repeat until thickened.
Pour over chicken.
Serve with rice.

title: fudgy christmas wreath
directions: In a sauce pan over low heat cook and stir milk and chocolate chips until chocolate melts and mixture is slightly thickened (about 6 minutes).
Remove from heat and stir in nuts and vanilla. Cool until it starts to set, about 15 minutes.
Line a baking sheet with wax paper.
Spoon mixture by 2 tablespoons full into small mounds to form a wreath.
Decorate with cherries.
You can just pour it out on
wax paper and then cut into pieces when firm. Chill until firm.
This makes a soft fudge.
Keep refrigerated.

title: crusty eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant into 1/2-inch slices.

title: mac and cheese souffle
directions: Melt cheese in with butter and milk.
Mix slightly beaten egg yolks with macaroni.
Add bread crumbs and onion, then milk ingredients.
Beat egg whites and fold in last.
Bake for 45 minutes in moderate oven (350°).

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll dough and press in a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix sour cream and Ranch dressing and spread on dough.
Top with vegetables of your choice:
Grated carrot, broccoli flowerets, diced onion, sliced green or black olives, sliced green pepper and mushrooms.
Top with grated cheese.
Chill. Cut in squares to serve.

title: lemon lust
directions: Blend together the oleo, flour and nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a greased loaf pan for 3/4 to 1 hour at 325°.

title: asparagus frittata
directions: Cook asparagus and carrot in oil.
Beat 6 eggs together.
Add the cheese and thyme to skillet of asparagus and carrot.
Cook 5 to 7 more minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Drain and mash squash.
Saute onion and pepper in oleo.
Beat eggs and add all other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 350° oven until done; approximately 45 to 60 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: veal paprikas
directions: Melt shortening.
Add onions, paprika, salt, pepper and parsley.
Add meat, cover and cook 1 hour.
Add flour, blend well and cook 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 pint sour cream.
Serve with rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cake as directed, except use milk instead of water.
Bake. Bring to boil pineapple and sugar.
Punch holes in cake; pour pineapple mixture over it.
Mix pudding as directed.
Mix with cream cheese.
Spread over cake.
Slice bananas on cake, then spread Cool Whip on cake.
Sprinkle with pecans, coconut and cherries.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Strips off stems and fibrous outer peel of broccoli stalks; cut into pieces, flowerets and stalks.
Place broccoli in large heavy saucepan and add boiling water and cook for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove choice flowerets (2 cups) after first 5 minutes and reserve.
When remaining broccoli is tender, crush with potato masher.
In the microwave, melt
butter and then add flour, evaporated milk, milk, salt, onion powder and Velveeta cheese. Cook until thickened.
Add to crushed broccoli.
Just before serving, add reserved flowerets.
Serve piping hot.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook until thick and clear.
Remove from heat and add 6 tablespoons strawberry Jell-O. Let cool.
Then add fresh strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Let congeal and top with Cool Whip.

title: bean dip
directions: Combine chilies, taco sauce, onions and seasonings in a saucepan.
Cook until onions are tender.
Add beans and simmer until warmed through.
Serve either hot or cold with tortilla chips.
Add grated cheese on top just before serving.

title: pocatello potatoes
directions: Cool
potatoes.
Cut
into
1-inch cubes, leaving skins on. Cube
cheese
and sprinkle over potatoes.
Place in 2 1/2 or 3-quart
casserole	dish.
Add
onion,
pimento
and
bread cubes. Pour melted butter over the top and sprinkle with salt and pepper or
parsley and paprika, if desired.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Beat whites.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to yolks while beating.
Add 1/4 cup sugar to whites after they have been beaten stiff.
Mix egg whites with yolks; stir in cream (whipped if you wish).
Add milk, whiskey and rum.
Mix.
Chill.
Serve with nutmeg.

title: cinnamon punch
directions: Boil 1 cup of water.
Dissolve jello and cinnamon dots in the water.
Add the brown sugar.
Simmer and stir until dissolved. Remove from heat and add apple and cranberry juices.
Serve hot.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Combine ingredients and top with salad dressing and 1 cup sour cream.
When serving, add bacon bits and croutons.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Gel lime jello in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add marshmallows and melt over double boiler.
Add 1 cup pineapple juice, drained from crushed pineapple and cream cheese, softened.
Beat well.
Fold in the crushed pineapple and whipped topping.
Pour gently over lime jello. Chill until set firmly.
Mix cherry jello by package directions. Cool at room temperature.
Pour over chilled layers very gently so it doesn't go underneath.
Chill until set.

title: hamburger-corn casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, make a layer of hamburger (cooked).
Add noodles and mixture of corn, cream of mushroom, cream of chicken, sour cream and pimento on top of it.
Sprinkle bread crumbs soaked in butter over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: lo-cal spice tea
directions: Mix.
Store in airtight containers.
One to two teaspoons for 1 cup boiling water.

title: rice krispy treat
directions: Melt marshmallows and margarine.
Stir in peanut butter, then add Rice Krispies.
Press mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: wine
directions: To
each
gallon, glass jug, add all ingredients; stir. Cover with
clean
wash
cloth or paper towel and secure with rubber band.
Stir
about	once or twice a week.
Let stand 3 weeks. Strain
off fruit and throw away.
Replace wine in jug (which
has been rinsed) for 3 more weeks, covered;
no stirring.
Carefully rack (siphon) wine into clean bottles.
Cork. Be
careful
not
to get
sediment
in	bottom of jug in your bottles.

title: ice cream with hot raspberries(very easy but delicious dessert)
directions: Heat the raspberries on stove or in microwave.
Add sugar to taste.
Pour the hot raspberries over ice cream.

title: fresh peach dessert
directions: Combine marshmallows and milk.
Stir over low heat.
Stir until marshmallows melt.
Let cool.
Fold in whipped Dream Whip.
Add diced peaches and spoon into a 9 x 9-inch round or square graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.
Serve with additional whipped cream topping and sliced peaches, if desired.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Stir in onion, butter, garlic, flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in soup with 1/2 can milk.
Simmer, uncovered, until onions are cooked through. Stir in sour cream and heat through.
Cook egg noodles according to directions.
Pour stroganoff over noodles.
Stroganoff can also be served with white rice.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
If it seems like it is too dry, add some ketchup. Place in a pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Add some ketchup to top and bake for another 15 minutes.

title: applesauce stuffing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
In large bowl, combine stuffing bread, Bell's stuffing mix, sausage, salt, pepper, thyme, Bell's seasoning, chopped apple, onion, celery and applesauce.
Mix together, then add apple juice and water to desired consistency.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Fry sausage.
Arrange bread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with cheese.
Scatter sausage over cheese.
Beat eggs with milk and mustard and add mushrooms.
Pour over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour. Dilute soup with milk and pour over top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
(Place a cookie sheet on lower level shelf in oven to catch spills.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Save broth.
Set aside.
Melt margarine and pour over stuffing mix.
Mix 2 cans of soup with 1 1/2 cups of broth.
Crumble crackers up.
Layer in dish 1 layer of crackers, 1 layer chicken, 1 layer stuffing mix and 1 can soup broth.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let it set about 10 minutes before serving.

title: white frosting
directions: Cream first two ingredients and add remaining ingredients. Beat well on high speed until real fluffy, about 8 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone.
Cut into bite size.
Mix with soups, sour cream and onion.
Pour into baking dish.
Melt butter and stir in crumbled Ritz crackers.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Allow broccoli to thaw or defrost in microwave.
Lay out in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Lightly salt.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: grape juice icebox pudding
directions: Cook the grape juice and tapioca in heavy saucepan until done; will be thick.
Add the sugar, orange juice, crushed pineapple and chopped nuts.
Let mixture partly cool.
Put layer of vanilla wafers in bottom of pan and 1/2 of mixture.
Repeat.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a loaf pan.
In large bowl with a fork, mix first 5 ingredients.
With a pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
With fork, stir in bananas, eggs and nuts just until well blended.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake 55 minutes to 1 hour until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: hatley georgia barbecue chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together in saucepan; heat on low.
Wash and cut chickens in half and salt.
Cook on grill.
Apply sauce several times during cooking until chicken is done.

title: banana split salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and sugar. Stir in pineapple, strawberries, and bananas.
Fold in the whipped topping, walnuts and rood coloring if using.
Pour into an oiled 13x9.2-inch dish.
Cover and freeze until firm, at least 3 hours. Remove from freezer 30 minutes before serving.

title: preacher steak
directions: Roll meat to desired size.
Dip in flour, then into milk and back to flour.
Fry in oil until desired doneness.

title: texas sheet cake and frosting
directions: Mix margarine, cocoa and water in a saucepan, bringing it to a rolling boil. In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, eggs, sour cream, salt and baking soda.
Mix well. Add cocoa mixture and mix all together.
Pour in a
greased and floured 11 x 16-inch cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together first 3 ingredients. Cream the sugar and butter. Add eggs and bananas; blend well.
Add buttermilk and flour alternately; blend well.
Add nuts.
Pour into medium well-greased loaf pan. Bake for 1 hour.
Yields 10 servings.

title: jello-rhubarb jam
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar; let stand overnight.
In the morning, cook slowly until mushy.
Turn off heat and add 1 package Jell-O. Stir until dissolved.
Pour into jars and store in freezer.

title: fudgie chocolate bonbon
directions: Melt chocolate and oil; stir in sweetened condensed milk.
Mix in flour, vanilla and nuts until consistency of play dough.

title: broccoli and sausage dip
directions: Crumble sausage, cook and drain.
Cook broccoli according to directions	and drain.
Melt cheese and mix everything together. Keep warm in crock-pot.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for one hour (or 1 1/2 hr. if in casserole dish).

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat unti light and fluffy.
Add almond extract.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Turn mixture into pan.
Spoon pie filling into the cake in 16 spots, spacing 4 spoonfuls evenly in each direction.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden and cake tests done.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and milk.
Mix well; add sifted dry ingredients.
Pour into 8-inch pie pan (slightly greased).
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Check with knife blade in center.
When knife comes out clean, it is done.

title: orange glazed beets
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium skillet; stir until blended. Add beets to skillet. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Cook 1 minute or until sauce thickens, stirring constantly. Yield: 4 servings.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and sugar and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes and cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzel crust.
Mix water and jello and let set until slightly jelled.
Mix in strawberries.
Pour over the cream cheese mixture.
Cool to set.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Mix all together; bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: oatmeal wheat bread
directions: Wash Concord grapes and pick from the bunch.
Separate pulp from hulls.
Cook pulp until seeds can be removed when strained through a colander.
Add to grape hulls and cook until tender; cool.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together and pour in a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: braised rabbit
directions: Cut rabbit into serving size pieces.
Soak overnight in water to which has been added about a tablespoon of baking soda. Remove, wipe dry and shake in a bag with a mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Brown the meat in hot oil.
Place on a rack in a roasting pan.
Sprinkle with carrots, add 1 cup water and bake at 300° until tender.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream Crisco; gradually add sugars, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and water, beating well.
Combine all dry ingredients, add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in peanut butter.
Shape into balls; place 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Dip a glass bottom in sugar and flatten balls of cookie dough.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove to wire racks and cool completely.
Yields about 8 dozen cookies.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Boil sugar and milk exactly three minutes and remove from heat.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let cookies set up.
Store in airtight container.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut top off bell pepper and remove stem and seeds.
Put peppers in boiling water about 5 minutes or until they turn lighter in color.
This helps to keep the pepper from splitting when stuffed. Spray a large skillet with Pam and saute the onion and the top slice off pepper (chopped).
Add meat and cook until red is gone from meat.
Add the rice and tomato sauce.
Mix well and fill peppers.
If there is any stuffing leftover, put it in the baking dish and put peppers on top.
Add a few bacon bits on top of each pepper and bake at 350°, covered, about 1 hour.
One pepper equals approximately 1 vegetable, 3 meats, 1 starch and 1 fat.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, eggs, shortening and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Shape into balls by teaspoonfuls.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon and roll cookies in this.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove when done.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: barbecue flavor pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in hot oil; add onion and saute.
Mix the next 5 ingredients
in separate bowl.
Pour over pork chops and simmer approximately 45 minutes or until tender.
Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: crock-pot ham
directions: Combine sugar, mustard and horseradish with enough cola to make
soft	paste
(save
remaining
cola).
Rub
ham
with mixture; put
in
crock-pot and add remaining cola.
Cover and cook on low heat
for
to
10 hours or 2 to 3 hours on high heat.
Slice ham and serve the following over slices.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar, water and Karo syrup in a skillet and cook about 20 minutes or until peanuts begin to pop.
Add vanilla and soda and mix thoroughly.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet.
Cool. Break up.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix soups, mayonnaise and American cheese.
Place broccoli in bottom of casserole.
Layer chicken.
Pour soup and mayonnaise mixture over it.
Put almonds on top.
Cover with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° until it bubbles, about 30 minutes.

title: surprise treats
directions: Work cheese and flour together until crumbly.
Add butter; mix with fork.
Mold 1 teaspoon of dough around each olive or wiener. Shape into balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Cover and chill for at least 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: grandma's brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch grease pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
You can ice these.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Combine rice, celery, onion, margarine, parsley flakes, salt, celery salt, pepper and peas with chicken broth.
Place in 3-quart baking dish.
Place chicken over this.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and milk.
Spread over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: time-to-spareribs
directions: You will need a large (14 x 20-inch) oven cooking bag.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Shake flour in oven cooking bag.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add barbecue sauce, onion and green pepper. Squeeze bag to blend ingredients.

title: carrot bars
directions: Combine margarine and brown sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Stir flour and spices into creamed mixture.
Fold carrots and raisins into batter.
Bake in a 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 40 bars.

title: frozen pineapple-strawberry salad
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend with mayonnaise.
Beat in syrup. Mix in bananas, pineapple and strawberries.
Whip cream and fold into fruit mix.
Pour into a refrigerated tray and freeze until firm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans thoroughly.
Toss with green pepper and onion. Marinate in 1/2 cup oil, sugar and vinegar for 24 hours in the refrigerator.
Drain before serving.

title: easy quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 6 ingredients.
Pour in pie shell and top with crumbled bacon.
Bake 1/2 hour.

title: apple dip
directions: Microwave on High chips and milk 2 minutes.
Stir.
Add vinegar and cinnamon.
Stir.
Microwave on High 1 minute.
Stir. Cut apples in 8 sections.
Serve with warm dip.
Makes enough for 6 to 8 apples.

title: egg custard
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add egg yolks and beat well.
Stir in vanilla and milk. Beat egg whites lightly in a separate bowl; fold into pie. Pour into a half baked pie shell. Bake at 350° until brown and center is set.

title: sausage and peppers
directions: Cook sausage, then cut into 1-inch pieces.
Remove from frying pan and saute peppers until soft and transparent.
Add sauce and vinegar; return sausage to pepper mixture.
Mix and serve.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Heat oil and butter.
Saute all vegetables except tomatoes. Simmer about 5 minutes with chicken.
Add spices and flour.
Add tomatoes and chicken broth.
Cover and simmer for about 1 hour. Brown chopped corn tortillas in margarine or butter.
Serve soup in bowl over tortillas, topped with cheese and sour cream.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut slice from top of peppers and remove stems, seeds and membranes.
Rinse, then put peppers in a pot and add enough water to cover peppers, boiling for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Cook and stir hamburger and onions until brown; drain.
Stir in salt, rice and ketchup.
Stuff peppers with the mixture.
Stand in upright, ungreased baking dish.
Cover and cook in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Uncover, cook 15 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: mexican chicken-doritos casserole
directions: Cook chicken (debone and cut up).
In bottom of casserole dish, crumble Doritos.
Mix sour cream, chilies, onions, soup, and 1 cup of cheese.
Add chicken to mix.
Pour on top of Doritos and add remaining cheese.
Cook at 350 for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: meat ball stew
directions: Mix ground beef with 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, pepper, egg, onion and bread crumbs.
Form into balls the size of walnuts.
Brown in hot oil.
Remove meat balls from skillet; pour off all fat except 3 tablespoons.
Blend in flour.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Bring mixture to a boil.
Simmer over low heat 10 minutes, adding more water if necessary.
Add to meat balls in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: balletjes soup(small meatballs soup)
directions: Roll ground beef, cracker crumbs, pepper, salt and egg into small meatballs.
Boil water. Add meatballs and cook, covered, 1/2 hour. Skim off foam.
Add tomatoes, canned soup, dry soup mix, noodles and bouillon cubes. Simmer 1/2 hour. Add potato. Simmer 1/2 hour. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and Crisco.
Add
sugar and eggs.
Beat well. Add flour, milk and flavorings.
Beat
well.
Fold
in coconut. Bake in tube pan at 350° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: dessert salad
directions: Mix jello (dry) and pineapple together in small pan and bring to a boil.
Let cool.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Place in mold and refrigerate.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl; serve salad over a layer of Fritos.
Top with Catalina French dressing.

title: daiquiri punch
directions: In large punch bowl, combine rum and daiquiri mix.
Stir in lemon-lime beverage.
Serve immediately.
Makes 25 servings, about 1/2 cup each.

title: 10-minute spinach and cheese lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat a 13 x 9 baking dish with cooking spray and spoon in a third of the sauce.
Arrange 12 ravioli on top and scatter the spinach over them. Top with half of each cheese.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet (no seasonings).
Drain; place on bottom of oblong cake pan.
Drain green beans; place on top of hamburger.
Place soup on top of green beans.
Place Tater Tots neatly on top of soup.
Cover.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool and cut in squares and serve.

title: veal scallopini with tomatoes
directions: Brown veal in skillet with oil and butter after drenching it in flour.
Set aside in baking dish, leaving liquid in skillet. Add mushrooms and all remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Put mixture over the veal and cover.
Place in preheated oven for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: five-spice beef ribs
directions: Place ribs in a plastic bag, set into a deep bowl.
For marinade, combine soy sauce, sherry or orange juice, garlic, sugar, lemon juice and 5 spices.
Pour mixture over ribs.
Seal bag. Marinate in refrigerator 6 to 24 hours turning bag occasionally. Remove ribs from bag, reserving marinade.
Place ribs, bone side down in a shallow roasting pan.
Pour marinade over ribs.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan pies
directions: Melt margarine. Add to sugar and flour. Add beaten eggs. Mix well. Add syrup, vanilla and pecans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Pour into pie crusts.

title: french toast plus
directions: Mix eggs, milk and dill in flat bowl.
Dip bread in egg/milk mixture.
Heat pan.
Add butter or use nonstick pan.
Build sandwich by placing dipped bread in pan, then cheese, then turkey or ham.
Top with another piece of "dipped" bread.
Cover pan and cook on low until cheese has melted and bread is browned.
Serve with salad and/or maple syrup.

title: orange supreme salad
directions: Combine mixes.
Add hot water.
Cook until thick and bubbly, stirring constantly as it burns easily.
Let cool completely in refrigerator.

title: pepper steak(low-fat)
directions: Trim all fat from steak and cut steak across the grain into 1/8-inch strips.
Place in bowl, sprinkle with meat tenderizer and about 2 tablespoons water.
Set aside while preparing vegetables. Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid, and cut into wedges or peel and wedge fresh tomatoes.
In large nonstick skillet, brown meat strips in 1 tablespoon oil over high heat for about 5 to 6 minutes. Drain off excess fat.
Add garlic and saute 1 minute.
Add dissolved bouillon, Worcestershire sauce, sliced onions and reserved tomato liquid.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender, 30 to 40 minutes.
Six minutes before serving time, add tomato wedges and pepper strips to meat mixture.
Cook over medium-high heat until crisp and tender.
Serve immediately.
(Can be served with steamed rice.)

title: smoked chicken salad with grapes
directions: Place grapes, bell pepper, celery and chicken in salad bowl. Set aside.
In small bowl stir orange juice, vinegar and salt and white pepper to taste until well mixed.
Add oil and tarragon and stir vigorously until blended.
Pour over salad, toss and serve.

title: marinated refrigerator pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers paper thin.
Add chopped onion and chopped bell pepper. Mix sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Pour over vegetables; mix well.
Place in jars with tight fitting lids and refrigerate.
The flavor of these pickles improves with age.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix the flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Add molasses and egg.
Mix and beat together until thoroughly combined.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Roll 1 1/2 inches thick.
Cut into desired shapes.
Bake at 350°, 1 inch apart, for 7 minutes.

title: bubble bread
directions: Mix sugars and cinnamon together.
With shears, cut each loaf into 32 pieces.
Form into balls.
Roll into melted butter, then in sugar mixture.
Place balls in greased Bundt pan.
Let rise for 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert onto plate and enjoy!!

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot	water.	To
Jell-O mixture, add cranberry sauce.
Chill
slightly
and
add other ingredients. Place in mold and chill overnight.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and sour cream.
Add hot potatoes and beat until light and fluffy.
Add salt and soup mix.
Spoon potatoes in 2-quart casserole.
Brush top with butter and paprika. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: "cookies" from the kitchen of grandmother
directions: Preheat oven.
Assemble ingredients, bowl and spoons.
Grease pans and crack nuts.
Remove ten books, seven crayons and one wad of bubble gum from the kitchen table.
Measure two cups of flour, remove Marly's hands from the flour, wash flour off her and measure one cup of flour to replace flour on the floor.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs. Let them get cold to peel by putting into refrigerator. Peel the eggs and cut in half lengthwise. Remove the egg yolks and place in a bowl. Mash the yolks and add mustard, bell pepper, salsa, relish and horseradish. Mix well and add salt and pepper to taste. Place the egg whites on a tray. Using a teaspoon, place the egg yolk mixture in each of the halved egg whites. When finished with filling of each egg white halve, sprinkle with paprika.

title: crock-pot chicken and noodles
directions: Wash chicken.
Place chicken in the crock-pot.
Salt and pepper the chicken. Add 6 cups of water.
Cook on low for approximately 8 hours. This can be cooked on high if you want it to cook faster.
When the chicken is cooked, take it out of the crock-pot to debone.
Put the noodles, soup and mushrooms into the crock-pot.
Mix with the broth. Cook on high until noodles are tender. Add chicken to the noodles, if desired.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Press chopped pecans in pie shells and bake.
With mixer, mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold mixture into cooled pie shells and hollow out middle.
Add favorite pie filling and refrigerate.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach and remove stems.
Soak in salt water 1 hour or until crisp.
Drain well.
Cut in bite size pieces and place in salad bowl.
Add mushroom slices, bacon crumbles, cheese and dressing.
Toss and add croutons and enjoy!

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash finely; blend all ingredients except cheese.
Put in a greased casserole; top with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan.
Let simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: red christmas punch
directions: Chill fruit juice and 7-Up.
Prepare 7-Up ice cubes by pouring
7-Up into 2 ice trays.
Freeze.
At serving time, combine cranberry and apple juice in a punch bowl.
Slowly pour in 7-Up. Add "ice cubes".
Serve.
Makes 35 punch cup servings.

title: salsa
directions: Place all ingredients in food processor or blender.
Process 3 seconds; stir, then process 3 more seconds.
(Should be slightly chunky.)
Makes 2 1/2 pints.

title: quick and easy date-nut bread
directions: Measure out 3/4 cup hot water; add chopped dates.
Set aside. Combine all other ingredients in a large bowl.
Add hot water and dates, mixing well.
Pour into loaf pan.
Cook at 350° about 45 minutes.
Slice while warm and serve with cream cheese.

title: chicken divan
directions: Simmer chicken breasts with onion, celery, carrots, salt and pepper.
Cook broccoli.
Mix soup, sour cream, mayonnaise, grated cheese and seasonings.
Drain broccoli.
Arrange broccoli in bottom of flat greased dish (3-quart).
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Debone chicken and spread in pieces on the broccoli.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Pour sauce over. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Put in the oven at 350° and cook for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: blueberry angel dessert
directions: Cream together cheese and powdered sugar.
Cut angel food cake in half through middle.
Spread 1/2 cake with layer of cheese and sugar mixture, then blueberry filling.
Place other 1/2 cake on top and layer with remaining mixture and filling.

title: bric-chip cookie
directions: Cream oleo and sugars together; add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and oatmeal.
Fold in chips and nuts.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pecan puffets *
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift flour and cream of tartar together.
Add 1/4 cup at a time to creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Shape into one large roll or two small ones. Wrap in aluminum foil and bake on ungreased baking sheets at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: "goodie" salad
directions: Mix dry jello with cottage cheese.
Add drained fruit cocktail and mix well.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Allow to chill 4 hours before serving.

title: rich pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar.
Add shortening and mix.
Work in liquid.
This makes a soft dough, easy to handle.
Roll between sheets of wax paper slightly floured.
This makes enough pastry for 3 big filled pies or 6 one crust pies.
(Can refrigerate a few days.)

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat vegetable oil and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs and bananas, mashed to a pulp; beat well.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to first mixture with milk and vanilla.
Beat well and stir in chopped nuts.
Bake in loaf pan, lined on the bottom with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Cook potatoes until tender (30 minute).
Cool, peel and mash. Combine with next 6 ingredients.
Spoon evenly into 2 greased 9-inch pans.
Combine sugar, pecans and flour.
Sprinkle over top. Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sandpaper cookies
directions: Cream shortening until soft; add sugar and beat until fluffy. Beat in eggs and extract.
Add dry ingredients; mix thoroughly. Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: boiled custard
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and milk.
Cook on high heat until boiling.
Lower heat and stir constantly with a wooden spoon (do not leave it at all). This usually takes approximately 13 minutes. Add vanilla flavoring.
Serve pudding hot or cold.
You may garnish with fruit or bananas, vanilla wafers or nutmeg sprinkled on top.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken in water until done.
Tear into bite size pieces. Grease 9 inch x 13 inch casserole dish.
Place chicken in casserole dish.
Rinse frozen vegetables with hot water and drain.
Pour over chicken.
In a small bowl, combine milk, and cream of chicken soup. Pour over vegetables.
Combine milk, Bisquick mix and margarine. Pour slowly over top of casserole.	Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 10.

title: filet steaks with mushrooms and wine sauce
directions: Saute
mushrooms
in hot butter and oil for 5 minutes to brown lightly.
Stir
in onions and cook slowly for 2 minutes. Season and
set
aside.
Place other oil and butter in skillet and set over moderately high heat.	After butter foam subsides, brown steaks
for
to	4 minutes on each side.
Immediately remove from heat.	Discard bacon.	Season with salt and pepper. Place
on warm platter.
Pour fat from skillet.
Stir in stock and tomato paste.
Boil rapidly until liquid is reduced to 2 to 3 tablespoons.
Add
wine
and
cornstarch
and parsley.
Boil rapidly
for
a
minute to evaporate alcohol and thicken sauce. Add
mushrooms
and
simmer
for
minute.
Spread
sauce and mushrooms over steak and serve.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: fish batter
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Dip fish and fry.

title: strawberry freeze
directions: In a blender combine all ingredients smooth.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix all together.
Butter bottom of baking dish, slice 3 large apples real thin and place in dish.
Put in 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup water and dash of cinnamon over apples.
Take mixture and place over apples.
Bake slow for 35 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cut whole tomatoes.
Put in large pan.
Add both tomato sauce and juice.
Turn on medium low heat.
In frying pan fry hamburger (scrambled); drain and add into sauce.
Put both bags frozen vegetables in sauce.
Peel and dice onion.
Add to soup.
Season to taste.
Cover.
Turn stove to simmer.
Cook for 2 or 2 1/2 hours.
Add a little water if more juice is wanted.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Crumble ingredients together with your hands and top potatoes. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until browned.

title: chicken bone cookies
directions: Mix butter and peanut butter.
Add powdered sugar, graham cracker crumbs, vanilla, and coconut.
Mix well with really clean hands.
Roll in balls and chill.
Melt paraffin with chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Dip cookies in chocolate and place on waxed paper.

title: cool and easy fruited pie
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice, using wire whisk. Blend in whipped topping.
Fold in pineapple and chill until mixture is very thick and well molded.
Spoon into pie crust. Chill 2 hours.
Garnish with pineapple.

title: banana macadamia nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 8 ingredients; beat at low speed until well mixed (2 to 3 minutes).
Add bananas and orange juice; mix for 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in coconut and nuts by hand.
(Batter will be thick.)

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and salt.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Roll into balls and roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon marshmallow whip
directions: Empty 1 can pineapple into bowl.
Add cinnamon red hots.
Let set overnight or until red hots are dissolved.
Remove from refrigeration and add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and serve.

title: date cake
directions: Cream the sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Alternate milk with flour.
Fold in dates.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350°.

title: not-too-sweet icing
directions: Gradually add milk to flour, stirring to blend.
Cook to thicken, stirring constantly.
Let cool.
Beat together shortening, margarine and sugar.
Add flour mixture and beat well. Add vanilla.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: shrimp curry in a hurry
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic until tender. Stir in sour cream, curry powder, salt and pepper.
Let this bubble a minute or so and pour in shrimp.
Serve over raisins or saffron rice.
Can use Minute rice.

title: quick pork and potato bake
directions: Place pork chops in an oblong cake pan.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Spoon soup over chops.
Lightly cover with grated cheese. Sprinkle with onion.
Place frozen Tater Tots in order all over the top of this so meat is completely covered.
Sprinkle with more cheese over Tater Tots.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Turn heat down to 200° and cook an additional 20 minutes.
Serve with a tossed salad for a complete meal, if desired.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Arrange cooked broccoli in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces; put over broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice in a bowl.
Pour over chicken; sprinkle with cheese, then crumbs.
Drizzle melted butter over it.
Bake at 300° about 1/2 hour.

title: the famous smithey human puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter and semi-sweet chocolate chips in microwave for 2 minutes on High.
Stir until well blended.
Pour chocolate mixture over Crispix cereal in large bowl.
Stir until well coated.
Put 2 heaping cups of powdered sugar into a large paper grocery sack.
Pour in coated cereal.
Roll down top of sack and shake, shake, shake.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients, except candy kisses, in large mixing bowl.
Mix on lowest speed of mixer until dough forms.
Shape into 48 balls.
Roll each ball in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top each cookie immediately with a candy kiss.
Press down firmly so cookie cracks around the edges.

title: peanut zucchini bread
directions: Scald
peanuts	in
boiling water until skins are soft. Grind peanuts up fine.
Mix zucchini and peanuts, then add all other ingredients,
mixing
well.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: linguini salad
directions: Boil pasta 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not rinse.
Put in bowl; add Zesty Italian salad dressing and 1/2 bottle Salad Supreme seasonings.
Toss; served chilled.

title: mrs. polly's divinity
directions: Measure 1/2
cup
sugar
and
cup	water
in small boiler.
In
large boiler, measure 3 cups sugar, 1/2 cup water and Karo.
While
both	mixtures
cook,
beat egg whites until stiff. When
mixture
in small boiler forms hard ball in cold water, pour slowly, beating at the same time, into egg whites. Add vanilla. When
mixture in large boiler forms soft ball in water, pour
into other mixture and stir until firm.
Beat in pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: halibut (or salmon) with vegetable crest
directions: Lay fish in single layer in shallow pan.
Pour lemon juice over fish.
Mix together all other ingredients.
Mound vegetable mixture atop the fish.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° to 450° oven until fish flakes with a fork (about 15 to 20 minutes).

title: crescent galric toast
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush each triangle with salad dressing. In small bowl, combine Parmesan cheese and basil.
Sprinkle over each triangle.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 11 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix milk, eggs and corn together; beat well.
Add meal, baking soda, salt, jalapeno peppers and cheese.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prick potatoes with a fork.
Put them on a baking tray.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Push a skewer through the biggest potato.
If it is soft, it is cooked.
Cut potatoes in half lengthways and scoop out the middles.
Mash potato in a bowl.
Add rest of ingredients and mix everything together well.
Fill potato skins with the mixture and bake them for another 15 minutes.
Decorate with parsley.

title: meat loaf
directions: Saute onion and bread in butter.
Combine remaining 6 ingredients in large bowl. Add mixture to bowl, mix well.
Spread in casserole dish (use 9 x 13-inch for thinner pieces or 8 x 8-inch for thicker pieces).
Spread top of casserole with sauce and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: jello pudding cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Remove from oven and poke holes quickly through cake with the round handle of a spoon or straw at 1-inch intervals. Combine pudding mix with sugar.
Gradually stir in milk, then beat at low speed, not more than 1 minute.
Quickly pour about half of the thin pudding over warm cake and into the holes.
Allow remaining pudding to thicken slightly, then spoon over top, swirling it to frost.
Store cake in refrigerator.
To use regular Jell-O pudding, follow the recipe on the box.

title: microwave milk chocolate peanut butter bark
directions: Melt chips in microwave.
Stir often.
Add peanuts.
Pour into foil lined 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Break into pieces.
Yields 2 pounds.

title: tuna sauce for spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and garlic lightly in butter or olive oil.
Add tuna.
Dissolve tomato paste in water.
Add seasoning, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes at low heat.
Stir occasionally.
Makes enough for 1 pound spaghetti.
Sprinkle with grated cheese before serving.

title: blueberry muffins(low-fat)
directions: Beat margarine, Splenda and applesauce.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, and add vanilla.
Alternately add sifted flour, baking powder and salt combination and milk. Fold in berries. Spoon into paper-lined muffin cups. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: creme puff dessert
directions: Bring the margarine and water to a boil to melt margarine.
Add the flour.
Add the eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
This will be very puffy.
Remove from oven; let it cool slightly and then press it down in pan.
Let it cool.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Add 1/2 stick of margarine and the cheese.
Mix.
Pour into buttered casserole.

title: spicy tomato juice
directions: Quarter tomatoes; place in 6-quart kettle. Add celery, onion, green peppers and parsley. Simmer, uncovered, until vegetables are tender, about 45 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cool slightly. Put through a sieve or food mill. Return to kettle. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Bring to boil. Remove from heat; cool. Pour into freezer containers; freeze up to 12 months. Yields 5 quarts.

title: meatballs in chicken broth(polpette in brodo di pollo)
directions: Combine meat, garlic,
Parmesan cheese, parsley, bread, salt and pepper.
Shape into small dime-size meatballs.
Bring broth to boil and drop
in meatballs.
(Do not fry meatballs.) Boil on medium heat for 5
to
8 minutes.
Serve with Parmesan cheese. Makes 6 servings.
This is a great first course.

title: crock-pot round steak
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and put in the crock-pot.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Combine baking soda, which has been dissolved in the boiling water and cooled, molasses and egg yolk.
Be sure soda water is not hot.
Combine flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, ginger, brown sugar and salt; mix well.
Stir in shortening with a fork, working until it is crumb consistency.
Put 1/3 of crumb mixture in pie shell.
Pour on half the liquid mixture and then top with 1/3 more of the crumb mixture.
Add the rest of the liquid mixture and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake 10 minutes at 400° until shell begins to brown.
Turn oven to 325° and bake until the center is a bit firm, about 30 minutes.

title: coke cake
directions: Cool slightly, then stir into flour mixture with 1/2 cup buttermilk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir in 2 whole eggs and mix well.
Pour into well-greased large cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: 5 spice beef and rice(serves 8)
directions: Cook onions and beef in oil; drain.
Add rest of ingredients; simmer until rice is tender.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, covered.
Add cheese to melt.

title: zucchini pizza fritta
directions: Make bread dough by mixing flour and yeast together, adding a little water at a time.
Let dough rise for about 1 hour.
Wash zucchini flowers and cut into small pieces.
Add to dough mixture. Grate zucchini and add to mixture.
Add egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Let dough rise another hour, then cut into small pieces. Shape like a patty.
Deep fry in skillet until golden brown.

title: tuna casserole
directions: A grandmother is a lady who has no children of her own, so she likes other people's little girls.
A grandfather is a man grandmother.
He goes for walks with the boys and they talk about fishing and tractors and like that.

title: cucumber boats with caviar
directions: Sprinkle insides of cucumber halves with salt.
Invert on paper towels to drain several hours until dry.
Blend cream cheese, onion powder, Tabasco and sour cream.
Gently stir in 3/4 of the caviar.
Put caviar mixture into cucumbers, mounding slightly.
May be prepared and refrigerated up to 5 hours.
Cut cucumbers crosswise in 3/4-inch slices.
Garnish each with remaining caviar and parsley.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: fruit nog
directions: Combine orange juice, nonfat dry milk and 3 cups water; beat until thoroughly blended.
Chill before serving.
Sprinkle cinnamon over each.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: shrimp salad sandwiches
directions: Boil shrimp until they turn pink.
Drain and set aside.
In food processor, blend celery and shallots together until they are a smooth consistency.
Remove celery mixture from processor. Combine shrimp, eggs and sweet relish in processor for 15 seconds. Add this mixture to celery mixture.
Add mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper.
Combine well and spread over your favorite bread.

title: tea bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until brown (when center falls in) at 325° to 350°.

title: grampy's fish chowder
directions: Cut fish into bite-sized pieces.
Simmer in just enough water to cover fish until fish turns white.
Remove fish and set aside. Add water to the same pot and boil potatoes until just about done. Remove potatoes.
At the same time, cook onions in saute pan with butter until soft and translucent.
Now, in large pot, combine fish, potatoes, onions, cream and milk.
Heat on low.
Do not let boil! Cover pot and let sit for a half hour or so.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix pudding as directed, except use 2 cups ice cream for one of the cups of milk called for.
Pour into shell and refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: scandinavian cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, egg yolk and flour together.
Form dough into little balls (size of walnut). Roll balls in slightly beaten egg white, then in nuts.
Place balls on greased baking sheet.
In each one, press thumbprint to make a hollow.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.
Cool. Drop jelly or jam in center.

title: the "dish"
directions: Saute meat, onions and peppers in about 2 tablespoons cooking oil.
Add rest of ingredients except noodles and cheese.
Cook slow for about 30 minutes, then add cooked and drained noodles and cheese.
Pour into 1 large or two medium casseroles.
Cover with more grated cheese and bake in moderate oven about 30 minutes. This freezes well.

title: 4 layer easy dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts.
Press like pie crust in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° or until slightly brown. Cool.

title: frosted watermelon delight
directions: With serving spoon, scoop meat from watermelon half in spoonfuls, reserving shell.
With a paring knife, remove surface seeds from watermelon with tip of knife.
Return watermelon to shell with rounded side up.
Chill overnight.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Mix drained fruit with Cool Whip. Chill and serve.

title: cottage cheese jello salad
directions: Blend cottage cheese in blender until smooth.
Add 2 packages of your favorite jello (dry); continue to blend until thoroughly mixed.
Remove from blender; stir in Cool Whip and then your choice of fruit (peaches, fresh blueberries, pineapple and coconut, etc.). Chill 4 hours or more before serving.

title: christmas cranberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter and sugar in bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, sour cream and lemon rind.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in cranberries and walnuts. Pour into greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes or until loaf tests done.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 15 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Wrap in foil for 24 hours before slicing.

title: frozen pudding
directions: Combine egg yolks, sugar, fruit juice and salt in top of double boiler. Cook over boiling water until thick. Cool.
Add 3 stiffly beaten egg whites. Fold in 1 cup cream (whipped).
Spread half of the cookie crumbs in bottom of an 8 or 9-inch pan.
Pour in pudding mixture. Spread remaining crumbs on top.
Freeze.
To serve, cut in squares. Garnish with additional whipped cream and cherry.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Melt butter and cool.
Mix all ingredients together and pour in pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: kung pao chicken(hot and spicy chicken)
directions: Cut chicken into 1 1/2-inch strips.
Combine ingredients with 1 tablespoon oil and add chicken.
Let sit for 15 minutes.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: You will need a paper grocery bag and Pam cooking spray.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine ingredients. Sprinkle cinnamon on top. Bake at 325° for 2 hours. Stir every 1/2 hour.

title: "puppy chow"
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter in double boiler or microwave.
Add cereal and coat well.
Set off burner to cool for awhile.
Put in paper bag with powdered sugar.
Shake until well coated.
Pour on wax paper or a tray and separate with fork or fingers.

title: sesame swiss chard saute
directions: Heat oils in large skillet and saute onion or leeks 2 or 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover.
Simmer on low heat, stirring occasionally, until chard is wilted and tender, about 4 to 5 minutes.
May sprinkle with toasted sesame seed before serving, if desired.

title: ladyfinger cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese (at room temperature), sugar and vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: hearty oat bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, mix dry ingredients.
In small bowl, beat Egg Beaters; add milk, honey and margarine and stir into dry cereal mix just until blended.
Let stand 4 minutes until thick.
Fill 12 paper lined cups.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil the first 5 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Add the soda; stir.
It will foam.
Add quickly to the popped corn.
Stir.
Put on cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour; stir every 15 minutes. Take out, cool and break apart.

title: my mom's oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add the eggs, milk, oatmeal, flour, soda, salt and spices.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: quick cheesecake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O using only 1 cup water. Chill until partially set. Blend cream cheese and sugar. Whip milk until stiff. Add cheese mixture. Beat again. Pour into crust. Chill until firm. Makes 12 servings.

title: blueberry banana pie
directions: Combine softened cheese and sugar; beat at low speed until fluffy.
Spread into the bottom of pie shell.
Place bananas over the cream cheese mixture.
Next, spread pie filling over bananas. Top with whipped cream and chill.

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: Put sugar and syrup in 4-cup microwave bowl.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts and microwave 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except baking soda and microwave 2 minutes. Add baking soda.
Stir well, then spread on ungreased cookie sheet.
You can vary the flavor by using brown sugar, maple flavoring, etc.

title: pimiento cheese spread
directions: Grate cheese. Let stand until warm (room temperature). Mix well in mixer or blender. Add mayonnaise until right condition to spread.

title: grilled cheese sandwich pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Generously grease an 8 or 9-inch pie pan.
(Lightly spoon flour into cup to measure and level off.)
In small mixer bowl, combine flour, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup milk. Using a rotary beater or electric mixer at lowest speed, beat just until smooth.
Blend in remaining milk and 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour into prepared pie pan. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown. Sprinkle remaining cheese over top. Bake about 2 more minutes until cheese is melted.
Makes 16 servings.

title: one minute chocolate icing
directions: Place all 5 ingredients into saucepan and boil for 1 minute. Let cool and place on cake.

title: alex's bean dip
directions: Mix beans and
salsa until it looks good, then eat with tortilla chips.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Put vegetables in bowl.
Mix vinegar, oil and sugar.
Pour over vegetables.
Marinate at least 24 hours.

title: marshmallow bars
directions: Melt peanut butter in microwave oven for minute or two.
Add one package of chips, stir and microwave for 1 or 2 more minutes until melted.
Then add the other package of chips.
Stir so chips will melt.
If needed, microwave again.
Add marshmallows.
Stir and put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set in refrigerator.

title: ground beef 'n tater casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet, drain. Combine beef, green beans, soup, salt & pepper. Pour into 1 1/2 qt. casserole.
Combine mashed potatoes and 1/2 can onions.
Spoon potato mixture in a mounded ring around top of outer edge of casserole. Bake, uncovered at 350 degrees for 25 min. Top potatoes with cheese and remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: mint cup(may prepare ahead.  serves 6.)
directions: Boil mint, sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Strain the syrup. Add the lemon juice, salt and food coloring.
Chill well.
Add ginger ale before serving.

title: sausage-kraut dumpling casserole
directions: Drain sauerkraut.
Mix remaining ingredients to make dumplings.
Cut off by teaspoon into boiling water.
Cook just until they rise to top of water.
Drain and rinse.
Mix together with sauerkraut and sausage.
Put into a casserole dish with small amount of water (about 1/2 cup).
Heat in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: toasted pecans(club member: nicholas thompson)
directions: Place pecans on cookie sheet; pour melted margarine over pecans, coating each pecan with margarine. Preheat oven to 350°. Toast until brown. Salt to taste.

title: hot peppers and wieners
directions: Combine everything, except wieners and peppers, in very large pan or dishpan.
Bring to a good boil.
Add peppers and wieners and boil for 10 minutes.
Pack in pint jars.
Cold pack 15 minutes in boiling water bath.
Yields about 14 pints.

title: taco party dip
directions: Mix sour cream and cream cheese together.
Spread on a large platter or pizza pan.
Top with salsa, then vegetables.
Sprinkle on grated cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.
Mmm good!

title: green salad
directions: Mix well together.
Garnish with chopped nuts.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Mix all ingredients, except raspberry preserves.
Beat at low speed, scraping sides of bowl often, until mixture is crumbly. Reserve 1 1/2 cups of crumb mixture; set aside.
Press remaining crumb mixture into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Spread preserves to within 1/2-inch from edge of unbaked crumb mixture.
Crumble remaining crumb mixture over preserves.
Bake in 350° oven for 42 to 50 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool and cut into bars. Makes about three dozen.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Into large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, pudding mix, sour cream, oil, water and eggs.
With electric mixer at medium speed, beat about 5 minutes.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Turn into a greased 12 cup fluted or swirled tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on rack for 10 minutes, then remove from pan and cool completely.
Serve with whipped cream, vanilla ice cream or a soft white frosting.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° about 25 minutes in a 13 x 9 pan.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Roll chops in flour and brown in oil.
Slice potatoes thin in long casserole dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add onion slices, then pork chops.
Mix soup and milk and pour over chops.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, celery, onion, pepper and green peas in large bowl.
Spread mayo or vegetables, sealing to edge.
Sprinkle cheese evenly on top, then bacon bits.
Cover and chill overnight. Mix when ready to serve.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: shrimp with dirty rice
directions: Cook rice until almost done.
Saute onion in shortening.
Add shrimp; cook until brown.
Add garlic, green onions, parsley, red pepper, water and salt.
Pour over rice.
When water is absorbed, put in large baking dish and dot with butter.
Brown for about 15 minutes.

title: cherry crumb pie
directions: Line two 9-inch pie plates with pastry; make high fluted edges.
Combine cherries, juice and water, 1 1/2 cups sugar, tapioca, 1/2 teaspoon salt, almond flavoring, butter or margarine and food coloring.
Divide evenly into the two pie shells.

title: chocolate hershey cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, then syrup and flour.
Mix well.
Pour into slightly greased pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Brown onion and okra in the margarine.
Add the tomatoes and bring to a boil.
Simmer until done, about 30 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Add the gelatin, water and oil to the cake mix; beat until smooth.
Add the eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Add berries and mix well.
Bake in a greased, floured pan.
This makes three layers.
Let the layers cool completely and fill with the icing mixture; make as follows:

title: baked spinach
directions: Cook spinach (slightly underdone).
Drain well; set aside. Melt butter.
Add celery and onion.
Saute until golden.
Combine with spinach.
Add sour cream, eggs and bread crumbs.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted and bubbly, approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for 2 hours at 250°.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and place in casserole (use Pam for easy cleanup).
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and remaining 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for approximately 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together with crackers on top and pour margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Chop onions fine and brown in frypan.
Add meat that is in fine pieces and brown well.
Place in saucepan and add sauce, water and fines herbes.
Cook for 4 to 5 hours on simmer or low.
Keep covered at all times while cooking.
Best to prepare the day before serving and refrigerate.
Continue to keep it covered.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix salmon with enough cracker crumbs to absorb salmon liquid. Add celery, onion and eggs; form into patties.
Beat eggs with fork; add milk.
Coat patties with egg mixture, then crumbs. Refrigerate 1 hour or longer before frying.
Fry in oil until nice and brown on both sides.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Place broccoli, onion, raisins, sunflower seeds and bacon in a bowl.
Toss with mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Mix well.
Keep refrigerated.

title: hawaiian grilled chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients in a shallow dish or heavy-duty Ziploc plastic bag.
Add chicken.
Cover or seal and refrigerate one hour. Place chicken on a lightly greased grill rack.
Cook, covered, with grill lid over medium hot coals (350° to 400°) for 20 to 25 minutes or until done, turning halfway through cooking time.
If not cooking on grill, use grill or bake in oven.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry tall cake
directions: Cook 4 layers and place in freezer overnight.
Slice strawberries and mix with glaze.
With electric mixer, beat cream cheese, whipped topping, granulated sugar and confectioners sugar until well blended.
Place 1 layer of frozen cake on serving platter.
Spread thin coating of cream cheese mixture over layer. Place 1/3 strawberry glaze mixture over cream cheese mixture. Repeat with two more layers.
Add last layer.
Cover with cream cheese mixture.
Place 3 tablespoons glaze in center of top layer. Place reserved strawberries around glaze.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook wild rice mix as directed.
Brown ground beef and onion. Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand overnight or several hours.
Bake in 3-quart casserole at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hawaiian banana split pie
directions: Crush and cover bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch dish with wafers.
Cream egg whites, cream cheese, flavoring and confectioners sugar.
Spread on top of vanilla wafers.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese and mix with sausage. Add Bisquick and mix well. Roll in
one inch balls. Bake at 350 for 15 -
20 minutes. Freezes well.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in 1-quart casserole dish; coat sides.
Beat eggs in casserole, then add remaining ingredients, one at a time, mixing with fork after each addition.
Bake in 375° oven for approximately 1 hour or until firm and golden brown.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Place spinach on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan or large bowl. Spread green onion, then celery.
Add the water chestnuts or cucumbers, then the peas.
Spread the mayonnaise next; sprinkle with sugar and Parmesan cheese.
Cover; place in refrigerator overnight.

title: dill pickle recipe (hot jar)
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Pack into hot jars.
Put 1/8 teaspoon of alum on top.
Add 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon pickling spice, 1 garlic button, 1 hind dill and 1 little green strong pepper.
Into each quart, use 1/4 vinegar to 3 parts water (more vinegar if desired).
Seal.

title: dorthy's orange slice cookies
directions: Cut candy in small pieces.
Add nuts and graham cracker crumbs and mix.
Melt margarine and marshmallows in a double boiler until melted.
Mix with crumb mixture.
Mix with hands until mixed well. Roll into rolls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Chill until it can be sliced.
If you chill it long, it is hard to slice.
Slice and dust with powdered sugar.

title: apple butter
directions: Sieve 7 cups of apple pulp.
Cook all ingredients over high until hard boil (rolling boil which cannot be stirred down); stir constantly for 1 minute.
Pour into jars.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: In bowl, mix milk, egg, soda and salt, then add flour.
I add melted butter last so you won't get lumps.
Fry on grill.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cornflakes and melted butter. Spread into a greased baking dish.
Mix crushed cornflakes and melted butter; sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tuna bake
directions: Cook and drain macaroni; blend in softened cream cheese, mushroom soup and drained flaked tuna.
Add pimento, onion, mustard and milk.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Combine bread crumbs and melted butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: lemon cream punch
directions: Mix juice, rind, sugar and cream together.
Put 4 tablespoons mixture into julep cup.
Fill with beverage and stir well. Garnish with mint.
Serves 8.

title: surprise sugar cookies
directions: Put flour and sugar in a bowl.
Make some flat stuff.
Put on a pan.
Put it in the oven to bake with sugar on top.

title: sweet potato nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and sweet potatoes.
Sift together dry ingredients; add nuts and stir into creamed mixture with coffee.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 5 inch loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Line a deep casserole with waxed paper; set aside.
Heat water and onion to boil. Remove from heat.
Stir in potato flakes; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream, vinegar, mustard and pepper.
Set aside 1 hard-cooked egg.
Chop remaining eggs.
Add eggs, celery, pimento and mashed potatoes to mayonnaise mixture in bowl.
Spoon half of potato mixture into bowl.
Layer ham evenly over mixture. Top with remaining potato mixture. Garnish salad with remaining hard-cooked egg, sliced.
Refrigerate 6 hours.

title: slush
directions: Boil tea bags and 2 cups of water.
Add the booze, lemonade and orange juice along with 7 cups of water.
Mix and freeze. Scoop into glasses and top with 7-Up.

title: spaghetti with zucchini sauce
directions: Saute in a large skillet oil and onion.
Add zucchini and rest of ingredients (except noodles).
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes. Uncover and simmer for 10 more minutes.
Discard bay leaf.
Cook spaghetti noodles according to package.
Serve noodles with sauce and grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: yionvarlakia veloute(minced meat and rice balls in veloute sauce)
directions: Saute the onion and mix it with the minced meat and parsley. Next add the washed rice, the egg yolks and season with salt and pepper.
Knead well and shape into small balls.
Roll them in flour and cook in hot salty water for 15 minutes; add a few drops of lemon juice.
Beat the egg yolks with the juice of 3 lemons; season with salt and pepper.
Add a little stock and continue beating. Pour the egg mixture into the soup and stir for a while.
Serve sprinkled with chopped parsley.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour 6 mini-loaf pans or 2 regular loaf pans or 4 (1 pound) coffee cans.
In large bowl, beat together sugar, eggs, oil, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Sift in flour, baking soda and baking powder; beat.
Add pumpkin and water; beat.
Stir in walnuts and raisins.
Fill containers 2/3 full.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Test.
Let set in cans or pans for 20 to 25 minutes. Remove.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In mixer combine confectioners sugar and peanut butter.
Blend to meal consistency.
Place half in baked pie shell; save other half for top of pie.
Combine egg yolks, salt and small amount of milk.
Add to heated milk, stirring constantly.
Mix sugar and cornstarch; add to heated milk, stirring constantly.
Add butter. When thickened, remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour over other ingredients in pastry shell.
Add remaining peanut butter and sugar over top of pie.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Cook first 8 ingredients until boiling.
Add flour and mix well.
Bake in a large loaf pan (greased) for 2 hours at 275°.

title: fuzzy bananas
directions: Cut bananas into bite size pieces. Dip into yogurt and roll in coconut.
Use toothpick to serve.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Layer the last 4 ingredients on top of the cornsticks and beans.
Mix 1 cup mayonnaise and 1 cup sweet pickle juice and spread on top.
Chill.
Serves approximately 10 people.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni until tender.
Saute green pepper and onion, which has been chopped.
Add one can tomatoes, which have been broken up until squashy.
Add salt, pepper and dash of sugar. Simmer for awhile.
Layer in a casserole the macaroni, sauce mix, etc.
Top with seasoned bread crumbs mix and sliced cheese.
Bake about 30 minutes in 375° oven.
Good with slaw as a salad.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Slice potatoes and layer in pan.
Add several slices of onion, if desired.
Put pork chops on top, then mix soup and pour over chops and potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: three soup chicken
directions: Saute celery and onion.
In a Dutch oven, melt oleo with soup, sauteed onion and celery, and rice.
Stir well.
Put salt, pepper and paprika on chicken, cover chicken with soup mixture.
Place into Dutch oven, cover and put in preheated 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: cucumber and onion salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate for at least 3 hours.
Drain before serving.

title: buttermilk hush puppies
directions: Heat 2 to 3 inches shortening or oil to 365° in deep fryer or deep saucepan.
Combine cornmeal, flour, baking soda and salt in large bowl.
Stir in buttermilk, egg and onion.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, a few at a time, into shortening or oil.
Fry 2 minutes or until dark golden brown.
Turn as needed for even browning.
Remove with slotted metal spoon.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: mushroom bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread over bread. Toast at 400°.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Mix tapioca with liquid.
Combine with all other ingredients. Place in heavy pan with tight lid, no steam holes (foil will work).
Bake at 250°
for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: pink fluff
directions: Boil pineapple and sugar for 5 minutes.
Add jello; stir and cool.
Beat the cream cheese and milk until fluffy.
Fold into jello.
Chill.

title: meat and potato casserole
directions: Brown ground meat.
Add sliced potatoes and can of soup.
Cook until potatoes are done. Season to taste.

title: dijon chicken
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients.
Place chicken in small casserole and pour sauce over it.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican skillet lunch(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cook sausage until lightly browned, stirring to keep meat crumbly.
Pour off drippings.
Add onion and green pepper and continue to cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, macaroni, sugar, chili powder and salt.
Cover and cook 30 minutes over low heat.
Stir in sour cream and cook just until heated through.

title: orzo casserole
directions: Melt butter in frypan.
Add chopped onions and mushrooms. Saute until soft.
Add soup mix, soy sauce and 1/4 cup water. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook orzo according to directions on package.
Drain and put in 2 quart casserole, adding mushroom and onion mix.
Stir all together and bake 20 minutes at 300°.
This can be reheated and if too dry, add a little water.
Serves 10.

title: hominy grits supreme
directions: Mix hot grits, butter and cheese until cheese is melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart casserole and sprinkle with additional cheese and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until set.
Serves 10.

title: taco rice
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; add salsa, tomato sauce and bouillon cube.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat to low and simmer 5 minutes, covered.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Garnish with chopped tomatoes, sour cream, grated cheese and black olives.

title: pecan delights(a crisp cookie)
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs to creamed mixture and beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to mixture.
Add pecans; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Yield: 7 dozen.

title: fred's peanut brittle
directions: Butter (grease) cookie sheet and set aside.
Stir white sugar and corn syrup into a 2-quart bowl and microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add salted peanuts and microwave on High for 4 minutes. Add butter and vanilla; stir in well and microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Stir gently until foamy.
Pour quickly into buttered cookie sheet.
When brittle has cooled sufficiently to touch with tips of the fingers, pick up the batch of brittle and turn it over.
This forces the peanuts to come to the surface on both sides.
When hardened, break with a small hammer.

title: baked shrimp
directions: Melt margarine on stove and add all ingredients.
Pour over shrimp and marinate at least 4 hours.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with large potatoes baked in margarine and topped with Cheddar cheese.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Bake sweet potatoes until very tender, about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Remove and let cool.
Reduce heat to 350°.
When potatoes are cool enough to handle, cut in half, scoop out flesh and mash until smooth.
Stir in 6 tablespoons of the brown sugar, lightly beaten eggs, orange juice, 2 tablespoons melted unsalted butter, salt and vanilla.
Spoon into casserole dish.

title: individual cherry cheesecakes
directions: Mix cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Beat well with a beater.
Put 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of cupcake papers.
Fill 2/3 full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.
Place 1 tablespoon cherry pie filling on top of cheesecake.
Refrigerate.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients in large skillet.
Cover.
Cook over medium heat for 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: icebox (refrigerator) fruit cake
directions: * I use 1 small jar marshmallow cream.

title: sugarless fruit bars
directions: Cook raisins, dates and water 5 minutes and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Next morning put through blender and add remaining ingredients.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° in cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.

title: crab delight
directions: Soak gelatine in 3 tablespoons cold water and combine with undiluted mushroom soup that has been heated slightly. Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and chill in ring mold. Fill center with olives and surround with crackers.

title: blender chocolate bavarian
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold milk in a 5-cup blender; let stand until gelatin granules are moistened.
Add chocolate (reserve some for garnish, if desired) and hot milk.
Cover; blend at low speed until chocolate melts and gelatin dissolves, about 5 minutes. Stop blender.
Add cream, eggs, sugar and rum; cover and blend at high speed until well mixed.
With blender still running, remove center cap of lid and add ice cubes, one at a time.
Blend until ice melts.
Pour at once into individual dessert dishes; chill until set, about 1/2 hour.
Garnish with dollop of whipped cream and a few chocolate pieces.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine soup and milk; heat.
Blend butter and flour; stir into soup mixture.
Add Worcestershire sauce; cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Stir in cheese.
Combine this with beans and pimento.
Pour into a casserole dish; sprinkle with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until crumbs are browned and corners bubble.

title: quick chicken a la king
directions: In saucepan on medium heat, combine soup and milk. Stir in peas and chicken.
Pour over muffins.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Stir in remaining ingredients (except sour cream), using juice from strawberries.
Spread half of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until firm (about an hour). Leave remaining mixture at room temperature.
When first layer is set, spread top with sour cream and then cover with remaining mixture and chill.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil whole chicken or use can chicken, with onion and celery. Drain; save broth (if used can chicken use canned broth).
Mix chicken, Veg-All, soup and 1 cup broth; pour into casserole dish. Melt butter and mix flour and milk into melted butter; pour over chicken mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Combine flour with salt, soda and cinnamon.
Mix small amount of mixture with nuts.
Beat eggs, oil, sugar and flavoring for 2 minutes.
Add apples; continue beating.
Add flour; beat 3 to 4 minutes longer.
Mix in nuts.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: oven baked fish
directions: Place fish in shallow baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour evenly over fish.
Marinate several hours (optional) in refrigerator, turning fish occasionally.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake fish for 30 minutes uncovered.
Broil for 5 minutes or until fish is crisp.

title: french strawberry tart
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix baking mix, 1/4 cup sugar and the orange peel.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Press mixture in bottom of ungreased round pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inch.
Bake until light brown, 10 to 12 minutes. Cool about 30 minutes.

title: yum-a-setta
directions: Brown hamburger with salt, pepper, brown sugar and onion.
Add tomato soup.
Cook egg noodles; drain.
Add chicken soup.

title: zucchini graham bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans, 9 x 5 x 3-inches or 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inches.

title: turkey scallop
directions: Alternate layers:
1 1/2 cups bread crumbs and turkey (season each layer).
Pour gravy over all.
Combine remaining crumbs, milk and eggs; spread over top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab mold
directions: Heat cream cheese and mushroom soup together.
Heat well. Remove from heat; stir in gelatine to soup mixture.
Let cool. Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into well-oiled mold.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter with both sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour, salt and soda; mix into creamed mixture.
Stir in oatmeal, chocolate bits and nuts.
Drop on lightly greased cookie tin.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
