title: molded salad
directions: Prepare jello with 1 1/2 cups water.
While hot, add marshmallows and cream cheese.
Chill until syrupy and add remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: no-miss microwave peanut brittle(never fails!)
directions: Spray Baker's Joy on cookie sheet.

title: mom's vegetable beef soup
directions: Cook beef with onions and celery until beef is fork-tender. Add next 6 ingredients.
About 30 minutes before soup is done, add rice and barley.
More or less of rice and barley may be used, depending on thickness desired.
(Use the quick cooking barley.)

title: holiday potatoes
directions: Peel cooled potatoes; add cheese.
(Shred potatoes.) Saute onion in oleo; add soup and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes. Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, sprinkle with crushed corn flakes and drizzle with butter.
Cover with tinfoil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: string beans and potatoes
directions: Cut up potatoes in small chunks, about 1-inch thick, and boil until cooked through.
Cut up string beans and boil or steam until cooked.
Add olive oil to the bottom of a pan (1/4 cup to 12-inch pan; use less for smaller amount).
Add garlic in large chunks to remove later.
(If you like garlic and can eat it, you can leave in or cut up smaller.)
First, slightly flavor string beans, to let flavor set in, then add potatoes for short amount of time. Don't let potatoes get mashed when stirring.
Enjoy!!

title: banana bread
directions: Grease and flour loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: orange almond salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients except oranges and almonds. Shake in jar.
Add oranges and almonds just before serving on salad.
Good on butter lettuce.

title: low-fat manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown beef and boil shells.
Add onion and garlic to beef mixture.
Saute 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain fat.
To beef mixture, add spinach, cottage cheese, eggs, salt and pepper.
Stir until mixed.
Fill shells and put on sauce and cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet sour spareribs
directions: Combine the flour, garlic, ginger, 1 teaspoon salt and shoyu into a paste.
Dab the paste onto the ribs and let soak for 15 to 20 minutes.
Brown the ribs on both sides with garlic.
Drain the excess oil.
Pour the mixture of vinegar, sugar, water and 1 teaspoon salt over the ribs and bring to a boil.
Then simmer until the meat is tender.
Serve the ribs over a bed of shredded carrots and Japanese turnip (daikon).

title: pecan pie
directions: Blend pudding and syrup; add milk and eggs.
Add pecans and put into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
If you like, put Cool Whip on top.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine very soft cheeses and pressed garlic and mix by hand. Sprinkle paprika onto aluminum foil and roll cheese ball to coat. Chill before serving.

title: cranberry relish salad
directions: Dissolve gelatins and sugar in boiling water.
Stir in lemon juice and undrained pineapple.
Chill until partially set.
Put cranberries and oranges through food processor.
Add to gelatin mixture along with pecans.
Turn into a 2 1/2-quart mold or 9-inch square pan.
Chill until set.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt butter or margarine.
Add to graham crackers.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan.

title: hawaiian low-fat sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, 1 cup sugar, egg, milk, coconut and vanilla in a bowl; mix well.
Spoon into a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pizza appetizer
directions: Brown all meat.
Add cheese and spices until melted.
Spread on cocktail rye bread.
Freeze.

title: chocolate heaven
directions: Soften margarine and mix all ingredients.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until golden.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Place butter and sugar in bowl.
In small saucepan, bring water, corn syrup and spices to boil.
Pour over butter and sugar; beat until well blended.
Gradually stir in flour mixture until well blended and smooth.
Wrap dough airtight; chill overnight.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Beat cheese until smooth. Stir in remaining ingredients. Roll or shape into a ball. Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: chocolate filled bonbons
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar, eggs, vanilla and almond extract.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and nuts.
Form dough into 1-inch balls. Press dough around a kiss until it is completely covered.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Makes 3 1/2 to 4 dozen kisses.

title: whole wheat applesauce cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar together; mix in applesauce and baking soda.
Add flour and cinnamon, blending thoroughly.
Oil and flour 8-inch baking pan or muffin tins.
Pour batter into pan or make individual cakes in muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes in an 8-inch cake pan, about 20 minutes for cupcakes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Form into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tropical fruit freeze
directions: Place fruit juices, except pineapple, in blender until smooth. Combine all and mix well.
Pour in freezing containers.
Freeze. Great as a beverage; unfreeze but leave icy.
Add ginger ale, a splash or so.

title: oven stew
directions: Mix all ingredients and cover with mushroom soup.
Pour into large casserole dish or Dutch oven.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil, then with dish or pot lid.
Place in 250° oven for 4 hours. Do not open casserole during cooking time.

title: aunt grace's gingery carrots
directions: Scrub carrots and slice into 1-inch slices.
Cook until just tender-crisp in a covered saucepan with ginger ale, molasses, garlic and butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with minced parsley, salt and pepper before serving.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: barbecued flank steak
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in large bowl; add steaks.
Marinate at room temperature for 3 to 6 hours.
Broil over hot coals until medium-rare or rare.
Slice diagonally, cutting in 1/2 to 3/4-inch strips.
Marinade will keep indefinitely in refrigerator if green onion is removed.

title: stuffing-on-pork chops
directions: Brown chops, both sides.
Place in baking dish.
Lightly mix together bread cubes, onions, oleo, 1/4 cup water and poultry seasoning.
Place mound of stuffing on each chop.
Blend soup and 1/2 cup water; pour over all. Bake at 350° for 90 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix oil, sugars, eggs, and vanilla.
Sift flour and dry ingredients together.
Add to sugar mixture.
Blend in oatmeal, nuts, coconut, and raisins.
Drop on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove immediately from pans onto rack to cool.
Freezes well.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat; skim off excess fat.
Add garlic, parsley, salt, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer uncovered 45 minutes.
Cook noodles in salted water until tender; rinse with cold water.
Let set.
Combine cottage cheese, eggs, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Line bottom of pan/dish with half of noodles.
Spread half the meat mixture.
Cover with Mozzarella slices.
Repeat layering.
Pour remainder of meat mixture over all and sprinkle with Parmesan. Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Let set 30 minutes before serving 12.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix rhubarb and 1/2 cup sugar; let stand.
Cream together shortening and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add egg; beat.
Put soda and vanilla in buttermilk.
Sift together flour, cinnamon and salt. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, starting and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in rhubarb.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream topping.

title: mustard string beans
directions: Cook beans in salt water until done; drain water, then add remaining mixture.
Boil for 15 minutes, and can.

title: sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Place in a large saucepan. Add 1 teaspoon salt and water to cover. Bring to a boil and simmer for 25 minutes.
Slice potatoes.

In a medium skillet, melt oleo over low heat. Add brown sugar, orange juice, orange peel and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly, until sugar is completely dissolved. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes until syrup is thick.
Add apple
slices to orange sauce. Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, to turn apple slices in sauce for 5 minutes or until apples are just tender. Remove apples from sauce and set aside.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Quarter each biscuit and roll in sugar mixture.
Layer biscuits and pecan pieces in a well-greased Bundt or tube pan.
In a saucepan combine brown sugar, butter, vanilla and remaining tablespoon cinnamon.
Boil for 1 minute and pour over biscuits and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Eat with fingers.
Pull apart.
You can add 1 cup raisins with pecans if desired.

title: pina colada dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Serve in hollowed cantaloupe or pineapple surrounded by strawberries and other fruit, as desired.

title: orange glaze
directions: Heat all ingredients in quart saucepan until spreadable fruit is melted.

title: lemon cake pudding
directions: Cream butter, add sugar gradually, cream until light and fluffy, add yolks, beat well.
Add flour, juice, rind and salt. Stir in milk, fold in stiffly beaten whites.
Pour into 5 x 9-inch baking dish.
Set in hot water; bake at 325° for 40 minutes then 350° until brown.

title: ant killer
directions: Clogged Shower Heads:
If your shower head is clogged, try boiling it in 1/2 cup vinegar and 1 quart water for 15 minutes.

title: dried peaches
directions: Cook over low-medium heat in a heavy large pan for several hours, stirring every few minutes.
When cooked down to pie filling, place into jars and seal.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter for 3 minutes (use margarine or butter).
Add sugar and beat 5 minutes.
Add eggs, flour and vanilla. Cream all together and add to mixture and beat until fluffy. Bake in a tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours (grease pan).

title: honey buns
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In
small
bowl, combine nuts, honey and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Pour into ungreased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan. Separate dough into 10
biscuits.
In
small bowl combine brown sugar and cinnamon; put 1
teaspoon
butter
on 1 side of each biscuit.
Stand biscuit on
edge,
rows
of biscuits in prepared pan.
Drizzle with
2 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30
minutes
or
until
golden brown.
Cool 3 minutes; turn onto serving plate.

title: apple crunch
directions: Generously rub sides and bottom of an 8 x 8-inch baking dish with 1/2 stick margarine.
Pour in pie filling.
Sprinkle spice over pie filling.
Pour cake mix on top and don't worry if there are some lumps.
Cut the whole stick of margarine over top of cake mix.
Bake for approximately 45 minutes at 350° or until desired brownness.
You can double the recipe and use a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chicken spoonbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour and salt in heavy saucepan; add broth and cook until thickened.
Stir in butter and cool.
Blend in beaten egg yolks and fold in chopped chicken.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a 6 x 10-inch greased baking dish at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix ingredients.
Grease muffin tins and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Store remainder in refrigerator for future use.
Keeps about 6 weeks.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix all together
and
simmer
minutes until cheese melts. Line 9 x 13-inch pan with medium bag of Doritos chips, crushed. Pour chicken mixture over chips.
Bake at 375° until it bubbles.

title: crab canapes(great for holidays)
directions: Mix well.
Spread on party rye bread.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake under broiler until it begins to bubble (5 to 6 minutes).

title: potato pancakes
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Do not overbeat. Fry and serve with bacon, applesauce and sour cream.

title: pepper steak(serves 6)
directions: Calories: 208 per serving without rice.

title: oven baked chicken cacciatore
directions: Place chicken breasts in large baking dish with garlic, pepper, onion and potatoes; add salad oil and stewed tomatoes. Sprinkle
with oregano and Italian seasoning.
Bake in 350° to 375° oven for about 2 hours.

title: porcupines
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients well.
Roll into 2-inch balls.
Place in oven dish or baking pan.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes, until done.
These can be cooked in beef broth or seasoned tomato sauce.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheets to 375°. boil potatoes
until easily pierced by fork.
Place potatoes in large mixing bowl. Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in butter and sugar. Beat eggs one at a time.
Mix in spices, salt, and milk into unbaked pie crusts.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet for 70 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: texas beans
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and cook in crock-pot on low all night or on high for about 4 hours.

title: buckeyes
directions: Bring butter to room temperature.
Mix butter and peanut butter together, then add powdered sugar.
Mix well and roll in 1-inch balls.
Chill mixture.

title: spicy zucchini bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Make a well in the center. Combine oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in zucchini.
Add mixture to dry ingredients.
Stir until moist. Spoon into 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove to wire rack.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift together dry ingredients; cut in shortening with pastry blender.
Add yeast mixture and buttermilk to dry ingredients.
Turn dough out onto floured surface and knead lightly.
Refrigerate dough until needed.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut into rounds with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Fold in half, as for pocketbook rolls, if desired.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yield: About 3 dozen.

title: green chili
directions: Cut pork into small pieces and fry at low temperatures with ground beef until pork is tender.
Add all spices and flour.
Stir until flour is browned.
Blend peppers and onion with a little water while flour is browning.
Add 16 ounces water to meat and flour to make a gravy.
When gravy has thickened a little, add onion and peppers.
Simmer for at least half an hour.
Serve with beans or Mexican food.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Put a drop of oil in frypan; brown pieces of chicken.
Add cans of tomato sauce, peppers, onions, wine, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook, covered, on low heat for 50 minutes.
Uncover, stir and add Parmesan cheese.
Serve over a bed of rice with Italian bread.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients.
Shape into oval loaf.
Put into baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce mixture over loaf.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, basting occasionally.

title: fat-free pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
In medium bowl, mix together Butter Buds with 1 cup water until well dissolved.
Add pumpkin.
Add this to large bowl of dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 loaf pans sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray.
Bake about 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Yield: 2 loaves.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar. Add eggs and beat. Combine flour and baking soda. Add to cream mixture alternately with sour cream. Stir in flavorings. Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool. If desired, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: hummus dip(yield: serves 12)
directions: 1. Put everything except the parsley in a food processor or blender and blend until smooth.

title: crazy cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 12-inch pan.
Put dry ingredients in large bowl, then mix.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bayley's west indies salad
directions: Spread half of onions on bottom of bowl, then add crab.
Mix water, oil and vinegar together and pour over crab.
Add rest of onions.
Salt and pepper the top (do not stir up).
Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Do not stir until ready to serve. Serve on lettuce leaf garnished with lemon wedges or tomato wedges and parsley.
Deelicious!!

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together and serve with crackers.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Remove cake from oven and while still hot, poke holes 1 to 2-inches apart with handle of wooden spoon.
Pour condensed milk across top of cake while still hot, then pour caramel sauce over cake.
Cool 1 hour in refrigerator.
Spread Cool Whip over top and sprinkle crushed Heath bars over whipped topping.

title: raspberry applesauce jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add thawed raspberries and applesauce.
Chill until firm.

title: cornbread
directions: Heat 9-inch iron skillet on top of stove with a tad of the oil to grease.
When hot, pour in batter and put in hot oven.
Bake for 20 minutes at 425°.

title: dennis' homemade lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix all other ingredients except Mozzarella cheese and noodles.
Add ground beef to sauce.
Line 13 x 9-inch pan with noodles, then a layer of sauce, repeating until you reach the top, ending with sauce.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on it and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix lard into flour.
Add baking powder and buttermilk. Mix well and turn
out on floured board.
Knead and shape into ball. Bake at 450°
for
to
minutes.
Makes about 18 small biscuits.

title: st. george's day scones
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, sugar, soda and salt.
Cut the butter in until mixture looks like coarse crumbs.
Add raisins. Gradually add buttermilk until dough clings together.
Turn out onto floured board and pat gently into a half-inch thick round. Cut into scones with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on greased baking sheet (or parchment lined), brush tops with cream and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 425° for about 10 to 12 minutes or until golden and baked through.
(This recipe can be multiplied well.)

title: carameled parsnips
directions: Cook brown sugar, butter and water until sugar dissolves.
Add parsnips and simmer on each side until tender and caramelized, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: green chilies enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet; set aside.
Take medium saucepan, and melt butter.
Dip tortillas in melted butter, one at a time, to soften.
Roll small amount of beef and a small amount of cheese into each tortilla.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Pour enchilada sauce over tortillas.
Top with leftover beef and cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: poppy seed loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients 2 minutes. Pour into 2 loaf pans, greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. After removing from pan, cover with glaze.

title: mandel bread
directions: Beat sugar and eggs; add oil.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.

title: commodity cake(over fifty)
directions: Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
I find the longer you beat the mix the better it rises.

title: fruit cake
directions: Scald milk in double boiler.
Mix in other ingredients. Bake for 1 hour in 300° oven.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in covered container.
Keep refrigerated.
Good salad dish for the holidays or any time.

title: country fried chicken
directions: Fry chicken, then make gravy.
Put in crock-pot on high for 6 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: key lime cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place dry ingredients into mixing bowl. Add eggs, oil, orange juice, vanilla and lemon extract.
Beat until well blended.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove cake from oven.
Let stand in pan 15 minutes or until almost cool.
Prick cake all over with fork. Drizzle thoroughly with lime juice mixed with powdered sugar. Cover and refrigerate.
To serve, cut into squares.
Top with whipped cream and garnish with lime slices.

title: rhubarb whip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes.
Add jello to hot rhubarb mix.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Chill until partially set and fold in Dream Whip.

title: orange frosty
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend well and serve.

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Mix together pudding and pineapple.
Fold pudding and Cool Whip and marshmallows together until well blended.

title: brown rice
directions: Brown onion in oleo.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add rice and soups.
Cover and bake 45 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill before serving.
If canned shrimp are used, be sure to drain, rinse well and pat dry before cutting up.
Fresh shrimp can be added as taste and pocketbook allow.

title: new england fruit pudding
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg together; set aside. Cream sugar and oleo.
Add egg and milk; beat well.
Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, then add apples, dates and raisins or nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in greased pan or greased bowl.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Combine the ground beef, milk, oatmeal, onion, salt and pepper.
Make meatballs and brown.
Combine the next 5 ingredients.
Pour over meatballs and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: almond paste
directions: In food processor, grind almonds very fine, enough to make 1 3/4 cups (may need to grind 1/2 at a time).
Put 1 3/4 cups almonds back in processor, add rest of ingredients.
Blend to a paste. Store in tightly sealed jar or plastic bag.
Yields 1 1/3 cups paste.

title: citrus seafood stew
directions: Thaw fish and shrimp, if frozen.
Rinse fish and shrimp.
Cut fish into 1-inch pieces.
Set aside.
In a large saucepan, combine undrained tomatoes and chicken broth.
Bring to boiling.
Add uncooked rice, chili powder and garlic.
Return to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until rice is tender, stirring occasionally.
Add fish, shrimp, orange concentrate and frozen pepper mixture.
Return to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer gently for 3 to 5 minutes or until fish flakes easily and shrimp turn pink.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange well-drained broccoli in greased 11 1/2 X 7 1/2 baking dish.
Place chicken over this.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Mix well and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Sprinkle on buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cooked cake frosting
directions: Combine water, sugar and Karo in saucepan.
Cook until it strings.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add syrup mixture while beating egg whites.
Add flavoring.
This is good for coconut cake frosting.

title: cheese and bacon specials
directions: Mix together first 8 ingredients.
Cut buns in half and brown under broiler.
Fry bacon strips until browned.
Spread mixture on half
of
buns
and place 2 strips bacon on top and slice of tomato
on top.
Place under broiler until cheese is melted. Serve warm.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Add hot water, 1/2 cup sugar, shortening and salt.
Dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add to cool mixture 2 whole eggs, well beaten.
Add unsifted flour.
Mix well.

title: growing crystals
directions: Mix salt, water and ammonia.
Pour this mixture over several small pieces of charcoal in a small glass bowl.
Add several drops of different colored inks on various parts of the charcoals.
Leave this undisturbed for several days and crystals will cover it in an interesting formation, growing and spreading every day.
It will be white where no ink was applied.

title: cherry fig bars
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a bowl; stir well.
Add eggs; stir until dry ingredients are moistened (batter will be slightly thick).
Spread into a 9-inch square baking pan coated well with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes; cut into bars about 2 inches across.
Bake about 12 to 15 minutes or until browned.
(The cookies won't be crisp unless they are browned.)
Yields 44 cookies.
Calories:
144 for 2 cookies. Food exchange:
1 bread and 1 1/2 fat.

title: cream of asparagus soup
directions: Cook asparagus in 1 cup of stock until tender.
Melt butter in deep saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour.
Add 2 1/2 cups stock, a little at a time.
Cook, stirring, until slightly thickened.
Stir in cream, pepper and cooked asparagus with liquid.
Heat through.
Serve hot with lemon wedges to squeeze over top of soup.
Serves 6.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in butter until lightly browned, about 20 minutes. Add beef broth and Worcestershire sauce.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
For better flavor add 1 envelope of chicken base.

title: moravian christmas cookies
directions: Combine 1st 4 ingredients and beat until melted.
Dissolve soda in boiling water and add to above mixture.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil the chicken until tender, with no salt.
Debone chicken and cut into small pieces.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix stuffing with melted margarine in bowl.
Put hot stuffing mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan and save other half for topping.
Heat the soups and broth in saucepan.
Pour the soup mixture over the chicken. Add the remainder of stuffing mix.
This may be dampened with some broth.
Bake at 350° for 39 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: puppy chow for humans
directions: Melt chips, oleo and peanut butter together. Pour over cereal in a bowl.
Fold until cereal is coated.
Shake in plastic bag with powdered sugar until coated.
Spread out on sheet to dry.
It works best to divide sugar in thirds and layer with cereal in bag.

title: fruit and ice cream pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Press cookie dough into greased 12-inch pizza pan or into 12-inch circle on greased baking sheet; bake 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool.
Spoon ice cream onto crust; freeze until firm.
Top with fruit and drizzle with topping.

title: cleo's chili beans
directions: In deep frypan, place oil, meat and salt.
Add 1/2 cup water. Cook until meat turns white.
Add celery, bell pepper and onions. Cook slowly for about 1 hour.
Add 1 can tomato sauce.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Soak beans about 1 hour in warm water.
Cook, adding 1/2 teaspoon or more of salt and 2 slices bacon.
Cook slowly until beans are done.
Add 1 can tomato sauce and simmer about 10 minutes.
Add meat mixture at same time.
Top with grated cheese, if desired.

title: cheese-bacon potatoes
directions: Layer into a well-greased casserole the potatoes, onions, bacon and cheese. Repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: carolyn's strawberry pie
directions: Boil sugar, water, cornstarch and jello until thick.
Cool. Bake pie shell and cool.
Place fresh strawberries in cooled crust.
Pour thickened mixture over strawberries.

title: rolls
directions: Mix Crisco, plus sugar.
To this, add 1 cup boiling water and mix well.
Add 1 more cup of boiling water to finish dissolving Crisco.
Put thermometer in and when temperature drops between 105 to 110°, add yeast.
Stir well and add beaten eggs.
Dump the mixture into the flour and mix until blended only.
Cover and let rise twice or refrigerate overnight.
Punch down and knead.
Roll out into rolls.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: hardees biscuits
directions: Melt butter in pan and cool.
Mix all ingredients and roll out on floured surface.
Place biscuits in pan, then turn so both surfaces are buttered.
Bake in a 500° oven until golden brown. (Can cut recipe in half.)

title: banana salad
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients to make the dressing.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, so it will not stick or cook in the microwave in a 4-cup measure on medium-high (7) until thickened.
Cool.
Can be prepared a day or two ahead.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar and mix thoroughly. Add milk, vanilla, nutmeg and flour. Blend well. Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until custard has set. Serves 12.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix by hand all the ingredients.
Shape into small balls. Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes. While cookies are hot, roll in confectioners sugar, cool completely.
Roll in sugar again.

title: nanny's forgotten cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Put in oven preheated to 350°.
Turn oven off and leave overnight in oven or until oven cools.

title: paella
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
Fry chicken in oil over moderate heat until lightly browned.
Put chicken in a large casserole at least 14 inches in diameter and 2 1/2 inches deep or roasting pan.
Add onion, garlic and green pepper; cook until tender.
Add tomatoes, bouillon cubes and bay leaf.
Cook and stir for about 5 minutes.
About 1/2 to 1 hour before serving the Paella, heat oven to 350°.
Take chicken out of casserole.
To the mixture left in pan, add rice, salt to taste, oregano and saffron (rub between palms before putting in).
Pour in boiling water and stir.
Taste and add more seasoning if desired.
Arrange chicken, sausage, shrimp and clams on top of rice.
Scatter peas over all.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 45 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Do not stir Paella after it is put in the oven.
You may cover it with foil to keep it warm for 1/2 hour.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Combine flour, nuts and melted oleo.
Pat into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: sopa de ajo(garlic soup)
directions: Heat the oil in a soup pot.
Add chopped garlic and bread crumbs.
Fry until lightly golden; stir in paprika.
Immediately add boiling water and salt.
Cover and simmer slowly for 20 minutes.
The bread should almost dissolve.
Place soup in 4 individual bowls and add one egg per bowl.
Poach the eggs in the soup by placing bowls in hot oven for a few minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: jalapeno steaks
directions: Heat olive oil and 2 tablespoons of butter in heavy skillet. Brown steaks on both sides.
Reduce heat and cook gently until they are medium rare or cooked to desired doneness.
Remove from the pan and keep warm.
Pour off the fat.
Add remaining butter to the remaining juices.
Add the onion and chopped jalapenos and simmer, stirring constantly, until softened.
Add the red wine; bring to a boil and deglaze pan, being sure to scrape up any bits that may have stuck to pan.
Add the ground pepper (black), stock and cream and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until sauce is smooth and thick.
Place the steaks on a plate; pour the sauce over the top and garnish with jalapeno slices and cilantro and serve.

title: oreo milkshake
directions: Place all ingredients into the blender and blend well.
Pour into glasses and enjoy!

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef in narrow strips.
Toss in mixture of 6 tablespoons flour, salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Brown in small amount of bacon drippings.
Add water, 1/4 teaspoon pepper, mushrooms and onion.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Add paste of 2 tablespoons flour and 2 tablespoons water.
Add slowly to meat.
Simmer until thick.
Add sour cream.
Do not boil.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: sugar-free pineapple-orange sherbet
directions: Stir together Eagle Brand and pineapple.
Pour into ice cream freezer, then add Orange Crush.
Start freezer.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes approximately 30 minutes in boiling water. Drain and add remaining ingredients, except paprika.
Beat until combined.
Spoon mixture into lightly buttered, 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: shortcake parisienne
directions: Berries may be flavored with 1 teaspoon Kirsch brandy.

title: debbie's pork tenderloins
directions: Brown tenderloin in oil; insert garlic in tenderloin with small pricks.
Rub remaining garlic on body of meat, then set aside.
Saute the following:
onion, mushrooms and garlic in butter.
Add wine.
Add cream until smooth.
Add mixture to pork in casserole dish.
Cover dish tightly with aluminum foil and bake (30 to 40 minutes per pound) at 350°.
Slice thinly to serve.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cream of cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflowerets in boiling water and salt until tender, 5 to 8 minutes.
Drain water from cauliflower into bowl.
Add bouillon cubes and mix well.
Reserve cooked cauliflower.
Melt margarine in 2-quart saucepan.
Blend in flour.
Remove from heat and stir in cauliflower water, cream or milk and cheese.
Add nutmeg and pepper.
Stir and cook over medium heat for 4 to 5 minutes or until mixture begins to thicken.
Add cooked cauliflowerets and heat 1 minute.
Serve hot, garnished with chopped fresh parsley.
Yield:
6 servings.
Can use broccoli and potatoes using dill for seasoning.

title: lemon-broccoli chicken
directions: Cut 4 thin slices of lemon; set aside.
Squeeze 2 teaspoons juice from remaining lemon; set aside.
In 10-inch skillet, over medium heat, in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until brown on both sides.
Spoon off fat.
Meanwhile, in small bowl, combine soup and milk; stir in reserved lemon juice and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Top each piece with lemon slice.
Reduce heat to low. Cover; simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is tender and juice runs clear, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: pineapple cake
directions: Sift sugar, flour, soda and salt together. Add two unbeaten eggs and crushed pineapple. Mix and pour into floured pan and sprinkle with 3/4 cup brown sugar on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon raspberry jumbo muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, combine eggs, cream, oil and extract. Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fold in raspberries.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 22 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes then remove to cooling rack.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients together well and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake in 425°
oven for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 50 to 60 minutes longer.
Cover edges of crust with foil after 30 minutes of baking to prevent excessive browning.

title: 7 layer cookie bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs. Pour condensed milk over this and then sprinkle with chocolate chips, peanut butter chips, nuts and coconut. Pat down. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Let cool and cut into bars.

title: scrabble
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours, stirring every 15 to 30 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 pounds.

title: pumpkin raisin bread
directions: Cook raisins in 1 cup of water.
Save 2/3 cup of water from raisins.
Sift together the dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well with hands.
Pour into 2 large or 3 small pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cranberry tuna salad
directions: Mix together tuna, eggs, celery, olives, onion, cashews, salt, pepper and enough salad dressing to moisten.
(Do not make mixture too wet.)
Pack firmly into fish mold.

title: baked ziti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook ziti in a large pot of boiling salted water until tender but firm, about 10 to 12 minutes. Drain and rinse under cold running water.
In a medium bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, eggs, 1/2 cup of Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and parsley.
Mix to blend well.
Toss cooked ziti with 2 cups marinara sauce.
Place 1/2 of the pasta in an 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Top with Ricotta mixture and 1/2 of the Mozzarella cubes.
Top with remaining ziti, marinara sauce, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake until ziti is heated through and cheese bubbles, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: killer dip
directions: Chop onions and Velveeta cheese and place in pan.
Add chili and heat on medium until cheese is completely melted.
Serve with nacho chips.
Great on hot dogs.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Add chocolate to water.
Place over low flame.
Bring to boil and cook 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add sugar and salt. Boil 4 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Serve hot or cold over ice cream, etc.
Makes 1 cup.

title: shrimp & everything(4 star)
directions: Place shrimp, onions, & peppers in sauce pan and saute until shrimp are pink. Add rest of ingredients (except rice) and bring to a boil. Stir in rice. Cover and remove from heat. Let stand 5-6 minutes. Fluff. Add parsley, if desired, and serve.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix crust and cook in oblong or square pan at 350 for 20 minutes.
Cook completely.

title: dump fruit salad
directions: Dump all ingredients together; mix.
Chill and serve.

title: sparkling red velvet punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot cranberry juice.
Add remaining 2 cups of cranberry juice and lemon juice.
Cool slightly.
Add 7-Up and ice.
Makes 28 (4-ounce) servings.

title: taco pie
directions: In a skillet, brown meat. Add taco seasoning packet. Drain and return to skillet. Sprinkle with broken chips. Spread beans over the chips.
Spoon salsa over beans. Top with cheese. Return to low heat and cover until cheese is melted.

title: mocked lemon meringue cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on package and bake.
Cook lemon pie filling and cool completely.
Set aside.
After cake has completely cooled, spread lemon pie filling between layers. Reserve about 1/3 of filling for topping on cake.
Cover entire sides and about an inch on top with Cool Whip.
Pour lemon pie filling around the top of cake.
Fill center of top with Cool Whip. Garnish with thin lemon slices twisted.
Lemonicious!

title: turkish stew
directions: You will need a large boiler or Dutch oven.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Combine peas, onions, and dressing.
Mix well.
Marinate overnight.
Add salsa or picante sauce and mix.
Use large corn chips for "scooping" dip.
A big hit with men!!

title: fried rabbit
directions: Shake rabbit in bag with mixture of flour, paprika, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Heat oil in large skillet over moderate temperature.
Cook the large meaty pieces about 10 minutes before adding the smaller pieces. Turn pieces often for even cooking. Cook until tender and brown, 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: walnut crunch brownies
directions: Prepare One Bowl Brownies as directed using 4 eggs and omitting walnuts in batter.
Spread into pan.

title: poor mom's cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine oats, sugars, flour and salt. Combine soda and water.
Stir into oat mixture along with shortening and vanilla. Roll in walnut size balls and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: cracker pie
directions: Whip egg whites until foam appears.
Add cream of tartar. Beat until stiff.
Add sugar and fold in crackers, nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: red rice
directions: Fry bacon strips until both sides are brown.
Drain excess grease onto a paper towel.
Slice sausage in 1/2-inch thick pieces; cook until well heated.
Add remaining ingredients (except water) in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add water; stir.
Bring to a boil; stir occasionally.
After about 6 to 8 minutes, turn down heat and let simmer until rice is done.
Serve hot with a side of steamed vegetables.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Spoon 1 cup spaghetti sauce in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook spinach and drain.
Mix spinach, Ricotta and Mozzarella cheese, eggs, Parmesan cheese and cooked Italian sausage.
Fill cooked shells (a cake decorator bag works well to fill shells).
Put shells in baking dish and top with remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: caramels
directions: Melt butter in a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Add brown sugar and salt.
Stir in corn syrup, mixing well.
Gradually add the milk, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir over medium heat until candy reaches 245°.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla; stir.
Pour into a well-buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cool, cut and wrap.
Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: bloody mary
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Serve in a glass with ice cubes. Makes 1 drink.

title: thirteen bean soup
directions: Cover beans with water and soak overnight; drain.
Add water and ham.
Boil; simmer for 3 hours.
Add rest of ingredients. Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 30 to 60 minutes.
Dish and serve.
This soup also freezes nicely.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Prepare ice ring by filling mold with water to within 1 inch of top rim.
Freeze.
Arrange pineapple chunks, orange slices and maraschino cherries on top of ice.
Carefully fill with water and freeze.

title: ham and beans(try this recipe with cornbread.)
directions: In my cafeteria, Hilda's Cupboard, I served this recipe once a week.
Many said once was not enough.

title: hot slaw
directions: Combine sugar, mustard, salt, flour and eggs; mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cabbage.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, until thickened.
Keep warm in pan and pour over cabbage.
Yields 1 pint of slaw.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef and cook onions and peppers until tender. Stir in soup and seasoning.
Put in casserole dish, placing large spoonfuls of potatoes on top and around edge of dish.

title: cornish hens and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread rice in 3-quart shallow baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes or until golden brown, stirring occasionally.
Combine salad dressing mix with 2 1/2 cups boiling water and soup.
Stir into rice.
Cut hens in half; season with salt and pepper.
Place cut side down on rice.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake for 30 minutes or until hens are tender.
Yields 2 to 4 servings.

title: grandmother's pecan pie
directions: Combine first ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecans. Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: bar-b-que beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet. Drain and place in casserole dish. Mix in BBQ sauce and pork and beans. Cut biscuits in half and place around sides of dish. Top with grated cheese. Bake 350 until biscuits are brown.

title: raisin drop cookies
directions: Bring raisins and water to a boil about 3 minutes.
Cool while you mix all the rest of the ingredients.
Stir in the raisins. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Core cabbage.
Separate leaves and parboil in salted water until limp.
Set aside.
Mix beef and pork, rice, onions, bell pepper, salt, pepper and garlic together well.
Place about a tablespoon of beef and pork mixture on cabbage leaf that has been cut in half lengthwise.
Roll, using toothpicks to hold together.

title: full of baloney
directions: Heat oven at 350`; mix all ingredients except cheese in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes; remove cover and top with cheese.
Cook until bubbly and brown.

title: oven mushrooms
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place large square of aluminum foil in baking dish.
Put the whole fresh mushrooms in dish.
Add the bouillon cubes and butter or margarine.
Fold foil up and together, making a complete seal.
Bake for about 30 minutes. Stir and serve.

title: burger bundles
directions: Mix beef well with the milk. Shape into 10 patties. On waxed paper, flatten each patty to over 6-inches. Put equal amounts of stuffing mix in center of each patty. Draw edges over stuffing and seal. Place in 3-quart casserole. Combine soup, sauce and catsup. Heat until smooth and bubbly. Pour over the meat. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hickory smoked cheese sauce
directions: Blend smooth all but lemon juice.
Add juice.
Lightly boil in a saucepan, stirring, 5 to 10 minutes.

title: blackberry sauce
directions: Combine berries, 1 cup water and sugar in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Combine 2 tablespoons water and cornstarch; mix well.
Stir into berry mixture.
Cook 1 minute over medium heat; add lemon juice.
Let cool.
Serve over angel food or sponge cake or over ice cream.
You can substitute any kind of berries for this sauce.

title: baked oysters
directions: Mix flour with approximately 2 cups of milk until moistened. Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Crush crackers and make layers of crackers, oysters and onion.
Sprinkle nutmeg, salt and pepper on top and dot with butter.
Pour milk mixture over all and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: alabama pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, water and margarine in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; let cool.
Beat eggs in a large bowl; gradually add syrup mixture, then salt and vanilla extract.
Add nuts.
Pour into pastry shell.
With a knife, flip over the pecan halves that are not facing up.
(My mother always did this.)
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add enough milk to make a paste and then remainder of milk and add margarine in saucepan.
Heat on medium-low and stir until thick.
Add vanilla.
Add more milk if needed.
(An old recipe and really delicious.)

title: ring ditty
directions: Saute onions; cut up cheese into cubes and mix with soup and onions.
Heat.
Serve over toast.

title: crepes-basic recipe
directions: In bowl, combine flour, milk, eggs, oil and salt.
Beat until blended.
Heat a lightly greased 6-inch skillet.
Remove from heat.
Spoon 2 tablespoons of batter into skillet.
Lift and tilt skillet to spread evenly.
Return skillet to heat; brown crepes on one side only.
Separate crepes with waxed paper.
Makes 16 to 18 crepes.
Freeze any remaining unfilled crepes.
Serve with fresh fruit or fruit compote rolled inside.
Top with whipped cream.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Add dry ingredients to melted oleo; combine egg yolks and milk and shake well.
Add to rest of ingredients and cook over low heat; stir often, until custard thickens.
Pour into baked pie shell. Beat egg whites until thick and fluffy.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar and beat.
Cover pie and bake at 350° until brown.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease angel food or Bundt pan with oil and flour.
Mix cake mix with pudding, 4 eggs and 7-Up.
Mix on high speed for about 5 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: jam bars(here is a basic crust that can be topped with any flavor of jam.)
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg. Stir in flours.
Press into a lightly greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Spread jam over crust, evenly.
Sprinkle nuts over jam.
Bake at 350° for 22 minutes, until firm.
Cool before cutting.

title: spinach gratin(gratin d'epinards)
directions: Oil dish with 1 tablespoon of oil.
Add spinach and salt. Coat with bread crumbs and rest of oil.
Preheat oven to 375°. Cook 50 minutes.

title: bread and cornflake pudding
directions: Beat eggs well.
Mix together with milk, sugar and vanilla and pour over bread and cornflake layers.
Bake at 350° until knife comes out dry.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar for 1 minute.
Add eggs and banana; beat well.
Add dry ingredients, milk and vanilla.
Mix well and stir in nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool before cutting.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Chop onions and tops.
Set aside.
Bake potatoes 1 1/2 hours. When cool, scoop potato out of skin.

title: "devilicious" cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except sunflower seeds.
Refrigerate until firm enough to handle.
Form into ball and roll in seeds. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into greased or buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: butterscotch buns
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Spread on bun halves and broil until bubbly.

title: bonnie's ripe tomato relish
directions: Chop vegetables.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cook until thick.
Seal in jars and process in water bath.

title: seared shrimp with spicy mango salsa
directions: In large skillet, heat oil until very hot.
Add shrimp; cook 2 minutes.
Add onions and cook until shrimp are done.
Add peppers, pear and pineapple juice and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add red onion, tomato, mangos and mint.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Squeeze lemon over and serve.
Garnish with mint.
Serves 4.

title: dove breasts and rice casserole
directions: Roll doves in seasoned flour. Brown in oil in heavy skillet. Add celery, onion and bell pepper. Saute until limp. Add rice, tomatoes and stock. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Pour into buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Check rice for doneness and bake longer, if necessary.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until creamy. Add sifted flour and salt alternately with milk, beating after each addition. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each.
Add flavoring and pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Put into cold oven and turn to 300°.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not open oven until cake is done.

title: quick halloween cake
directions: Mix and spread in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: half pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter well.
Add one egg at a time; beat well after each.
Reduce speed of mixer and add flour small amounts at a time, beating well, then add vanilla and salt, beating well. Cook in floured and greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: devil crabs
directions: Clean crab meat well and put in a pan.
Bring to a boil with 1 cup of milk.
Set aside.
Then add salt and pepper, dried red peppers and Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Mix all together.
If too mushy, add cracker meal.

title: strawberry-bavarian cream cake
directions: You will need 2 (8-inch) cake pans and a 22-inch decorator tip pastry bag.

title: bacon cheese fries
directions: Cook French fries as directed.	Sprinkle with cheese and bacon bits.
Put under broiler for 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with Ranch dressing.

title: peggy's truly different dessert
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate.
Add pecans.
Blend; don't beat the flour, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Pour chocolate mixture into flour mixture.
Do not beat; pour into paper muffin cups (do not put cups in muffin tins).
Put on cookie sheet with sides.
Fill half full.
Cook 35 minutes at 325°.
Do not overcook.

title: havasu peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring all ingredients, except peanut butter, to a boil until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add the peanut butter; use wooden spoon.
Place pan in cold water and beat 1 minute.

title: chill-out salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Add dressing and toss gently.

title: black-eyed pea supper dish
directions: Cook sausage in large skillet.
Crumble with fork as it cooks. Drain.
Add green pepper, onion and garlic; cook 5 minutes.
Stir vegetables into sausage.
Add tomatoes, seasonings and peas with liquid in can.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes.
Serve hot with grated cheese on top.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat cream cheese good.
Fold Marshmallow Creme.
Use as dip for all kinds of fruit and pears, apple, etc.

title: apple pie
directions: Pare apples; slice into bowl.
Mix spices and sugar.
Combine with sliced apples.
Add lemon juice if apples are not tart enough.
Arrange in unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Put on top crust; seal around edge and either prick with fork or cut design with sharp knife in top crust, to allow steam to escape.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake pie for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer, or until crust is brown.

title: chocolate walnut strudel
directions: Thaw pastry sheet at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Mix egg and water in small bowl.
Microwave chocolate, milk, and butter in large bowl on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through heating time.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat together margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add flour to margarine mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 or 9 minutes for chewy cookies or 10 to 11 minutes for crisp cookies.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325° and grease 13 x 9 inch pan. Reserve 3/4 cup of dry cake mix. Combine remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into pan and bake for 20 minutes.

title: potato soup(serves 4)
directions: Put potatoes and onions in heavy pot; cover with cold water. Add salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer until potatoes flake and water is cooked down.
Remove from heat, add butter.
Mash potato mixture until slightly lumpy.
Add milk, stirring well.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients together.
Drop on a greased cookie sheet by spoonfuls and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix and store in covered container.
Add 3 to 4 teaspoons mixture to 1 cup hot water.

title: ruth lyons' ochsenschwanzsuppe(oxtail soup)
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, brown onion, celery and oxtails in butter or bacon drippings.
Remove oxtails; add flour and stir until lightly browned.
Return oxtails to saucepan and add consomme.
Add water to cover.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for three hours, or until oxtails are tender.
Remove oxtails and bay leaf.
Remove meat from bones and dice, discarding bones and fat.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Skim fat from top and heat to simmering.
Serves 6.

title: allison's squash casserole
directions: In a large skillet, steam squash and onions in butter and water, cover with a lid.
When squash is done, remove skillet from heat. Crumble crackers over squash, then sprinkle cheese on top. Cover for five minutes to let steam melt cheese.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese and chips.
Place in greased casserole.
Top with cheese, then with a layer of chips. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pickle squash
directions: Salt down the squash 1 hour, then drain.
Add all ingredients together.
Bring to a hard boil and can.
To be eaten with vegetables.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix Hawaiian Punch, pineapple juice and sugar.
Pour in a plastic container and freeze.
After frozen, pour in a punch bowl. Pour ginger ale over punch to make a slush and serve.

title: cool whip cake
directions: If strawberries are frozen, thaw.
Mix your pudding according to instructions on back of package.
Slice pound cake in bottom of dish; put a layer of cake, then pour 1/2 of your pudding on top of cake, then add crushed pineapple.
Now add sides of dish with cake and another layer over pineapple, then rest of pudding mix, then add strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: pineapple bake(great as a side dish with ham)
directions: Melt butter and add bread until coated; set aside.
Mix other 4 ingredients together until smooth.
Blend in pineapple, bread and butter.
Place in medium Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve warm.
Feeds 6.
Should be doubled for a larger group.

title: big red ice cream
directions: Put milk and strawberries in 1/2 gallon freezer.
Fill with soda.
Freeze according to freezer instructions.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Melt chocolate.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder and set aside.
Mix
oil,
melted
chocolate and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a
time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Drop by teaspoon into bowl of powdered
sugar.
Roll into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: date pudding
directions: Boil brown sugar, hot water and stick of butter for 5 minutes. Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 3 tablespoons butter and sugar. Add milk, flour and baking powder and mix well.
Add nuts and dates, pour batter over the mixture in pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut bacon into 1 to 2-inch squares.
Fry and drain on several layers of paper towels.
In a large cast-iron skillet or casserole dish, empty the cans of pork and beans, barbecue sauce, brown sugar, onion and green pepper.
Mix well along with the bacon bits.
Place in a 350° oven.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.
Even better if left in oven after this time with oven off for an additional 15 to 30 minutes.

title: rolled chicken breasts
directions: Debone chicken, saving bones and skins for broth.
Mix cheese and seasonings.
Dip chicken breasts in melted butter.
Roll in cheese mixture, then roll in cornflake crumbs.
Fold into a light roll and fasten with a toothpick.

title: friendship cake(30 days)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large glass bowl or 1-gallon jar. Stir all together with a WOODEN spoon, not metal, every day.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Mix all together.
Bring to a full boil for 5 minutes on medium heat.
After 5 minutes, take off heat.
Let cool.

title: ramen egg drop soup(makes 2 servings)
directions: Bring the chicken broth and water to a boil in a large saucepan. Add the noodles. Return to a boil and simmer, uncovered, until nearly tender, 3 minutes. Beat the eggs in a small bowl and pour into the simmering soup; do not stir (the eggs will rise to the surface in a cluster). Heat 30 seconds, then stir in the watercress and simmer until wilted, 1 minute. Stir in the soy sauce and garnish with the scallion. Serve at once. Per serving: 2 cups.

title: juice drink
directions: Combine the apple and cranberry juices in a large pot.
Tie the spices in a bag and drop into the juice.
Let simmer.
Do not boil.
Serve hot or cold.
Good for a winter drink.
This may be left on heat all day.

title: rice salad
directions: Drain peas, chop onion, celery, mushrooms and pepper.
Grate carrot.
Combine all ingredients together.

title: italian beef
directions: Rub roast with garlic and season salt.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
(Can be cooked in crock-pot.)
Prick roast and pour 1/2 cup Rhine wine in holes.
Cook 1 hour and then add another 1/2 cup Rhine wine.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Slice very thin. Remove fat from juice and add water to make 2 quarts.
To this, add 2 beef bouillon cubes, chili sauce, beef broth, onion soup and oregano.
Simmer slices in juice until time to serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix and chill before serving.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix dry cake mix with the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 370° for 10 minutes or until golden.
Let the cookies set for 2 minutes on the cookie sheet, when you take them out of the oven, so they will finish baking.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Cook okra in large iron pot with 2 to 3 tablespoons vegetable oil, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
Cook until the sliminess has diminished.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water with salt, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain, combine with onions and peppers in large bowl. Stir together remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours. To serve:
Drain marinade and save.
Serve carrots in lettuce lined bowl.
If desired, return leftovers to marinade.
Marinade can be reused.

title: moist marble cake
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Add cooking oil, vinegar, 1 tablespoon vanilla and cold water.
Mix well; set aside.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Place chips and milk in microwave bowl. Microwave 2 minutes on high. Stir. Add 10x sugar and vanilla and stir.
Pour into 8x8 greased pan. Chill two hours and cut into squares. Nuts may also be added.

title: picnic coffee cake
directions: Chop chocolate.
Place in bowl with coffee.
Add boiling water.
Let stand until melted.
Stir to blend.
Beat butter with half of the brown sugar until light.
Beat in remaining brown sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add well beaten eggs, blending well.
Stir in walnuts and chocolate paste.
Add flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add to chocolate paste alternately with sour cream; stir until batter is blended.
Turn into greased and floured angel food pan.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 50 minutes or until cake tests done.
Sift powdered sugar on top before cutting.

title: double orange whip
directions: Boil ginger ale.
Dissolve gelatin.
Add orange juice.
Place bowl of gelatin in larger bowl of ice and water until slightly thickened.
Whip with rotary beater or mixer until fluffy and thick.
Will double in volume.
Spoon into dessert dishes.
Chill until set, about 30 minutes.

title: libby's green salad
directions: An oblong dish is best to use.
Serves 6.
May be doubled.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Cook chicken, onion and pepper in hot oil in a large skillet until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve chicken and vegetables over rice.

title: sausage and bean chowder
directions: Brown sausage and ground chuck together until done; drain off grease.
Chop vegetables and put all ingredients into a large pot. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to simmer for about 1 hour until all vegetables are tender.
This recipe is great with Mexican corn bread on a cold day.

title: diabetic applesauce cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups water until water is gone.
Mix all ingredients and bake in loaf or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake is done.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Combine stuffing mix and seasoning packet, boiling water, 1/2 cup orange juice, pecans and margarine.
Stir and let stand for 5 minutes.
Clean chicken breasts.
(If desired, pound with meat mallet and cut each breast in 2, lengthwise.)
Place 1/3 to 1/2 cup of stuffing on each breast.
Wrap chicken around the stuffing. Wrap with bacon.
Secure with a toothpick.
Place in a greased pan. Pour remaining orange juice over breasts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken breast
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken.
Coat chicken breasts and put in baking bag with barbecue sauce.
Cook at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: toffee bars
directions: Thoroughly cream butter, brown sugar, egg yolk and vanilla. Add flour; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pat into ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
While warm, cut into bars.

title: nacho dip
directions: Fry and drain hamburger.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook until Velveeta is melted.
Serve warm with Tostitos.

title: fat free oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Spray cookie sheet with cooking spray.
In large bowl combine dry ingredients.
Stir in egg whites, corn syrup and vanilla until well mixed.
Add raisins (batter should be very stiff).
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until firm.
(Do not overbake.)
Makes 2 1/2 dozen. Each cookie has 0 fat, 0 cholesterol, 60 calories, 1 gram protein, 13 grams carbohydrates and 6.5 mg sodium.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil and brown sugar and beat well.
Add vanilla, zucchini and chocolate.
Beat.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to first mixture.
Add nuts and beat well.
Bake in standard loaf pan at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan until bread will remove easily, then cool on rack.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Combine in saucepan, sugar and corn syrup and bring to boil. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Stir in corn flakes and peanuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Let cool and enjoy.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients; top with cheese.
Use greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle on crushed chips the last 10 minutes.

title: orange icing
directions: Mix all together and beat.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add cocoa.
Alternately add milk and flour; beat well after each addition.
Add salt, baking powder and vanilla.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan at 250° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: chili beans
directions: Season your meat the way you like.
Brown meat, chilies and onion together.
Drain excess fat (optional).
Combine meat, tomatoes and beans and simmer about an hour.
If it is too dry, you may add a little water.
If you do, let it simmer a little longer to keep flavor.

title: veggie salad
directions: Cut up vegetables into bite-sized chunks.
Mix together in large bowl; add green olives and pour on entire bottle of salad dressing.
Marinate in refrigerator 1 hour or more before serving.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix well and pour into greased 9x12 or two 8 inch square pans. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Freezes well.

title: puffs
directions: Boil water, butter and salt. Reduce heat and add flour. Mix well with spoon until it forms a ball. Remove from heat. Add eggs, one at a time. Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then lower heat to 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: favorite brown meat stew
directions: Roll beef in blended salt, pepper, paprika and flour to coat each piece.
Then brown the meat in the Crisco in a heavy kettle. This browning gives rich, brown gravy and extra flavor to the meat, so it pays to take time to do a thorough job here.
Add water and seasonings.
Cover tightly and simmer about 2 hours.
(Do not boil. "Let the water smile, but never laugh.")
Add the prepared vegetables.
Cover and cook another 30 minutes or until the vegetables are tender when pierced with a fork.

title: hidden valley ranch dip
directions: Mix together.
Make a day ahead.
Good as dip for raw vegetables.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Beat cream cheese with flavorings, sugar and brown sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Chill until serving time. Serve with apple slices.
May sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Combine all ingredients and macaroni together.
Sprinkle with crushed crackers; top with butter.
Cook at 350° about 30 or 35 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine crumbs, cheese, oregano, garlic salt and pepper.
Roll chicken pieces in crumb mixture to coat well.
Arrange in a shallow dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°; turn and bake 20 minutes more.
Mix soup and milk together.
Pour over chicken and bake 20 minutes more, topped with more crumbs or cheese, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: gumbo
directions: *Salt, pepper, gumbo file, small can tomato paste, flour, onion and celery.

title: evergreen tree soak (fireproofing)
directions: Pound end of tree trunk, about 2 inches up, and then immerse the trunk into liquid to fireproof your tree.

title: john's buttermilk pancakes
directions: Fry on a teflon frying pan on both sides until golden brown on very little oil.

title: elegant and easy beef burgundy
directions: Put meat in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover with foil and bake for 3 hours at 325°. Do not peak.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to cranberries.
Then add to creamed mixture alternately with the milk.
Mix until blended.
Fill greased muffin tins 3/4 full. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: easy friendship cake
directions: Yield: 16 servings.
Pan Size: 10-inch Bundt.

title: cheese and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain very well in colander.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Add broccoli (while still warm) to Velveeta cheese.
Mix well until cheese melts slightly.
Crush crackers and sprinkle over top. Pour on melted butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until edges bubble and top is golden.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix and press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Let cool completely.

title: clam chowder
directions: Combine potatoes, onions and water.
Salt and pepper to taste and cook until tender.
Add half and half, minced clams, clam chowder, milk, cajun seasoning and garlic powder.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix together in a large kettle the sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and cornstarch.
Stir constantly and boil for 1 minute.
Have the yolks slightly beaten in a medium bowl.
Mix in some of the boiled pudding into egg yolks; stir constantly, then put it back in kettle and boil for 1 minute.
Mix in the butter and vanilla. Pour into a 9-inch baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and bake.

title: our favorite apple cake
directions: In large bowl, mix apples, sugar and nuts together.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla, then add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: non cook date candy
directions: Melt marshmallows and water in saucepan.
Stir in powdered sugar and milk.
Then add dates, nuts and vanilla.
Turn into buttered pan or drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let stand 3 hours.

title: cream cheese crunchers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine over hot (not boiling) water, butterscotch morsels and butter; stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Transfer to large bowl; stir in graham cracker crumbs and walnuts with a fork until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Reserve 2 cups crumb mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture into ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
In large bowl, combine cream cheese and sugar; beat until creamy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in flour and lemon juice. Pour evenly over hot baked crust.
Sprinkle reserved crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely on wire rack; cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.
Chill before serving.

title: "mushrooms a la"
directions: This is served as a vegetable course or in a chafing dish to be eaten with toothpicks at a buffet. The bread crumb mixture is made up in advance and stored in the freezer, adding the olive oil when the mushrooms are ready to be stuffed. Wash and remove stems. Place caps, cup side up, in baking dish. Place stems around caps. Mix crumbs, cheese, parsley and garlic together with 1 tablespoon olive oil. Mixture will be dry and crumbly. Sprinkle mixture over caps and add a few drops of olive oil to each cap. Place about 1/8-inch water in bottom of pan and bake in moderate oven about 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Pat rolls out in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook sausage or bacon; drain.
Beat eggs and pour over crescent rolls.
Sprinkle 1 cup cheese on top, then bacon or sausage.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Topping can vary.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate 24 hours for best flavor.

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Mix all ingredients together. Put in greased casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: beef and onion cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Dice green onions approximately halfway up stalks.
Dice dried beef into very small pieces.
Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into ball, loaf, wedge or whatever desired.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: summer key lime cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and lime gelatin in a mixer bowl.
Add eggs, oil, orange juice, vanilla and lemon extract.
Beat until well blended.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil about 1/2 chicken, salted to taste.
Have boiling hot with lots of broth.
To make dumplings mix one egg and 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Make a hole in a bowl of all purpose flour and work into real stiff dough.
Roll out extra thin and cut into pieces to drop one at a time in boiling broth.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix until creamy.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken tender and debone; cut up.
Mix eggs, mayonnaise, chicken broth and soup.
Set aside.
Layer (in large baking dish) stove top mix; next layer chicken.
Layer carrots lengthwise; next layer broccoli.
Pour eggs and mayonnaise mixture over casserole. Add grated cheese and bread crumbs on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: crinkles-molasses cookies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Shape into balls.
Dip one side in granulated sugar.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Flatten each with a glass which has been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 12 minutes.
They cook quickly, so keep watch on them.

title: creamy frosting
directions: Mix flour and milk and cook until thick; chill.
Beat margarine and Crisco 4 minutes at high speed.
Add sugar and beat 4 minutes.
Add flour-milk mixture and beat 4 minutes.
Blend in vanilla.

title: fresh orange cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add grated orange rind, margarine and juice with milk, enough to equal 1 cup.
Beat with mixer at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and beat 2 minutes more.
Pour into layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banapple cake
directions: Heat applesauce and raisins.
Let cool while mixing cake. Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and soda.
Add banana and milk to applesauce; add to mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Dust nuts with 1/2 cup of the flour.
Stir in last.
Bake in 3 loaf pans at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.
Cake is done when springs back when pressed lightly with fingertip.

title: calzone
directions: Roll out dough to fit lengthwise on cookie sheet.
Place on cookie sheet and set aside.
Heat margarine in skillet.
Saute red pepper until tender, then add mushrooms until golden.
Remove with slotted spoon onto paper towels; drain well.
Set aside.
Layer hot ham, salami and Mortadella on dough.
Next spoon pepper/mushroom mixture on top.
Spoon black olives next, then layer with Provolone cheese.
Fold dough over one, more than halfway and again on the other side.
Pinch ends.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: five hour stew
directions: Cut onion, celery, carrots and small potatoes into large chunks.
Layer in order in roasting pan.
Mix the soups together and pour over mixture. Sprinkle 1 package onion soup mix over top. Cover and bake 5 hours at 225°.
Do not peek!

title: blushing fruit punch
directions: Blend in Osterizer on blend for 1 minute.
Keep cold.
Add 2 quarts of ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: chocolate ice cream syrup
directions: In a heavy saucepan over low heat or double boiler over simmering water, melt the chocolate.
Add butter.
Cook and stir until melted.
Add sugar alternately with milk, stirring constantly.
Cook for 15 minutes, stirring often.
Serve warm over ice cream.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Yield:
2 1/2 cups.

title: creamy taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion with it, then add chili, then Velveeta (chopped melts faster).
Add whipping cream last.
Makes an electric skillet full.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Line baking dish with nuts, then coconut.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour cake mix over nuts and coconut.
Melt sugar, cream cheese and butter.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook beef and onion slowly until meat turns white. Drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 2-quart casserole.

title: buttery bubble bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, shortening, egg, salt and 1 cup flour.
Beat until smooth. Stir in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Turn onto a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic (about 6 to 8 minutes).
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled (about 1 hour).

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Roll into walnut size balls.
Place close on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° until lightly browned.
Roll into powdered sugar while hot.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: draxie's pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt; cut in shortening until mixture resembles corn meal.
Combine egg, vinegar and water.
Add to flour mixture. Stir lightly with fork until dough follows fork in bowl.
Form into ball and chill.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pie shells.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix cornflake crumbs with milk and egg.
Season with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix ground beef into mixture. Shape into 2 loaves.
Place loaves in pan.
Cover loaves with tomato sauce.
Place strips of bell pepper on top.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Cream butter.
Separate eggs.
Add beaten egg yolk and vanilla to butter.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, and sugar. Add to first mixture.
Alternate with water.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
While making cake batter, melt 5 1/2 to 6 tablespoon butter and 1 1/2 cup brown sugar in a skillet.
When thick, pour into about a 9 inch pan.
Add pineapple slices, cut or whole and decorate if you like with maraschino cherries and pecan halves.
Pour batter over the fruit and bake 35 minutes at 350°. Turn upside-down on correct size plate so fruit is on top.

title: spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, stir spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, water chestnuts and green onions until well mixed.
Cover; chill 2 hours to blend flavors.
Stir well.

title: mandarin parfaits
directions: Stir milk, sour cream and almond extract in bowl.
Add pudding mix.
With electric mixer at low speed, beat until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Layer pudding and orange sections in individual parfait glasses.
Chill for about 1 hour.
Garnish with whipped topping.

title: carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 12 muffin pan cups.
In large bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
In medium bow, whisk carrots, egg, milk, oil, sugar and raisins.
Stir into dry ingredients until combined.
Spoon into prepared muffin pans. Bake for 20 minutes.
Unmold and cool on wire rack.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: bacon pinwheels
directions: Trim the crusts off all the slices of bread and cut in 1/4-inch lengthwise slices.
In small bowl, mix softened cream cheese with the garlic.
Spread cream cheese mix on each slice of bread and sprinkle with parsley, if desired.
Roll each slice lengthwise and cut in half.
Wrap each half with a strip of bacon and secure with a toothpick.
Place each pinwheel on a broiler rack and put under the broiler until the bacon is crisp.

title: wopatuli
directions: Mix in cooler.
Freeze fruit and pineapple rings.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Dissolve soda in hot water and set aside.
Sift together all other dry ingredients using part of flour to coat gumdrops, nuts and raisins.
