Cream sugar and butter and add well beaten eggs. Stir in soda and applesauce, then add gumdrops, raisins and nuts. Bake 2 hours in 325° oven.
A tube pan is best for this.

title: fiesta nacho platter
directions: Combine beans, picante sauce and cheese.
Stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
On a serving platter, layer chips.
Put the bean mixture on the chips.
Add your lettuce and tomato on top with sour cream.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Serve before main meal.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Preheat oven to 275°. Set aside.
Melt wet ingredients on low.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar.
Let cool 3 minutes.
Add dry ingredients intermittently, then add beaten eggs.
Add vanilla.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon til crisp.
Drain, crumble and set aside.
Cook onion in 4 Tbsp. bacon drippings til tender, not brown.
Blend in next 5 ingredients.
Add vinegar and water.
Cook and stir til thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in bacon and potatoes.
Sprinkle with 2 Tbsp. snipped parsley.
Can be baked at 350° for 20 minutes in a round baking dish with 8 to 10 halved hot dogs
around the edges for a casserole supper.

title: fish batter
directions: Dip floured fish in batter and let excess drop off.
Deep fry 4 minutes each side.
Drain on paper towel.

title: heavenly pineapple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Make cake according to package directions. Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Make pudding according to package directions and mix with cream cheese until smooth.
Spread cream cheese/pudding mixture over cooled cake. Spread pineapple on top, then Cool Whip and refrigerate for 2 hours or more.
Sprinkle on chopped nuts and serve.

title: microwave sliced baked potato
directions: Peel potatoes (otherwise rinse and pat dry).
Cut potatoes in thin slices but not all the way through.
Place potatoes in microwave dish.
Sprinkle on butter and seasoning.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes rearranging potatoes after 5 minutes.
Let rest 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave another 4 or 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: stuffed clams
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mixture should be loose enough to spoon into clam shells.
Fill clam shells.
Sprinkle with additional cheese and lightly with paprika.
Add small dab of butter in center of clam mixture. Broil until brown.
Mixture should stand for 1 hour before filling shells. Coat clam shells with oil or butter before filling so shell will be easier to clean.

title: old fashion egg pie
directions: Cream sugar.
Add milk and flour.
Mix well.
Stir in well beaten egg yolks, vanilla, and cinnamon.
Fold in egg whites which have been beaten until thick, but not dry.
Pour custard in to 9 inch pie crust and bake at 325 degrees until done.

title: salad bowl of fresh vegetables
directions: Rub salad bowl with 1 cut-up garlic clove.
Place lettuce pieces in bowl.
Arrange vegetables over lettuce.

title: mexican slush
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; stir well.
Cover and freeze overnight or at least until frozen.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes.
Fill each serving glass with slush mixture and then fill with ginger ale.
Garnish with cherries. Serve immediately.
Yields 24 servings.

title: pistachio salad 2
directions: Drain off 2 tablespoons of juice from fruit cocktail; mix fruit and remaining juice with the pudding mix.
Mix in Cool Whip and add pecan pieces.

title: banana jelly muffins
directions: Beat egg, oil, bananas and milk.
Stir in sugar.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to wet mixture until moistened.
Put in greased tins.
Make depression in top of each with tip of spoon and fill with jelly.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: stuffed tortilla rolls
directions: Let cream cheese and sour cream soften. Add Accent and blend well. Then add chopped ingredients. Spread on flour tortillas and roll up tightly. Refrigerate until firm, usually overnight. Slice into narrow slices and enjoy.

title: bavarian wiener supper
directions: Halve 4 franks; reserve. Slice remaining franks 1/4 inch thick. Mix soup and mayonnaise. Combine sliced franks with half of soup mixture and kraut. Spread in an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2 baking dish. Stir remaining soup mixture into potatoes; arrange around edge of dish. Combine buttered crumbs and paprika and sprinkle over potatoes. Arrange halved franks in design on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot. Enjoy!

title: blueberry green salad
directions: Toss together greens and berries.
Combine remaining ingredients (except blueberries).
Mix well.
Pour desired amount of dressing over greens and toss.
Sprinkle Blue cheese over top. Makes 4 servings.

title: date nut bread
directions: Heat sherry or water to just below boiling.
Sprinkle soda over dates in a bowl.
Pour hot sherry or water over dates and cool.
Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add cooled date mixture, beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix mixture, stirring until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans (7 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2 inches).
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: italian knot cookies
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla to eggs and mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt and add to egg mixture, one cup at a time.
Pinch off a small amount of dough and roll between hands to form thin strips and tie in a knot.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Dip immediately in vanilla icing glaze.
Makes several dozen.

title: easy beef pot pie
directions: Cook ground beef in skillet and drain well.
Add vegetables (do not drain) and beef stew seasoning.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with canned biscuits; brush with butter.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are brown.

title: sloppy tacos(serves 12)
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off grease.
Add taco seasoning and beans (optional); simmer.
Spoon over corn chips; top with cheese, lettuce and tomatoes as desired.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans and olives.
Add onion and green peppers.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over beans.
Chill.

title: sausage pie
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Slightly brown the pie shells.
Mix the eggs, flour and evaporated milk together, then add the cheese. Pour over sausage which you have divided into the 2 pie shells. Cook at 350° until golden brown.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Butter sides of heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Combine in saucepan cream and sugars.
Cook on medium heat.
Stir to boiling.
Cook to 234° soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add margarine.
Stir in nuts.
Beat until candy begins to thicken.
Just when it begins to lose its glossy look, spoon out on wax paper.
Makes about 36; store in tightly covered container.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, pineapple and nuts; blend well, then fold in egg whites.
Use vanilla wafers as base; spread with mixture (thick).
Add wafers and repeat.
Use 3 wafers for each ball.
Place in refrigerator for several hours (12) before serving.
Cover completely with whipped cream.
Sprinkle over coconut (I add a cherry on top).

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes.
When cool, peel and dice in bowl.
Cut raw bacon in small pieces, fry until crisp; set aside.
Add vinegar, bouillon and water to the pan where bacon is in.
Pour over potatoes.
Add pickles and boiled eggs and stir lightly.
Last enough mayonnaise to make it moist.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: baked parmesan cheese
directions: Combine egg and milk; stir well and set aside.
Combine Parmesan cheese, flour, paprika, salt and pepper; mix well. Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Dip in egg mixture.
Dredge in flour mixture.
Place chicken in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour butter over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender. Yield:
4 servings.

title: apricot-banana mold
directions: Drain apricots, measuring liquid (syrup).
Add water to syrup to make 3/4 cup liquid.
Heat 1 cup water to boiling in glass bowl in microwave (2 to 3 minutes).
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir in liquid.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Mix apricots and banana into thickened gelatin.
Turn into 4-cup mold or serving bowl.
Chill until firm.

title: homemade bread
directions: Place water in mixing bowl and add yeast.
Stir in 1 3/4 cups lukewarm water; add half of sifted flour, salt, sugar and shortening.
Beat with spoon until smooth, batter falls from spoon in sheets.
Using hands, mix in enough remaining flour until dough cleans bowl.
Turn onto lightly floured board.
Cover and let rest 15 minutes.
Knead until smooth (about 10 minutes).
Round up in greased bowl; bring greased side up.
Let rise in warm place 1 hour or until double in size.
Punch down and let rise 30 minutes more.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add melted butter, blending well. Add beaten eggs.
Combine soda and buttermilk, then add to mixture.
Stir in lemon extract and rind.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until brown and almost firm.

title: fruit bread
directions: Line two loaf pans with foil, leaving 1/2-inch collar.
Grease foil.
Blend cream cheese, oleo, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Gradually add flour and baking powder.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Brush chicken pieces with butter.
Roll in cracker crumbs. Arrange pieces in a flat microwave baking dish.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave at High 12 to 15 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn halfway through cooking time.
Let stand, covered, 2 to 3 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: holiday cheesecake
directions: Coat bottom of 8-inch spring-form pan with graham cracker crumbs.
Mix cream cheese, cream, eggs, sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Add candied fruit.
Pour into spring-form pan and bake in pan (13 x 9-inch), filled halfway up with water at 300° for 2 hours.
Turn oven off after 2 hours, but let cheesecake sit in oven for 1 more hour.
Cool, then refrigerate.

title: cheese strata
directions: Trim crusts off bread and arrange 6 slices on buttered 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place slices of cheese on each; add onion and chilled Smoke 'N Chip.
Cover with remaining slices of bread.

title: dump cake cobbler
directions: Dump the pie filling, pineapple and vanilla into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle on cake mix and pecans.
Cut butter or margarine in slices and spread on mixture.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: broccoli and ham casserole
directions: Place in oven proof 2 qt. casserole dish. Spread bread crumbs over mixture. Bake 1 hour at 325° or until browned and bubbly.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch in top of double boiler. Blend in milk
and
cut
up chocolate.
Cook over direct heat, stirring constantly,
until	mixture thickens and boils.
Set over boiling water

Remove.
Beat egg yolks slightly and beat into them a little of the hot mixture. Blend with mixture in double boiler.
Place again over boiling water.	Cook
5 minutes

Stir
to keep mixture smooth. Cool.
Pour into baked
pie shell.
Top with whipped cream or meringue.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream butter or oleo and sugar, adding eggs and beating well. Mix in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: pina colada cream dessert
directions: Combine milks, pineapple and lime juices. Transfer to 9 x 9-inch baking pan. Cover and freeze for 2 hours or until almost firm. Break frozen mixture into small chunks; transfer to chilled large bowl. With mixer, beat until smooth but not melted. Stir in coconut. Return to pan. Cover and freeze for 6 hours or until firm.

title: noodles alfredo
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on package.
Do not overcook!
Drain well, but do not rinse.
Meanwhile, in a medium sized skillet, saute garlic in butter.
Add parsley, salt and pepper, half and half and Parmesan cheese.
Stir over heat, but do not boil.
Pour sauce over pasta and serve.
If desired, you can sprinkle extra Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: ham and cheese appetizer log
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and mustard. Mix until well blended.
Stir in Cheddar cheese and chives.
Shape in log.
Roll in nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap and store in refrigerator.
Serve at room temperature with assorted crackers.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix ingredients together until smooth.
Fold in 9 ounce package Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Do not bake nor freeze.

title: sweet-sour cabbage slaw
directions: Alternate layers of cabbage, onion and pepper in glass bowl. Sprinkle sugar over mixture, then set aside.
Bring to boil the last 7 ingredients and pour over cabbage mixture.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.
Let stand for 4 hours before using.
Keeps a week to 10 days.

title: low-fat chili
directions: Stir in large saucepan and simmer; add Tabasco and crushed red pepper to your taste.
Serve with Italian breadsticks with low-fat Mozzarella cheese or saltine crackers.

title: tulsa turkey
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan; stir in the flour and heat until mixture foams.
Remove from heat and add milk slowly.
Put pan over low heat and stir until thickened.
Add the cheeses and seasonings.
Add turkey, celery, olives, mushrooms and cauliflower, stirring gently.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 400° for at least 30 minutes until hot and bubbling.
Also works well baked and served in individual casseroles.

title: strawberry salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine cottage cheese and dry Jell-O; mix well.
Add the marshmallows; mix.
Add drained strawberries and fold in Cool Whip.
Mix all well; chill.
Makes 10 servings.
Can be made 1 or 2 days before serving.

title: hawaiian spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs into 2-inch pieces.
Mix flour, salt and soy sauce together.
Cook ribs.
Allow to stand 10 minutes.
Heat oil in a skillet and brown ribs on all sides.
Drain excess fat and add sugar, vinegar, water, juice and ginger.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender, about 45 minutes.
Stir in pineapple and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Garnish with sesame seed.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream margarine and gradually beat in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, milk and peanuts together in saucepan.
Bring to boil and cook to soft ball stage.
Add 4 teaspoons butter, red food coloring and 1 cup powdered sugar.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on buttered wax paper.

title: pork chop dinner bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake in casserole or Dutch oven.
Brown pork chops in skillet.
Lift chops.
Set aside.
In skillet with drippings, add tomato soup, milk and liquid off of peas.
Heat and remove from burner.
Butter casserole and add all vegetables in layers, thinly sliced.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Top with can of peas, chops on top lastly.
Pour liquids reserved over all. Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: wacky chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well and make 3 holes.
Melt butter; add vanilla and vinegar.
Pour into the three holes.
Pour in 1 cup cold water over all.
Mix well with fork but do not beat. Bake in 9-inch square greased cake pan for 35 minutes in preheated oven at 350°.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Drain pineapple; set aside.
Beat eggs (saving 2 whites for meringue); add milk.
Mix flour, sugar and salt and add to egg mixture.
Add juice from pineapple.
Cook in top of double boiler (or directly over low heat, stirring constantly) until thick. Fold in pineapple and pour into cooked pie shell.
Top with meringue and bake at 350° until meringue is golden brown.

title: steak diane
directions: Cook and stir mushrooms, onion and seasonings in 1/4 cup butter until mushrooms are tender.
Stir in parsley; keep sauce warm.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Turning once, cook meat in butter over medium-high heat to medium doneness, 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Serve with mushroom sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Stew chicken in crock-pot until tender.
Remove meat from bones.
Reserve broth.
Cook sausage, ground beef and onion. Drain.
Add chicken, sausage and beef to chicken broth in crock-pot.
Dice potatoes and add to broth.
Add corn and tomato sauce to broth.
Add red pepper and salt and pepper to taste. Cook on low heat for 3 to 4 hours.
(Good for freezing.)

title: rich chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until quite smooth.
Add egg yolks, sour milk, dissolved soda, cocoa.
Stir together, add cake flour.
Fold in egg whites and vanilla.
Bake in layer pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut marshmallows in small pieces and put between layers while hot.
Cover with seven minute white frosting.

title: pecan rye snacks
directions: Brown meats and drain. Return to burner and add Velveeta cheese. Melt. Add rest of ingredients. Spoon onto rye bread. Place on cookie sheet on waxed paper. Freeze uncooked.

title: banana bread
directions: Crumb shortening and sugar; add mashed bananas and unbeaten eggs.
Mix flour and baking soda together and add to above.
Beat and bake in greased loaf pan for 50 minutes in a 350° heated oven.

title: walnut waffles
directions: Beat eggs, milk and cooking oil.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to liquid mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Add chopped walnuts.
Bake immediately on seasoned waffle iron.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Alternate milk and flour with shortening and sugar mixture.
Add eggs.
Flour 1 cup chopped black walnuts.
Pour into pan and bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 300°.

title: holiday cake
directions: Dredge raisins and pecans with 1 cup of the flour.
Cream butter and add sugar gradually, beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour, vanilla, raisins and pecans.
Mix well with hands as dough is very thick.
Put in tube pan and bake 1 hour 45 minutes at 300°. Delicious!

title: eggnog-cherry nut loaf
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix egg, eggnog and oil.
Stir into dry ingredients, mixing well.
Fold in chopped nuts and cherries.
Turn into two greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans, cool on wire rack.
Makes two loaves.

title: chicken-macaroni casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir together all ingredients, pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour. Serves 4 to 6.

title: french velvet pie
directions: Combine melted oleo, flour and nuts.
Press into a 12 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex pan.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Let cool. Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip until smooth and spread over cooled crust.
Combine both puddings and milk; blend until thick.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip (9 1/2 ounce carton).
Chill.

title: coconut pies
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add butter and eggs.
Mix well.
Add buttermilk, coconut and vanilla.
Put into 2 pie crusts and bake at 375° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: brenda's peanut butter bars
directions: Melt butter and add remaining ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Melt 12 ounces chocolate chips and spread over top. Cool and cut.
Do not refrigerate.

title: chicken and sausage baked bean cassoulet(serves 8)
directions: In large kettle, combine beans and water.
Bring to a boil; boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour (do not drain).
To beans, add celery, carrots, bouillon cubes and salt.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Cut sausage into small pieces and brown in skillet. Remove sausage and set aside, reserving drippings.

title: crabmeat muffin snacks
directions: Mix together all ingredients, spread mixture on muffin halves, freeze.
Cut into fourths while still frozen.
Broil 5 to 7 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: ginger ale salad
directions: Drain the peaches.
Overlap slices in a 1 1/2-quart ring mold. Outline ring with quartered cherries.
Dissolve the gelatin in hot water; add ginger ale.
Spoon a little gelatin into mold around fruit.
Chill.
Chill remaining gelatin until thickened. Beat until fluffy with rotary beater.
Chop remaining peaches. Fold into gelatin with nuts.
Turn into mold over clear layer. Chill until firm.

title: corn au gratin
directions: Mix all ingredients in dish.
Top with bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on boxes and drain.
In 2-quart casserole dish put in cauliflower, then add others by layers.
Mix soup, Cheez Whiz and milk.
Pour over vegetables.
Stick through with fork so this will go through.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Last few minutes put a can of French onions over this.

title: corned beef stew
directions: Peel
potatoes;
cut up stew style.
Add finely chopped onion. Put
to
cook
over
medium
heat	in a thick pot with sufficient water.
Add
salt	and
pepper.
When potatoes are almost completely	cooked,
add tomato sauce and corned beef. Corned beef should be cut in small blocks. Let this simmer for 15 minutes. Serve over already cooked Water Maid rice.

title: bobbie's chicken and noodles
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Add soup and broth.
Cook to desired thickness.

title: italian sausage fettucini
directions: Boil sausage 45 minutes approximately.
Saute peppers/onions in lite olive oil until tender, not mushy.
(Slice peppers in long strips and onions sliced, not chopped.)
Cook fettucini until tender.
Lay out fettucini in bottom of pan (12 x 16 x 2-inches). Lay sausage on fettucini; cover lightly with some sauce.
Place peppers and onions over sausage.
Cover with rest of sauce.

title: easy german chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over coconut and pecans in a 9 1/2 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix butter and cream cheese. Warm and add powdered sugar; pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cucumber hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix cream cheese and Italian dressing mix; set aside. Score cucumber with a fork. Then slice into thin slices. Spread cream cheese mixture on party bread pieces. Place one cucumber slice on each piece of bread.
Sprinkle with dill weed.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream the shortening, 1 1/2 cups of sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Roll in small balls, then roll in combined 1 cup sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9-inch square pan with Pam. Combine dry ingredients.
In another bowl whisk egg whites, water and corn syrup.
Stir into dry ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until cake springs back.
Cool 10 minutes.
Makes 16 servings.
Contains 0 grams fat and 130 calories per serving.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Melt butter.
Pour over fruit and bake 1 hour uncovered at 350°.
Check from time to time.

title: light lemon pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, butter and nuts together until crumbly. Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and half the Cool Whip together. Spread on cooled crust.
Mix the puddings individually, each with 1 1/2 cups milk.
Prepare following directions on box.
When thick, spread on cream cheese.
Layer and top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: old-fashioned egg nog
directions: Separate eggs and beat yolks until blended.
Slowly add 1/4 cup sugar and beat at high speed.
Stir in milk, vanilla and salt. Chill.
Whip cream and set aside.
In a large bowl beat egg whites until light peaks form.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and beat to stiff peaks.
Fold in yolk mixture and whipped cream into egg whites.
Serve immediately.
Garnish with nutmeg and cinnamon sticks.
Makes 7 (8 ounce) servings.

title: greek cocktail meatballs(keftaidakia)
directions: Combine all ingredients except olive oil with 1/4 cup wine. Knead well, form into small meatballs (the size of a walnut) and place in an oiled baking pan.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven and pour 1/2 cup wine over the meatballs, shaking the baking pan to turn meatballs.
Place in a chafing dish to keep warm and pour the pan juices over the meat.

title: cavatini
directions: Mix all ingredients together, using 1/2 of cheese; place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot punch
directions: Put spices in percolator basket and perk mixture or wrap spices in cheesecloth and put in crock-pot and heat.

title: beet and pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot beet juice (one cup).
Add water if not enough beet juice.
Use pineapple juice for the cold liquid. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: apricot nectar salad
directions: Bring apricot nectar to boil; add jello, stirring until dissolved.
Stir in water and lemon juice.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Stir in next 3 ingredients; pour into an oiled 4-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold salad; garnish with apple slices, mandarin oranges and grapes, if desired.

title: salted peanut cookies
directions: Mix as given.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350°.
If you want to, you can decorate with peanuts. Cocktail peanuts work best.

title: french apple squares
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Blend in egg yolk and milk.
Roll out 1/2 dough to fit a jelly roll pan.
Spread on filling, then dot with butter.
Roll out remaining dough and pour over apples.
Brush with beaten egg white and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar or drizzle glaze over when cool.

title: sour cream muffins
directions: Mix all together and put into mini muffin pan (sprayed with Pam).
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together in a large mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour.
Beat well.
Beat in lemon extract and 7-Up.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured pan or mold. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let it cool.
Decorate with glaze or frosting (lemon).

title: icebox pickles
directions: In a gallon jar, combine all ingredients except cucumbers and onions.
Mix well, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Add sliced cucumbers and onions to mixture.
Refrigerate for 1 week to season.

title: butter icing
directions: Cook milk and cornstarch.
Cool.
Add sugar, butter, vanilla and salt.
Beat until smooth.
(Quick and Easy.)

title: spiced tea
directions: Heat, but don't boil.
Simmer
for
about
1 1/2 hours. Remove spices and serve orange
slices.
This can be stored in the refrigerator for about 2
days
and reheated in the microwave a cup at a time.

title: dirt cake
directions: In blender or by hand crush Oreos in one bowl. In another bowl, combine powdered sugar, cream cheese and butter. In another bowl, mix pudding, milk and
Cool
Whip. Combine all ingredients except Oreos. Put half the Oreos in the bottom of a dish and pour mixture over the Oreos then put the rest of the oreos on top and refrigerate.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Cook and drain macaroni.
Mix ingredients together in ungreased baking dish.
Cover and bake for 40 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with potato chips and bake 5 minutes more.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; let cool.
Add bananas, strawberries, pineapple and nuts.
Pour half in serving bowl. Spread with whipped topping.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and spices and bring to a boil.
Add peaches and cook until tender.
Put in hot jars and seal.
To heat jars, place in boiling water.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight before baking.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
For 6 muffins, you may add 1/4 cup crushed pineapple, cranberry-orange relish or applesauce.
Will keep for up to six weeks in refrigerator.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook and debone chicken (cut into cubes or tear into pieces).
Put chicken in bottom of baking dish.
Melt margarine in heated chicken broth.
Mix soups and milk together and pour over chicken pieces.
Mix margarine and chicken broth with stuffing until moist.
Spread mixture over other ingredients. Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Arrange in 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Lay Swiss cheese over chicken.
Spoon mixture of soup and water over chicken.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: no cook strawberry cheese cake
directions: Beat until fluffy the softened cream cheese. Gradually add milk, stirring. Stir until mixed.
Add lemon juice and vanilla and mix well.
Pour into crust.
Chill 2 to 3 hours, then garnish with strawberry mixture and serve.

title: chicken in a basket
directions: Butter both sides of bread with soft margarine.
Cut hole in center of bread in any shape you desire.
Put bread in skillet and lightly brown on one side.
Turn bread over and place egg in center hole.
Cook egg and season to taste with salt and pepper. Flip over and finish cooking and browning.
Serve hot.

title: hamburger rolls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then add cold milk.
Make round ball and roll into a rectangle shape about 8 x 10-inch or 1/4-inch thick.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix milk, sugar and butter in a heavy, 10-inch skillet.
Cook over medium heat and boil 4 minutes.
Remove.
Stir in marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla until evenly blended. Pour into buttered square pan.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits; roll in ball and roll in cinnamon and sugar that have been mixed together.
Place chopped nuts in bottom of greased Bundt pan.
Put rolled balls in Bundt pan.
Melt butter, brown sugar and water; boil 2 minutes and pour over biscuit balls. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Place on dish after cooking and pull apart and eat.

title: spaghetti pie(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Spoon cottage cheese on bottom of spaghetti crust.
Brown meat, onion and green pepper until vegetables are tender; drain. Add remaining ingredients.
Spoon over cottage cheese filling and crust (except Mozzarella).
Cover with foil; refrigerate 2 to 24 hours.
Bake, covered, for 50 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and add Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Let stand 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: chicken & rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done and debone.
Save 1 c. of broth.
Mix cream of celery and mushroom together.
Add rice, cheese and chicken broth. Put in large casserole dish.
Bake on 350 degrees until cheese melts.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and place into graham cracker crust. Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: In a saucepan, cook spaghetti in boiling water until done. Rinse with cold water; drain well.
Place in a large salad bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Toss lightly to mix.
Chill until serving.
Yields 15 to 20 servings.

title: my favorite snack:  pumpkin seeds
directions: Clean off the seeds.
Get an oiled pan and put butter on it. Put the seeds on and put them in the oven for about 20 minutes. Take them out, let them cool, put salt on it and eat.

title: "jim jam"
directions: Peel and core apples and tomatoes. Cut in quarters.
Measure the tomatoes and apples.
Add the same number cups in sugar.
Tie spices together in cheesecloth.
Add spices and vinegar. Simmer for 1 hour.
Add raisins and simmer 30 minutes.
Pack into hot clean jars and seal while hot.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix uncooked sausage, cheese, and Bisquick until thoroughly combined.
Crumple large sheet of foil, then smooth out and place on cookie sheet.
Form mixture into small balls.
Place on top of foil, about an inch apart.
(Balls may be frozen at this point.) Bake at 350° for 35 - 45 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serve hot with mustards.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets; peel and slice.
Add to mixture, then boil for 10 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix hamburger meat, salt and onion and add rice.
Work up all together.
Brown in skillet in oil.
Heat 1 can or more tomato soup until it gets hot.
Make hamburger into small balls, drop into tomato soup and cook until done.

title: dilled egg salad
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together.
Mix in diced, hard-boiled eggs.
Refrigerate for several hours to allow the flavors to blend.
A great change!

title: seattle slew
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain off fat.
Add everything else.
Cook 2 to 3 hours.

title: cherry congealed salad
directions: Mix
all ingredients together well in large bowl.
Pour into dish and chill.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Chop up lettuce finely, covering the bottom of a 14 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan. On top of lettuce, layer with diced up celery, onion and green pepper. Place frozen peas in a colander and run cold water over them. Drain peas, then layer over diced vegetables. Set aside. Mix mayo, sour cream and sugar together. Spread over peas. Sprinkle cheese over mayo mixture, then do the same with bacon bits. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve. Can be cut into squares.

title: judy's cake
directions: Cream the Crisco, butter and sugar.
Set aside.
Cook together milk and flour until thick.
Cool completely.
Add to the Crisco and butter mixture.
Mix well.
Frost the 4 layers of cake.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Roll gumdrops in 1 cup of flour and cut in small pieces.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add coconut, gumdrops, rolled oats and vanilla.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: pork pimentos and peas
directions: The night before, brown the pork with ginger.
The next day, heat the pork and ginger up again and add the round onion.
Add the bay leaves and the tomato sauce; simmer until the meat is soft.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add the peas and pimentos and cook for 3 minutes.
Serve.

title: squash casserole delight(low-fat recipe)
directions: Boil squash in small amount of water until tender. Drain. Place in casserole dish when cooled.

Season with garlic powder, salt, pepper and Butter Buds. Add onion. Stir in beaten eggs. Toast 2 to 3 slices of lite bread and crumble on top of casserole. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Add grated Cheddar cheese on top and bake 5 more minutes.

title: apricot chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine preserves and remaining ingredients; pour evenly over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil sugar and water 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add juices.
Blend thoroughly bananas and add.
Mix all ingredients together and freeze.
Remove from freezer two hours before serving.
Mash or chop and add 2 quarts 7-Up just prior to serving.

title: coffee-banana whip
directions: Cut banana into chunks.
Combine with coffee.
Add ice cream and vanilla.
Blend at high speed until mixture is thick and fluffy.

title: fudge brownies
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter and chocolate.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar.
Blend in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Mix well.

title: spicy oatmeal cookies(from the files of ola dortch williams)
directions: Beat the egg and add the sugar and milk.
Mix well and add the rolled oats.
Sift the Gladiola once and measure, then add the spices the soda and the baking powder.
Sift the dry ingredients into the first mixture and blend well.

Melt the butter or other shortening and add it, then the chopped nuts and the raisins. Drop the mixture onto a well-greased baking sheet or pie pan with a teaspoon and bake in hot oven for about 15 minutes.
The cookies will spread slightly in baking, so place them well apart on the sheet.
This recipe makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: dream bars
directions: Mix butter, salt, brown sugar and flour together. Pat into an ungreased 13x9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: asparagus blankets
directions: Cut off crust of bread.
Mix all of the remaining ingredients together, except the asparagus spears.
Spread mixture on each piece of bread.
Put 1 or 2 asparagus spears on each piece and roll up corner to corner.
Secure with a toothpick.
Place on a cookie sheet and brush with melted butter.
Bake about 10 minutes at 400° and serve hot.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: cajun rice casserole
directions: Fry bacon in skillet and drain.
Cool; crumble into small pieces.
Saute onion in bacon grease until golden.
Add garlic salt, onion salt, okra, tomatoes, Ro-Tel, parsley flakes, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Simmer uncovered 1 1/2 hours.
Meanwhile, prepare rice according to package directions.
Serve cooked mixture over rice.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Add enough Miracle Whip to moisten and to bond ingredients together.
Chill overnight for best results.

title: recovery soup
directions: Brown the meat and onions lightly.
Add all vegetables and juices, cook until tender.
Then add beans and herbs and heat. Use a large pot as it makes enough for 8-12 portions.
*Rosemary, Thyme and Basil make good seasonings.

title: mince beef on toast
directions: Crumble up raw ground beef; crush tomatoes and chop onion. Put these ingredients and the bay leaves in a pan and cook about 30 minutes to 45 minutes or until meat is cooked.
(Add salt to taste.)
After it is cooked thoroughly, add thickening.
Cook a little longer until it has thickened.
Serve over toasted bread.

title: cracker mix
directions: Mix crackers and oil in a large container with a wooden spoon. Then add garlic powder, dill weed, lemon pepper and Hidden Valley dressing mix.
Mix well and let stand for 4 hours.
Place crackers in a Tupperware bowl that has a tight-fitting lid.

title: quick rolls
directions: Put yeast cake in 1/4 cup warm water and 1 teaspoon sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Allow to foam about 10 minutes.
In the meantime, heat milk.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar, salt and butter or margarine; allow to cool.
Add milk mixture to yeast and mix in flour.
This is a very soft dough (too soft to knead).
Cover with a damp cloth and allow to rise in warm place, about 50 minutes.

title: posy icing
directions: Put all in mixer bowl and beat 5 to 8 minutes after blending. Good for graham crackers or cookies.
Keeps in refrigerator for months.
If you want chocolate frosting, add a little cocoa.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain and save juice from cherries and pineapple to make 1 cup of liquid.
Heat juice and add Jell-O.
Dissolve and cool.
Add pineapple, cherries, pecans and Coca-Cola.
Pour in pan.
Grate cream cheese over top.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with seasoned salt and lemon pepper.
Cut chicken into 1 inch cubes; brown in the butter.
Cut lemons into small wedges; squeeze onto chicken.
Add mushrooms; cook until tender.
Add the white wine; cook 2 minutes.
Remove the lemons. Pour off liquid and reserve.
Brown chicken in 2 tablespoons butter.
Serve over white rice and add liquid.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, soup, sour cream and cheese together.
Put in 11 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1 sleeve Ritz crackers, crushed.
Cut 1 stick of butter into cubes and place on top of crackers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in order listed.
Bake in an 8-inch square cake pan for 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and spread with mixture of remaining ingredients, mixed in order listed.
Return to oven and bake 20 minutes longer at 350°.
When the cookie mixture is cold, spread with the glaze.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together until fluffy.
Add bananas and eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Sift flour with salt and baking soda and add to banana mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake at 325° for an hour in a tube pan or two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Line bottoms of pans with waxed paper.

title: sweet cranberry apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line a 10-inch pie pan with pie crust. Mix all ingredients together and pour into crust.
Place top crust on, crinkle edges and make a few punctures in top crust to let steam escape.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and bake 50 additional minutes. Allow to cool before serving.

title: baked gouda appetizer
directions: Roll crescent dough flat.
Place cheese in middle of dough. Spread a layer of spicy mustard on top of cheese.
Fold
dough up and fit it around and over cheese to enclose it and press seams together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix together and chill before serving.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef with onion and celery and drain.
Combine all ingredients in Dutch oven and simmer for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Can be put in crock-pot on high for 8 to 10 hours.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine corn meal, flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Combine remaining ingredients and then add to the dry ingredients.
Stir only until moistened.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan or 10-inch heavy skillet. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until bread is golden brown and when toothpick in center comes out clean.

title: doris' drop cookies
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter in microwave.
Pour over cereal and mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half; scoop out seeds.
Add butter, brown sugar and sprinkle with pepper.
Place in roast pan and fill bottom of pan with 1/4-inch water.
Cook at 350° until tender.

title: margaret's margaritas
directions: Mix all ingredients well and freeze in large Tupperware type container.	When
ready
to
serve,
take out only amount needed (mixture will be slushy) and put in blender for about 1 minute. Add
jigger
of	Triple	Sec
or
Cointreau before blending if you like.

title: meatless chili
directions: Combine ingredients, adding water as needed for chili consistency.
Add chili powder, salt and black pepper to taste. Heat and simmer as long as desired.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Sift flour once, then measure.
Add baking powder and salt. Sift again.
Cut in shortening until it is a very fine texture. Keep mix in a container that is airtight and keep in cool, dry place.

title: grated au gratin potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in water until almost tender but still firm. Cool, peel and grate, using grater.

title: turnips and cornmeal dumplings
directions: Clean turnips and wash thoroughly 3 or 4 washings.
On first washing, add 2 or 3 tablespoons baking soda and let stand about 5 minutes.
Then continue washings.
On last washing, transfer to dishpan without dripping (leave as much water as possible on greens).
In a Dutch oven, heat bacon drippings or oil.
Place dripping turnips in pot and stir down slightly, making sure they do not stick to the bottom.
Add water to cover turnips well to make pot likker.
When turnips are tender, add dumplings.
Mix cornmeal, flour and salt.
Add enough water to make soft enough to drop by small teaspoonfuls.
Cook until done.
Serve with cornbread.

title: oven "fried" potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray cookie sheet with vegetable spray.
Slice potatoes 1/4 inch thick.
Coat with oil in a bowl. Arrange on cookie sheet and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake about 15 minutes or until fork-tender and cheese has browned.

title: sara's candied pecans
directions: Melt sugar and water together.
Add nuts when liquid.
Mix and stir until caramelizing over a medium-high heat.
Spread onto cookie sheet.
Lightly salt.
Place in a 350° oven and brown for 5 minutes.
Stir them around and bake for 5 additional minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let chill.

title: zucchini maison dillon
directions: Place zucchini in 2-quart bowl, cover with wax paper, and microwave for 15 minutes on High.
Stir once during cooking. Drain well.
In a separate bowl, place onions, olive oil and parsley and microwave 3 minutes.
Slice tomatoes.
Blend salt, cayenne pepper, garlic powder and Italian seasoning.
Layer in 3-quart casserole: zucchini, tomatoes, onions, and oil and seasonings.
Top with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Microwave covered 3 minutes on High.

title: ellie's tavern zucchini casserole
directions: Drain zucchini and combine with next 7 ingredients.
Mix last 4 ingredients and add to zucchini mixture.
Spoon into casserole and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden.
Let cool for 10 minutes.

title: mozzarella cheese dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve with chips, crackers or vegetables.

title: coconut cloud cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake as directed on package in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
While cake is baking, bring milk, sugar and half of coconut to a boil but do not continue to boil.
When cake comes out of oven, punch holes in cake and pour milk-sugar-coconut mixture evenly over cake, spreading coconut carefully.
Let cool completely at room temperature.
When cake is cool, spread with the whipped topping and top with remaining coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: oklahoma chicken loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Taste; add more seasoning if needed. Put in a 2-quart 2 x 6 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° until firm, about 1 hour.
This is good served with giblet gravy to which has been added 1 can mushroom soup.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: hello dolly pecan squares
directions: Melt butter and pour into graham cracker crumbs.
Pat crumbs into bottom of large glass Pyrex dish.
If not enough crumbs, mix more crumbs so entire pan is completely covered.
Sprinkle coconut flakes over crumbs, then chocolate morsels, then pecan pieces. Pour condensed milk over top of entire dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool 2 hours, then cut into pieces.

title: puerto rican cake
directions: Bake cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 12 to 15 minutes. Follow directions on box.
Mix cream cheese, pudding and milk in blender.
Pour over cooled cake.
Drain pineapple and sprinkle over cream mixture.
(Can add a layer of sliced bananas next.) Spread Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle nuts.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake up salmon and add tuna.
Add beaten eggs, flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add celery, bread and milk.
Mix well. Put in a buttered casserole.
Top with a small can of chicken gravy.
Bake in 400° oven for about 30 minutes.
You can put this in microwave instead and bake until done.

title: impromtu apple cake
directions: Place apples in greased pie tin (8 or 9-inch).
Combine 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on apples.
Cover with foil and bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: "jezebel sauce"
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into jars.
Serve over cream cheese with crackers or with poultry or meat.
If sauce is too hot, add more jelly.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Pour into casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: watch hill zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon. Combine oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in a large bowl.
Mix well and stir in flour mixture. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into oiled 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake for 40 minutes or until done.
Cool on wire rack.
Yields 12 squares.

title: overnight cookies
directions: Cream together butter, lard and 4 cups of brown sugar.
Pack, using your hands.
Add the black walnuts. Then add the eggs, flour, soda (dissolved in water), cream of tartar, vanilla and salt. Make the dough into long rolls.
Let stand overnight or refrigerate.
Cut in slices. Bake in moderate 400° oven about 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 12 dozen.

title: poppy chicken
directions: Place chicken in lightly greased pan.
Mix together the soup, sour cream and poppy seed, then pour over chicken.
Crush crackers; sprinkle on top.
Melt margarine; drizzle all over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick butter, crumbs and sugar.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 2 sticks butter, powdered sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat on high 15 minutes or longer.
Spread on crust. Slice bananas lengthwise on top.
Sprinkle on crushed pineapple. Spread Cool Whip over top.
Place cherries on top and sprinkle nuts.
Ready to serve 12 happy people.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 375° (350° for glass pan).
Heat soup, broth, chicken and vegetables to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Spread in ungreased rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour evenly over soup mixture (crust will rise during baking).
Bake about 30 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Stir until dissolved and add juice.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Serves 50.

title: darla's mexican dip
directions: Brown and drain sausage and ground beef.
Combine with remaining ingredients in crock-pot and heat until blended and hot. Use enough Velveeta cheese to thicken.
Serve with tortilla chips or corn chips.

title: autumn tea
directions: Place tea bags in a large heatproof bowl; add boiling water. Cover and steep for 8 minutes.
Discard tea bags.
Add the remaining ingredients to tea; stir until sugar is dissolved. Serve warm or over ice.
Yield: 3 quarts.

title: lemon sunshine cake
directions: Beat egg yolks, sugar, water, vanilla and lemon extract until very thick, at least 5 minutes.
Stir in cake flour.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until foamy. Slowly add 1 cup sugar, beating until thick, glossy peaks form. Gradually fold yolk mixture into egg whites.
Bake in ungreased tube pan at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Invert pan to cool. Remove from pan.
Slice into 3 layers.
Spread lemon filling between layers.
Dust with powdered sugar on top.

title: classic french silk pie
directions: Beat granulated sugar and butter until light and fluffy. Stir in vanilla, cream of tartar and chocolate.
Beat in eggs until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Pour into pie shell. Refrigerate until set.

title: vegetable lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne; drain and rinse in cold water.
Meanwhile, combine Ricotta, cream cheese, milk, onions, basil, garlic and oregano.
Blend until smooth.
Add vegetables; spread 3/4 cup on bottom of pan.
Add a layer of noodles, 1/4 remaining vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers, end with noodles and cover with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes, covered.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: mayonnaise muffins
directions: Mix and cook at 425° approximately 10 minutes.

title: potato salad(servings:  8. preparation time:  3.)
directions: Boil potatoes in salty water and quarter into large mixing bowl and add the rest of the ingredients.
Refrigerate for three hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except flour and soda,
in pan and boil for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add flour and soda.
Pour into a greased 8 x 11-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook hash browns, onion, broth and water slow for 30 minutes. Add soup, milk and butter. Simmer for 30 more minutes. Stir occasionally to keep from sticking.

title: mom's perfect pie crust(this crust is consistently flaky, no matter who makes it.)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Put egg into 1 cup measuring cup.
Add vinegar, then fill cup the rest of the way with water.
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Mix until moistened. Cover and let cool overnight.
Make five 7 ounce balls.
They may be frozen or used now.

title: colorful pea salad
directions: Cook carrots for 2 minutes. Add peas and cook additional 5 minutes. Drain, rinse in cold water, and then drain again. Place in a bowl and add celery, cheese and onions. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over the veggie mixture. Toss to cover. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: surprise stuffing
directions: In a large skillet, saute the squash and onion in butter until tender.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients. Transfer to a greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: classic sour cream cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press firmly in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Beat in eggs, then sour cream and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 50 to 55 minutes or until lightly browned around edge (center will be slightly soft).
Cool, then chill.
Top with cherry filling and garnish as desired.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In 2 1/2 or 3-quart saucepan bring sugar, margarine and milk to full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Once it comes to a full boil, cook 5 minutes.
Continue stirring.
Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla until melted. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Mix margarine and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Stir in corn syrup, salt and vanilla.
Fold in coconut and oatmeal, just enough to blend.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: spinach squares
directions: Mix eggs, margarine, milk, flour, salt and pepper.
Add to spinach and cheese.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Cut into squares.

title: corn chowder
directions: Dice and saute bacon until crisp.
Pour off fat.
Add red pepper and sliced scallions.
Cook 4 minutes.
Add chicken broth and creamed corn.
Add cream.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serves approximately 4.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add beet juice and vinegar.
Cook on medium heat until thick.
Add salt and butter; then add beets. Cover and continue cooking about 10 minutes.

title: haystacks
directions: Cook kidney beans for 5 minutes with taco sauce and chili seasoning mix.
Add meat and let simmer for about 2 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bones. Save broth and add 2 cups of water to cook spaghetti in. Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in 2 tablespoons butter. Stir in soup, Ro-Tel, chicken broth (1/2 to 1 cup), black olives and spaghetti. Sprinkle cheese on top with salt, pepper and paprika. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, covered, and 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and
3 cups of water.
Add onion soup mix into the mixture.

title: alfredo
directions: Cook noodles.
While noodles are cooking, mix the rest of ingredients.
Cook until thickened.
Pour over noodles just before serving.

title: marinated wieners
directions: Cut wieners into bite size pieces.
Combine remaining ingredients; add wieners and heat thoroughly.
This stores well in the refrigerator.
For smaller servings, reduce measurements. Good for parties and family gatherings.

title: easy freezer ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Line loaf pan with aluminum foil.
Pour mixture into pan.
Cover with foil.
Freeze at least 6 hours. Slice and serve.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Cut into thin slices and steam for 1 minute. Combine remaining ingredients in a glass jar.
Add mushroom slices and marinate, at least overnight.
Keep refrigerated.

title: oatmeal banana cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add egg and blend thoroughly. Stir in bananas and remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake in 375° oven until lightly browned and no imprint remains when touched (10 to 12 minutes). Makes 5 dozen.

title: lemon filling
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually add water, yolks, peel and juice over medium heat until it thickens.
Remove from heat and stir in butter.

title: grace's delight
directions: Prepare instant puddings as directed.
Cut Biscotti cookies lengthwise in half.
In a glass baking dish, approximately 10 x 13 x 2 1/2-inch, layer 1/2 of cookies.
Cover with vanilla pudding. Layer 1/2 of cookies.
Cover with chocolate pudding.
Keep refrigerated until just before serving when you top it off with whipped cream.
Serve by large spoon into dishes!

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and chop fine.
Marinate crowns in soy sauce for 1/2 hour.
Mix remaining ingredients with stems. Fill crowns with stuffing. Brush tops with soy sauce.
Broil for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Place on middle rack.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, salt, evaporated milk and vanilla.
Beat well and pour into freezer container and fill remainder with whole milk.
Add desired flavors, such as strawberry, pineapple, banana, etc.

title: macaroni ham salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except salad greens; toss lightly to mix well.
Chill.
Serve on salad greens.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: hawaiian haystacks
directions: Put chicken and broth in large pan; thicken broth with cornstarch.
Add cream of chicken soup and milk.
Cook large box of rice.
Pour creamed chicken on top of rice, then stack with the remaining ingredients.

title: brown sugar frosting
directions: Bring the brown sugar and half and half to a boil until the sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat; stir in the powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat until it is the right consistency.

title: haystack
directions: Heat and melt first 3 ingredients over low heat, then mix all together.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper to cool.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients together until flour is well mixed in. Bake in 350° preheated oven for 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in water.
Add chopped onion, bouillon, chicken base and pepper.
Cook and debone chicken.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In food grinder, grind cranberries and navel oranges.
To this, add sugar and food color.
In blender put small package strawberries and orange juice.
Blend until the berries disappear. Add to cranberry mixture.
Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add Knox gelatine.
Stir until dissolved.
Add to berry mixture.
Add pecans.
Chill overnight.
Whip cream and add sugar to taste.
Layer the cranberry salad with the whipped cream for a beautiful holiday salad.

title: dessert heroes
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package directions.
Cool and cut each panful into nine 3-inch squares.
Cut ice cream into 3-inch squares and place on 9 brownie squares.
Top with remaining brownies.
Wrap in plastic wrap and store in freezer until ready to serve.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Combine all ingredients and freeze in electric freezer.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix flour and sugar and then add next water, vinegar , salt and pepper.
Boil mixture until clear.
Cool.
Add mayonnaise and mustard.

title: delicate mint candies
directions: In a large bowl, blend corn syrup, butter and vanilla and peppermint extracts.
Add confectioners sugar; mix well.

title: southwestern pasta with tequila sauce
directions: Saute sliced garlic, jalapeno pepper and chicken strips or shrimp in oil until tender.
Remove from pan.
Add tequila to hot pan and allow alcohol to evaporate.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Add cream, chicken base and cilantro.
Bring to boil. (Careful not to scorch or burn!)
Lower heat and simmer until sauce is reduced by 1/2 and begins to thicken.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion in skillet until beef is browned. Drain.
Stir in salt and pepper; spread in plate.
Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick mix until smooth or mix 1 minute with hand beater. Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese olives
directions: Melt butter. Mix flour, Old English and melted butter together to make a paste. Flatten a small portion of paste in palm of hand and place 1 olive in the middle. Fold paste around olive. Repeat until paste is used up. Cook in a preheated oven at 350° until slightly browned.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into freezer container and freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: grandmomma's corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients together and stir up well.
If it mixes up a little dry, add water until it's about the consistency of pancake mix.
Before pouring into a 10 x 17-inch baking dish, put a thin layer of Crisco oil on bottom of dish and then pour in batter.
Bake about 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tourtiere(french canadian meat pie)
directions: Mix together; roll out dough into 9-inch foil plates for a double crust pie.

title: ten minute apple butter
directions: Heat applesauce and Sure-Jell.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to boil (10 minutes).
Can in hot jars.
Very good.

title: christmas cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Coat raisins, nuts, cranberries and apples with some of the flour mix.
Beat eggs slightly into oil.
Add oil mixture and fruits to flour mix. Stir until moistened.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: meringue pie shell
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Spray 9-inch pie pan with Pam.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy.
Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating until stiff and glossy.
Do not underbeat.
Pile into pan, pressing meringue up against side of pan.

title: party punch
directions: Put sherbet into large punch bowl and break into large chunks. Dilute orange juice as directed.
Add to sherbet.
Add pineapple juice and add ginger ale.
If desired, garnish with floating slices of fruit.

title: snow balls
directions: Cream together butter and

2 Tbsp. sugar. Add other ingredients. Shape into marble size balls. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. (Balls will be very light brown.) Roll in powdered sugar while hot. Then roll second time after cooled.

title: stay crisp slaw
directions: Cover all vegetables with water and chill.
Soften gelatin with water.
Mix all dry ingredients with oil; bring to a boil on the stove.
Add softened gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add hot mixture to drained vegetables.

title: old fashioned apple cake
directions: Mix together oil, eggs and sugar.
Add dry ingredients to this.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with bits.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool, then cut in squares.

title: orange poppy seed dressing or dip
directions: Mix together and serve over or with fresh fruit.

title: fritter fried okra
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a medium mixing bowl. Add eggs and milk.
Heat until smooth.
Add okra, stirring until coated.
Spoon okra into hot oil in large skillet.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown.

title: sour cream mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Boil until done.
Drain and pour into a mixing bowl.
Mix with electric mixer.
Pour in milk, margarine, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add sour cream last.
Cover until ready to serve.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello and marshmallows in 3 cups boiling water. Refrigerate until almost set, then fold in pineapple and Cool Whip.
Put into mold.

title: taco snack mix
directions: Melt butter; add taco seasoning.
Pour over other ingredients; mix well.
Store in airtight container.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix by hand thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Use Cream Cheese Icing, if desired.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put in lightly greased glass baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: ham and cheese roll-ups
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Mix until smooth and fluffy.
Spread on ham slices.
Roll each slice as for jelly roll. Place seam side down on plate and chill until firm.
Slice each roll into 8 pieces.
Place on toothpicks and arrange on tray. Serves about 12 people.

title: olive balls
directions: Mix cheese, flour and butter.
Make small balls with olives in center.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: corn beef salad
directions: Prepare jello and let cool.
Add mayonnaise and sour cream and beat with egg beater.
Add corn beef that has been broken into small pieces.
Add celery and green pepper.
Chill until firm.

title: pecan muffins
directions: Soften and mix butter and cream cheese.
Mix into flour.
Form into walnut size balls and press into mini muffin tin.

title: barbecue sandwiches
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion.
Drain off excess fat and add mustard, ketchup, water and chili powder.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: iowa fresh apple cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour and dry ingredients together.
Mix in apples to creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serve with Hot Caramel Sauce.

title: hanky-panky
directions: Brown all meat.
Drain fat.
Add seasonings.
Add cheese and stir.
Put on party rye bread.
Put in oven.
Broil 5 to 10 minutes.
Great for parties!
Freezes well.

title: crispy cheese cookies
directions: Cream the cheese and margarine, using electric mixer.
Blend in flour slowly.
Stir in rice cereal.
Drop batter by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet and flatten, with back of spoon or fork to make round wafers.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Store in airtight container to keep crisp.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: mama's tired cake
directions: Mix drained pineapple and cherry pie filling together.
Spread this mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Pour cake mix evenly over mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts and press them in lightly.
Slice 2 sticks of margarine and distribute evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: creole pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in shortening on both sides.
Add other ingredients and cover.
Cook until tender.

title: super easy chocolate fudge brownies
directions: Microwave sugar, butter and water in a large, microwave-safe bowl on High (100%) power for 4 to 5 minutes or until mixture bubbles, stirring once.
(Or heat sugar, butter and water in a medium saucepan just to boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.)
Add baking bars; stir until melted.

title: curried chicken and rice
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan (with lid), combine all ingredients except rice.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink, rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Put rice in 13 1/2 x 9-inch baking pan.
Add chopped onion. Cut sausage in rings and place on rice and onions.
Pour tomatoes on top.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: danish dessert ii
directions: Bring water, sugar and Kool-Aid
to
a boil.
Thicken with mixer of 3/4 cup clear jell and 1
cup
water.
Add
jello the same flavor as Kool-Aid.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine first four ingredients in iron skillet. Cook on medium high heat until you can hear the
peanuts pop. Remove from heat and stir in baking soda. Pour on a cookie sheet.

title: dip for raw vegetables
directions: Mix well and serve with raw vegetables.

title: ecuador cariucho(creamed potatoes)
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Melt fat in saucepan and saute onions.
Add cream, bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Add peanut butter, salt and a few drops of food coloring while stirring.
Pour over cooked, drained potatoes; garnish with chopped egg.
Serve with chicken or roast and lettuce salad. Serves 4.

title: holiday breakfast casserole
directions: Spread hash browns in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan and bake for 25 minutes in a 425° oven.
Layer ham, cheeses and chiles on hash browns.
Combine eggs, milk and salt and place on top of ham and cheese mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Place salsa on top when serving.
Can easily be doubled and baked in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: avocado salad
directions: Cut avocados, tomato and onion in chunks.
Add garlic salt to taste and Italian dressing.
You can serve now or let it set overnight.

title: half hour apple butter
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy 1 1/2 quart saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Cook 30 minutes on low heat.
Stir often.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Cream oil and brown sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: old fashioned honey wheat bread
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients in a saucepan, then add to rest of ingredients.
By hand, stir ingredients until stiff dough.
Knead dough about 2 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl.
Let rise in a warm place until doubled in size (45 to 60 minutes).

title: fudge
directions: In a small bowl, mix water and 8 packages of chocolate mix. Add vanilla. Stir well to make a stiff paste. Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on wax paper.
Freeze in airtight container.
You can have 1 piece a day.

title: shoepeg corn salad
directions: Put in a bowl and mix.

title: "seven layer salad"
directions: Break lettuce into a large bowl with tight-fitting lid. Layer with next 5 ingredients.
Spread mayonnaise over top; seal to edge.
Cover and refrigerate.
Do not stir until ready to serve.

title: fruit cake christmas cookies
directions: Mix like cake.
Add 7 cups nuts, chopped fine. Add all pecans or 1/2 pecans and 1/2 walnuts.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam. Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 300° until done, approximately 20 minutes.

title: hommous tahini(chickpea filling)
directions: Blend until smooth.
Good as sandwich spread or pita bread filling.

title: quick and easy sausage supper
directions: Place sausage in Dutch oven and cover with water.
Cook for one-half hour.
Add
carrots
and
cook
for
another half hour. Add potatoes and cabbage and cook until done.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Add remainder.
Pour into greased and floured (10 x 15 x 1-inch) pan.
Top with 1 cup chopped walnuts or pecans or almonds.
Bake 15 minutes in 375° oven.

title: punch for a bunch
directions: Combine juices, sugar and mint leaves.
Chill.
Before serving, add ginger ale, soda water and strawberries.
Pour in large punch bowl over ice ring.
Serves around 50 people.

title: amish tomatoes
directions: Pick young, small okra pods, cut off each end and slice into 1/2-inch slices.
Roll okra in a mixture of 1 cup corn meal and 1/2 cup flour.
Heat 1/4 cup oil in an iron skillet.
Add okra and fry until golden brown, stirring often.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper on when okra is about half done.
Add more oil if needed.

title: nell's breakfast tacos
directions: Crack eggs into large bowl.
Add milk, salt and pepper. Beat or mix together very well.
Take large skillet, butter it very well and turn stove on medium low.
Add butter, onion and hot sauce to
eggs.
Cook until done.
Warm up tortillas.
Put 5 tablespoons of
egg mixture in middle of tortilla; add bacon and as much
cheese
as
you
want.
Roll
tightly.
Wrap with Saran Wrap
and
they
stay
fresh
all
week.
Please
label. Remember onion and hot sauce are optional.

title: south of the border burgers
directions: Combine first six ingredients, the beef, onion, catsup and spices.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into six patties.
Grill over medium-hot coals to desired doneness.
Spread 2 tablespoons of combined sour cream, catsup and chilies on bottom half of each roll.
Place burgers on top.
Top with additional sauce, lettuce and tomato if desired.
Top with remainder of rolls or buns.

title: muddy buddies
directions: Since I've not time to be

title: aunt ruth's chocolate cake
directions: Combine sugar, lard and cocoa.
Add boiling water and mix well.
Add flour and soda alternately with buttermilk.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill in covered bowl overnight. Serve chilled.

title: pretzel animals
directions: In a big bowl, mix together yeast, water, sugar and salt. Stir in flour.
Knead on table until dough is smooth.
Shape dough into animal shapes.
Brush with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with salt. Bake in oven set at 425° for 15 minutes or until browned.

title: french toast in microwave oven
directions: Beat egg in bowl.
Dip a slice of bread in the egg, turning it until it's well coated.
Place bread on a plate.
Pour any remaining egg from the bowl on top.
Cook at High power for 1 minute.
Serve with butter, syrup or other favorite topping.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with whole graham crackers.
Mix pudding with milk and add Cool Whip.
Put 1/2 the pudding on top of the graham crackers.
Put another layer of graham crackers on top of the pudding.
Top those crackers with remaining pudding.
Top with third layer of graham crackers.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Saute onion and garlic.
Mix thoroughly in bowl with meat, rice, egg, salt and pepper; set aside.
Boil head of cabbage in salted water until leaves can be cut away from center core, one at a time.
Cook until leaves are soft and pliable.
Drain and cool to touch.
Strip down core, which runs down back of leaf.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer rice, broccoli, and chicken in 9 x 13 casserole dish. Mix soups, butter, cheeses and milk in pot and heat on low until cheese and butter melts. Pour over ingredients in dish, sprinkle Progresso Bread crumbs on top and bake in preheated oven at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: nancy reagan's baja california chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with seasoning salt and pepper.
Crush garlic into oil and vinegar in skillet.
Saute chicken pieces until golden brown, turning frequently.
Remove.
Place in a baking dish.
Pour sherry over pieces and place in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: grannie bryant cherry pie
directions: Sift sugar and flour together.
Cream with butter (or oleo). Add eggs; mix well.
Add vanilla and fold in cherries.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake about 1 hour in a 325° oven.

title: cauliflower salad supreme
directions: Layer ingredients in the order listed in a large salad bowl.

title: ground beef grand style
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Combine cream cheese, soup and milk.
Add salt, catsup and olives.
Add all to ground beef and mix well.
Put in a casserole dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Place biscuits around edge of casserole.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or longer until biscuits are browned.

title: chocolate water cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350°.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Spread in baking dish.
Melt margarine and stir in stuffing mix.
Spread on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick beef stew
directions: In a 6-quart electric wok, cook butter, potatoes, onions, celery and carrots to tender.
Add beef broth, tomatoes and roast beef with gravy.
Mix good as it cooks.
Cook until thickened. Eat with crackers or rice.
Season to taste.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add liquid ingredients.
Preheat grease in frying pan.
Drop in hot grease by tablespoons.
Cook until both sides are golden brown.
If grease is deep enough in pan puppies roll over alone.

title: cheese - coconut  balls
directions: Mash cheeses and combine them thoroughly with electric mixer. Chill for 1 hour.
Shape into 1 inch balls and roll in coconut.

title: garlic shrimp and linguini
directions: Stir-fry broccoli in 1/4 cup oil for 5 minutes.
Add remaining oil.
Add mushrooms, shrimp, garlic, onion, lemon rind, salt and pepper.
Stir-fry for 5 minutes.
Add to buttered linguini. Sprinkle with Romano.
Toss well.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, and baking soda.
Stir in nuts and peel.
Combine egg, juice, and oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring just till moistened.
Pour into greased 8 1/2-inch by 4 1/2-inch by 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.
Wrap and store overnight.

title: orange jello dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add sherbet while Jell-O is hot. Add rest of ingredients, adding cold water last.
Jell in refrigerator.

title: blueberry-buttermilk bread
directions: Cream together brown sugar and oil.
Add egg.
Add buttermilk alternately with dry ingredients.
Stir in vanilla, blueberries and nuts.
Turn into greased loaf pans, 3 1/4 x 7 x 2 1/4-inches or 3 pans, 2 1/2 x 5 x 2-inches.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until bread tests done.

title: feather light cheesecake
directions: Combine milk, Dream Whip, sugar and cream cheese in a large mixing bowl.
Whip until thoroughly blended.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.

title: chicken delight
directions: Put ingredients in a long baking dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Sift the flour and salt together; add the beaten eggs, then the milk.

Beat two minutes with eggbeater and pour into hot baking pan, 9 x 12-inches, with the beef drippings from the roast beef. Have the drippings bubbling hot before pouring in the pudding. Bake in 450° hot oven for 30 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 15 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve immediately.
Serves 6. Serve with roast beef.

title: veal scaloppine
directions: Pound veal and dredge in flour.
Place in a hot pan with olive oil, garlic, 1 teaspoon butter, salt and pepper.
Turn meat and add remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly and serve.
Serves 2. Buono Appetito!

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until very light.
Beat 5 egg yolks and 3 egg whites with butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and 3/4 cup milk. Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add to other mixture.
Put into four greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peppercorn steak
directions: Pound pepper into both sides of steaks using a meat mallet. Set steaks aside.
Saute onions and mushrooms in butter in a skillet until tender.
Add bacon and wine; set aside and keep warm.
Place steaks on a broiler rack coated with cooking spray. Place rack in broiler pan.
Broil 4 to 6 inches from heat for 8 to 10 minutes on each side or to desired degree of doneness.
Remove steaks to a platter and top with mushroom mixture.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tuna spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let set at least 1 hour.
Serve at room temperature.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix everything together in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Baste on meat.

title: carl gohs' zucchini bread
directions: Beat the eggs until light and foamy.
Add the sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla and mix lightly but well.
Combine the flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon and add to the egg-zucchini mixture.
