Stir until well blended, add nuts and pour into two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour. Cool on a rack.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in margarine for 10 minutes.
Combine beaten eggs with zucchini mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Separate and spread the crescent rolls into a pie pan or casserole dish.
Pour mixture in and cook for 20 minutes in 375° oven.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef; then drain.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer slowly for 2 hours.
Can be made in crock-pot.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water in bowl; stir in apricot nectar.
Add pineapple and mandarin oranges; mix well.
Stir in almonds and cream cheese; spoon into serving bowl.
Chill in refrigerator, stirring once as mixture begins to set.
Chill until set.
(Cream cheese chops better when very cold.)
Yields 12 servings.

title: bengal tea
directions: Shake or mix well.
Keep in airtight container.
Use one tablespoon per cup of boiling water.

title: mixed up rice salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Sprinkle paprika on top for color. Chill.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice and cook carrots; add green pepper and onion.
Heat vinegar, oil, sugar, tomato soup and mustard.
Pour over carrots. Marinate overnight.
Serve either hot or cold.
Serves 10.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar until crumbly.
(A fork will do it well.)
Save 2 tablespoons of this mixture.
Put the rest in the pie shell.
Pour the vanilla pudding over top.
Top off with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of mix on top. This is a quick, tasty dessert.

title: russian salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water. Add blueberries with juice. Let set until it starts to jell.

title: lottie's noodleburger
directions: Brown the ground beef; stir in the mushroom soup.
Add the cooked noodles in a quantity you desire.
Mix together thoroughly and serve.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute hamburger meat and onion in skillet.
In large pan, mix chicken soup, mushroom soup, enchilada sauce, chopped green chilies and can milk.
Cut up Velveeta cheese.
Heat and stir. Add cheese and stir until melted.
In large covered dish, layer meat, sauce and tortillas.
Cook in oven at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: pita pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spread pita bread with tomato paste. Sprinkle with oregano.
Add olives, mushrooms and top with cheese. Bake on cookie sheet 10 minutes until cheese is bubbly.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth for 20 minutes.
Saute celery in butter.
Now mix with picked off chicken, soup, salad dressing and onion.
Mix gently and bake for 45 minutes.
Can put bread crumbs or cornflakes on top.

title: raisin bread pudding(microwave cooking)
directions: In an ungreased 2-quart microproof dish, mix bread and raisins. Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt until well blended.
In a 4 cup glass measure, heat milk and margarine on High for 4 1/2 minutes or until steaming hot.
Stir in egg mixture.
Pour over bread and raisins.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes.
Center will be slightly soft but will set as pudding cools.
Serves 6.

title: ensalada de papas(mexican potato salad)
directions: Boil potatoes, peel and mash. Add mayonnaise more or less just for taste. Add onions that are chopped. Dice the apples with peel left on. Add to rest of ingredients. Mix well. Chill.

title: pecan pumpkin loaf
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Add pumpkin; beat well.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in vanilla.
Combine the dry ingredients; add to pumpkin mixture alternately with water.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan to a wire rack.
Yield: 1 loaf.

title: clam chowder
directions: In a large, wide saucepan, gently fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
To bacon drippings, add onion; fry gently, stirring often, until rich, golden brown.
Remove onion.
Drain clams and add liquid to saucepan along with chicken broth and potatoes.
Boil gently, covered, until potatoes are tender.
Gradually stir 1 cup cream into flour, keeping smooth.
Add to the potato mixture with remaining cream, drained clams and salt and pepper.
Cook over moderately low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in the milk, bacon and onion.
Reheat.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter; add egg yolks and beat well. Add sugar; beat well. Add flavoring; beat well. Add a little flour at a time until of consistency for cookie press. Press cookies on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Do not brown. Add any decoration you wish. If dough gets too stiff before all are baked, add a drop or two of milk to batter. Take cookies up before they get cold.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine; mix with dressing (or corn flakes). Put half of this mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread evenly. Put cooked chicken bites over this mixture.
Mix sour cream and cream of chicken soup; spread over chicken. Sprinkle remaining crumbs or flakes over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: olive-cheese balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients to make dough.
Form mixture around each olive to make a small ball and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10-15 minutes, until slightly browned. Serve warm. Can be prepared ahead of time and put into freezer unbaked.
Bake as directed without thawing.

title: uncooked butter frosting
directions: Put butter in small mixing bowl.
Cream a few seconds with warmth of hands.
Add sugar, salt, milk and vanilla.
Beat with beater until blended and fluffy.

title: baked country omelet
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 12 x 8-inch (2-quart) baking dish.
In a large bowl, combine potato slices and 3 cups boiling water.
Let stand while preparing sausage.
In medium skillet, cook sausage and onion until sausage is crumbly and no longer pink.
Drain. Drain potato slices and add to sausage mixture with green pepper and mushrooms.
Blend well.
Beat in milk and eggs. Pour evenly over potato-sausage mixture in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Garnish with green pepper rings.

title: "mamaw" collins old fashioned custard pie
directions: Bake in medium oven.
Makes one nine inch pie.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies according to package directions.
Cool.
Punch holes in brownies with a fork.
Pour Kahlua over brownies.
Set aside.
Whip up chocolate mousse according to package directions. Break Skor or Heath bars into small pieces in food processor or by tapping them with a hammer (right in wrapper).
Sensation bits can be used out of bag without chopping.
Break up half the brownies and place in the bottom of a glass trifle dish.
Cover with half the mousse, layer with half the candy and then add half the whipped topping.
Repeat layers with the remaining ingredients.

title: pot of collards
directions: In a large cooking pot filled halfway full of water, boil the pig tails or side meat.
(Make sure you have washed off the salt.) Boil until it is tender.

title: apple-cream coffee cake
directions: Mix in small bowl the walnuts, cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar. In large bowl, cream butter and 1 cup sugar, then add eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir dry ingredients at low speed alternately with sour cream.
Spread half of batter in greased 9-inch tube pan and top with apple, pared, cored and thinly sliced and half of walnut mixture.
Then add remaining batter and top with remaining walnut mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool for 30 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: There's work to do, deadlines to meet,

title: cabbage soup
directions: Melt butter in a large kettle.
Stir in cabbage and onions; mix well.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle flour over top and mix well.
Gradually add water.
Heat until it boils.
Add broth, sugar, pepper, caraway seed, tomatoes, lemon juice and salt. Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: swiss bacon pleasers
directions: Separate dinner rolls into triangles.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan (well-greased).
Place cheese over top of dough.
Combine eggs, milk and onion and pour over cheese.
Sprinkle with bacon and parsley flakes.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; cut into squares.

title: deviled pork chops
directions: Combine all ingredients but the onion and worcestershire sauce and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add the onion and sauce pouring over the chops in a shallow baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 50 minutes or until done.
Turn chops once while cooking.

title: brownies and frosting
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, chocolate syrup and flour.
Mix well.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar, corn syrup and cornstarch in double boiler until thick.
Add food coloring and jello to mixture.
When mixture is cool, add strawberries.
Pour into a 9-inch baked pie crust.
Top with Dream Whip and serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand. Make 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: ruby chicken
directions: Place breasts in single layer in 13 x 9-inch baking dish; mix other ingredients, pour over chicken.
Marinate overnight.
Bake at 350° for one to two hours or until done.

title: geologist's field sandwich
directions: The Geologist's Field Sandwich is designed for the culinary inept and non-gifted.
Its purpose is primarily the provision of a staple to be consumed between a hearty breakfast and the evening meal.
No Precambrian, Paleozoic or Ice Age contaminants are included in this recipe.

title: spinach dip
directions: Process in food processor the cottage cheese.
Place in bowl. Press spinach between paper towels until barely moist.
Add spinach and remaining ingredients to cheese.
Stir; cover and refrigerate 3 hours.
Serve with crackers or raw vegetables.
Yields 3 cups.

title: cheese brunch bake(kids cookery breakfast)
directions: Lightly grease an ovenproof baking dish, about 9 x 9 x 2-inch. Put 4 slices of bread next to each other on the bottom of the prepared dish.
Put a slice of cheese on top of each slice of bread.
Sprinkle bacon bits over top of cheese.
Top with other 4 slices of bread.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Combine chicken, onion and cheese; fold into noodles.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over noodles.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fudgey mocha nut pie
directions: Melt butter over low heat; add cocoa and stir until smooth. Stir in condensed milk, water, eggs, coffee and chocolate chips and whisk until blended.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Pour into shell and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Garnish with whipped cream. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: golden glow pickles
directions: Peel cucumbers, slice in half and remove seeds.
Dice into chunks.
Cook slowly with all ingredients added, until tender. Fill jars with cukes and pour hot sauce over them.
Seal tight. Ready after 24 hours cooling.

title: hard sauce
directions: Cream the butter; add sugar gradually.
Add vanilla.
Keep in refrigerator until served.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra well; drain and set aside. Place 1 clove garlic and 1 hot pepper into each of hot sterilized pint jars.
Pack jars firmly with okra, leaving 1/2 in. headspace; add 1 tsp dill seed to each.

title: sour cream cherry cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine, sugar and beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat in sour cream and vanilla until smooth.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and baking soda and beat into creamed mixture, alternately with the milk until well mixed.
Pour 1/2 the batter into lightly greased tube pan with a removable bottom.
Spread the cherry pie filling over the batter in the pan and then pour remaining batter over the pie filling.
Add topping to cake before baking.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let cake cool before removing sides of pan.
DO NOT INVERT CAKE.

title: sherry cheese pate
directions: Put in dish for serving.
Add chutney and green onions on top.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: scrambled eggs
directions: Mix in a bowl all together and stir until it turns orange. Pour in flat pan and push with spatula.
Then clean the bowl. Then put in bowl.
Scrambled eggs in bowl.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix oil and spices together.
Toss crackers in mixture until covered.

title: taco bake
directions: Place cooked spiral noodles in a greased dish.
Brown hamburger meat in jar of pizza sauce.
Pour this over noodles. Top with grated cheese.
Heat at 350° until cheese melts.

title: poultry seasonings
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in an airtight container for use in sauces, gravy and any pork or poultry dishes.
Also good in meat loaf.

title: sherry blackberry cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Crumble nuts in bottom.
Combine cake mix and pudding.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour on Sherry Berry Sauce.

title: corn salad(club member: jason baldwin)
directions: Drain corn very well. Chop green onions and cut tomatoes into bite-size pieces. Add to the whole kernel corn; stir.
Toss with mayonnaise to suit your taste. Serve cold.

title: fresh blackberry pie
directions: Combine water, sugar, cornstarch and gelatin in small saucepan.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and cook 3 to 4 minutes, stirring occasionally, until thickened.
Let cool completely.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer about 10 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Cover cake mixture with chocolate chips and nuts. Bake as directed on box.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pineapple juice with pudding and Tang.
Mix all fruit together; pour pineapple-pudding mixture over fruit and let chill overnight.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: meat loaf
directions: Chop bell pepper and onion; beat eggs.
Mix ground chuck, eggs, bell pepper, onion, crackers, tomato sauce, salt and pepper together.
Shape into 3 loaves.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 2 hours (cover with foil).

title: grilled cheese and ham on rye bread
directions: Spread 4 slices of bread with butter or margarine and 4 slices with mustard.
Place cheese, then ham on buttered bread.
Top with remaining bread.
Cut in halves diagonally.
Grill sandwiches in small amount of butter in skillet or on a griddle over medium heat until golden, about 3 minutes on each side.
Our favorite.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Boil solution for 5 minutes.
Pour boiling hot brine over cukes in jars.
Put on heated caps and screw band tight.
Process in hot water or bath 5 minutes.
Fills 5 pint jars.
Add more sugar for sweeter pickles.

title: phyllis deaton's p-nut butter bars
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour and stir only until blended.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: prize winning cheese cake
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust using about 2 cups crumbs and 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Press on bottom of spring-form pan. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate date nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In a large saucepan, over low heat, melt butter and chocolate.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in sugar until well blended.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flour, dates, nuts, vanilla and salt until smooth.
Spread in pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until center is set (do not overbake). Cool in pan on wire rack.
Cut into bars.
Makes 32 (2 x 1 1/2-inch) bars.

title: mandarin coconut bowl
directions: Fold in one cup of dairy sour cream.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serve in lettuce cup.
Makes 8 servings.

title: green tomato relish
directions: All ingredients must be run through a food chopper and drained; one way is to run through a colander.
Add together vinegar, spice and sugar.
Heat all together until simmer stage or until ingredients change color.
Put in jars and seal; cold packing helps sealing process.
Makes about six 1/2 pints.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix and pour into 2 graham cracker crusts, either bought or made.
Freeze and cut just before serving. May substitute orange juice for lemonade and chocolate crust.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Stir in salsa, corn, mayonnaise and chili powder. Layer 1/2 each of meat mixture, cheese and chips.
Repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with shredded lettuce and tomatoes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream all wet ingredients slowly, add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Set oven at 350 degrees for 15 - 20 minutes.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Cut up potato and apple, thinly.
Over medium high heat, mix beef, potato and apple.
Stir-fry until almost done.
Mix 2 tablespoons peach jam and 2 tablespoons red wine.
Fix onion soup mix as directed.
Add to peach jam mixture.
Add pepper and add to beef stir-fry and simmer until peppers are done and jam is over beef, stirring well.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar in large bowl.
Combine Coca-Cola, oil, margarine and baking cocoa in medium saucepan; mix well.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla; mix well. Add to flour mixture, stirring to mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake tests done.
Pour frosting over warm cake.
Yield: 15 servings.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Set pineapple aside.
Add water to pineapple juice to measure 1 cup.
Stir in lemon juice.
Stir juice mixture into gelatin mixture; chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Add cranberries, oranges, celery and walnuts to gelatin mixture; mix well.
Pour into lightly oiled 10-cup mold.
Chill until set.
Yields 15 to 18 servings.

title: buttermilk lemon pie
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar and flour.
Slowly stir in buttermilk. Cook in double boiler until mixture begins to thicken, stirring constantly.
Add beaten egg yolks; cook 2 minutes more.
Blend in lemon juice, peel and butter.
Pour into pie shell.

title: christmas wreath
directions: Melt marshmallows and oleo in double boiler. Add green food coloring. Pour over cornflakes and shape into wreath. Decorate with red hots.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage together. Drain. Add mushrooms, spaghetti sauce and macaroni twists to meat.
In a large pan (13 x 9-inch), layer 1/2 sauce mix, 1/2 pepperoni and 1/2 cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can be made ahead. Also freezes well.

title: baked fish
directions: Wash and dry fillets. Lay them flat in a large baking dish. Put on tomato sauce and sprinkle grated cheese, salt, pepper and oregano on top.
Add the minced garlic and put the oil over everything.
Do not cover.
Bake at 350° until done.
Serves 4.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix in pan the butter, sugar, cocoa and milk.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: kluski noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salt water until al dente; drain.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until thoroughly heated.

title: communion bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Makes 4 circles, 3/8-inch thick.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce(part i)
directions: In bowl, combine all ingredients.

title: trash (puppy chow)
directions: You will need 1 white kitchen trash bag.
In 2-quart saucepan, melt butter, chips and peanut butter.
Pour Crispix into large bowl.
Slowly pour chocolate mixture over Crispix.
(It will look horrible.)
Gently fold mixture over until all Crispix are covered.

title: tropical blush
directions: In punch bowl, combine juice, honey, orange rind and ginger. Refrigerate at least 2 hours to blend flavors.

title: easy low cholesterol pie crust
directions: Mix until forms into a ball.
Roll out between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Makes 1 crust.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix after adding each ingredient.
Fill 2 graham cracker crusts.
Chill overnight, or you can freeze.

title: ma cannons greens
directions: Cook pigtails until almost tender.
Add mustard and turnip greens; cook slow until tender, approximately 30 minutes.
Add salt and sugar.
Remove from boiler and enjoy.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash, drain and hull strawberries.
Cut in half.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually add water mixing until smooth.
Add 1/2 of the strawberries.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens, about 5 minutes.
Cover and continue cooking 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and cool.
Fold in remaining strawberries.
Pour into pastry shell and chill.
Serve topped with sweetened whipped cream.

title: butternut squash souffle
directions: Combine spices and sugar.
Add to squash.
Beat eggs and add to squash.
Add milk and margarine.
Stir in vanilla.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers and bake until set, another 30 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute onion, garlic and meats.
Drain grease and add sauce, parsley, salt, pepper, basil and oregano.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Mix all cheeses and egg.
Sprinkle with parsley and oregano.
In a large rectangular baking dish, place in layers sauce, lasagna and cheese mixture.
Repeat layers ending with a layer of lasagna covered with sauce.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cookies and cream
directions: Add confectioners sugar to egg; mix until smooth.
Beat in sour cream.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix well and add crushed cookies; stir well to combine.
Cover and refrigerate overnight to soften cookie crumbs.
Any cream-filled sandwich cookies could be used.
Using 3/4 of cookies is my preference.
Cookies smell when they set; it's up to you.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Add all other ingredients and mix. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Dissolve cranberry sauce in hot water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the sweet potatoes, butter, spices, eggs, brown sugar, Karo syrup and milk.
Stir to mix well. Add the nuts, raisins or coconut, if you like.
Pour into a greased 1-quart baking dish and bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until well set.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: jo's chili(healthy eating)
directions: Saute garlic, onions and meat of your choice in heavy kettle sprayed with Pam until meat is almost done.
Add tomatoes and seasonings and simmer for about an hour until meat is done.
Add beans and simmer another 30 minutes.
Put the chili to bed and enjoy the next day when the flavors have had time to mellow.
As for the red wine, enjoy it while you tend the chili or throw a dash in the pot!

title: fried peanut butter and banana sandwich
directions: Spread peanut butter extra thick between slices of bread. Melt margarine in frypan on medium heat.
Brown sandwich on both sides in melted oleo.
Mash banana.
Open browned sandwich and spread on banana.
Serve hot with knife and fork.

title: baked mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients except the last 2 and pour into a 1-quart casserole dish. Dot top with butter slivers and sprinkle the 2 tablespoons water over the top of the mushrooms.
Cover dish. Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: company chunks
directions: Cover cucumbers with boiling water; let stand until next morning and drain.
Repeat next three mornings.
On 5th day, drain and slice into 1/2-inch slices.
Combine remaining ingredients. Bring to boiling point and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 2 days. On 3rd day, bring to a boiling point and seal in hot jars.
(I let slices heat, then pack in jar.
Let brine come to boiling and pour over slices.)

title: seasoned salt
directions: Place all ingredients in a pint jar and seal.
Shake until mixture is completely blended.
Yields about 3/4 cup of seasoning.

title: coconut icebox dessert
directions: Pat this mixture into a well-greased oblong pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add unbeaten eggs and blend thoroughly.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add with vanilla to other mixture.

title: suf soof (tabouleh)
directions: Wash bulgur and soak in water to cover for 1/2 hour.
Mince parsley, spearmint and onions.
Chop tomatoes finely.
Mix well. Drain bulgur and squeeze dry with hands.
Add to vegetables. Combine oil, lemon juice, salt, pepper and cinnamon.
Mix into salad.

title: molding for a perfect housewife
directions: For
a delicious loaf of bread, go to the nearest store and purchase
one.
Bring
it
home and "pig out".
(Best yet, call my mother.)

title: irish cream
directions: Whip eggs; add all ingredients.
Stir well and pour into containers.
Store in refrigerator right away.
For richer flavor, double recipe and add small bottle inexpensive Irish cream.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: For crust, unroll crescent rolls and pat into a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake according to package directions. Cool. Meanwhile, in a small mixing bowl, stir together the cream cheese, mayo, dill weed and salad dressing mix. Spread evenly over cooled crust. Sprinkle with broccoli and tomatoes, then cheese. This makes a fancy dish when cut in 1 inch squares.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix ingredients together with fork until crumbly and sprinkle over apples, which have been placed in a buttered baking dish. Pour margarine over mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Brown and season hamburger, celery and onion in frying pan. Cook rice.
Mix everything together and bake until heated real well.

title: oriental cabbage salad
directions: Combine noodles, cabbage, sunflower seeds, almonds and onions in large bowl.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Sift flour into a large bowl.
Beat eggs and add, with the rest of the ingredients, to the flour in large bowl.
Mix well, making sure all of the zucchini and flour is mixed into the batter. Scrape bowl often and keep mixing for several minutes.
Pour into greased pans and bake in preheated oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Let cool in pans on wire racks and store in plastic wrap and freeze.

title: shipwreck
directions: Slice tomatoes in greased casserole.
Crumble meat on top and sprinkle on 1/2 the seasonings and onion.
Spread kidney beans over all.
Use remaining seasonings.
Cover all with soup.
Bake at 375°, covered, for 1/2 hour.
Uncover and bake for 1 hour more.

title: peach pecan pie
directions: Mix together peaches, sugar, tapioca, lemon juice and almond extract.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Pick salmon to remove skin and bones.
Add eggs, onion and enough oats to hold together (about 1/2 cup).
Take 1/4 cup of mixture and shape into little logs.
Roll in oats.
Fry in 1/4 cup oil and turn to brown on all sides.
Drain on paper towels.

title: country garden noodles
directions: Cook egg noodles according to directions.
Melt oleo in large skillet.
Saute ham and broccoli; season to taste.
When noodles are tender, toss with skillet mixture.
Add tomatoes and serve.

title: broccoli and onions in cheese sauce
directions: Cook broccoli and onions together in a medium saucepan (use package directions for broccoli).
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup of the liquid, and set vegetables aside.

title: margret's pecan pie
directions: Combine first six ingredients in saucepan over low heat.
Stir frequently to avoid burning.
Cook until bubbling.
Remove from heat and set aside to cool slightly.
Spread 3/4 cup over the bottom of each pie shell.
Pour 1/2 of filling in each pan over the top of the pecans.
Bake at 350° for the first 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 355° until firm.
Cool on racks.

title: steamed broccoli rabe
directions: Trim and cut off bottom stalks of broccoli rabe.
Rinse broccoli rabe.
Heat olive oil in heavy skillet.
Add garlic and red pepper.
Add broccoli rabe and saute until leaves are wilted. Cover skillet and lower heat.
Cook broccoli rabe for about 5 minutes, turning occasionally.
Add more oil, pepper or garlic if desired.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil sugar, water and cornstarch, stirring constantly, until mixture turns clear and thickens.
Add jello.
Put berries in baked pie shell; pour cooked mixture over berries and cool.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Place in buttered pan and bake in a moderate oven over hot water if desired.

title: chocolate caramel dip
directions: Melt caramels in water.
Add chocolate, cream and nuts.
Serve with fresh fruit, cubed pound cake, etc.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place rice in large bowl while it is still hot.
Mix in soup, Cheez Whiz and milk.
Place frozen broccoli into a cup of hot water.
Pick out any leaves, drain and place in the bowl.
Stir in well.
Bake in baking casserole dish at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Chop Oreo cookies in blender, about 3 at a time; set aside. Soften cream cheese with tablespoon and gradually add 1 cup powdered sugar and set aside; add 3 cups milk to the vanilla instant pudding mix.
Mix together cream cheese and powdered sugar with Cool Whip and mix with pudding.
Then layer cookies, pudding, cookies, pudding.
Put in flowerpot and stick flower in center.

title: mellowscotch pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, salt and water.
Boil over moderate heat to a thick syrup (about 5 minutes).
Mix 1/4 cup milk and cornstarch to thin paste.
Add 1 3/4 cups cold milk, then combine with hot syrup.
Cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly. Stir a small amount of mixture into beaten egg yolks; return to mixture.
Cook a few minutes longer.
Add butter and vanilla. Cool.
Pour into shell.

title: meat, potato, vegetable cake
directions: Saute onion in bacon drippings.
Brown ground beef and sauteed onion.
Meanwhile, boil peeled potatoes for mashing and cook peas (or other vegetable) in butter.
In a casserole dish put peas (1st layer), ground beef (2nd layer) and on top spread the mashed potatoes.
Bake 15 minutes in a 300° oven.
Serve hot.

title: oven-fried sesame chicken
directions: Combine sesame seeds, flour, and pepper.
Dip chicken pieces into soy sauce and dredge in sesame seed mixture.
Arrange chicken, bone side down, in shallow baking dish.
Drizzle margarine over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 40-45 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: garlic butter
directions: Shape mixture with wet hands and chill.
Put on bread to serve with pasta.

title: single guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados in bowl and squeeze 1/2 lemon into avocados to prevent them from turning black.
Also it gives avocado dip a nice twang!
Stir in your salsa with the avocado and lemon mixture. Ole!
You have Guacamole!
Makes about 2 cups.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix turkey, 1/4 cup barbecue sauce, oats, onion and egg whites.
Shape into loaf.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Top with 1/4 cup barbecue sauce.

title: red and green pepper relish
directions: Grind vegetables together.
Cover with boiling water; let stand 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Add salt, sugar and vinegar.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pour in hot, sterilized jars and seal.

title: josie's pineapple shortbread
directions: Break bread into small pieces and add pineapple. Beat eggs lightly and add to bread mixture. Stir in sugar and melted butter. Pour into a greased baking pan, 10 x 10-inch.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Put in colander and rinse.
Let drain and mix all together.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream shortening and add sugar.
Mix soup, water and baking soda; add to sugar mixture.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder and spices together; add to creamed mixture.
Add raisins and nuts. Use a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: hearty beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain. Set aside. Saute hamburger and onion until all red is gone from meat.
Drain. Add remaining ingredients and simmer until cheese is melted. Add macaroni and pour into a large casserole dish.
Place in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: greek spaghetti
directions: Cook onions, garlic and rosemary in butter until clear.
Brown lean ground beef in separate pan.
Add to onion mixture.

title: "dig-in" cake
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar in one bowl.

title: company special steak dish
directions: Cut steaks into smaller pieces if desired.
Salt and pepper steak on both sides.
Brown in hot oil.
Remove to Pyrex dish. Mix mushroom soup and water and heat.
Add sprinkle of garlic powder and olives.
Add the red wine and
stir well.
After heating, pour over steak pieces.
Bake in a 375° oven approximately 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve individual servings on bed of cooked rice.
